261 VOID
262 MiProcessLoaderEntry (
263  IN PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry,
264  IN LOGICAL Insert
265  )
266 
267 /*++
268 
269 Routine Description:
270 
271  This function is a nonpaged wrapper which acquires the PsLoadedModuleList
272  lock to insert a new entry.
273 
274 Arguments:
275 
276  DataTableEntry - Supplies the loaded module list entry to insert/remove.
277 
278  Insert - Supplies TRUE if the entry should be inserted, FALSE if the entry
279  should be removed.
280 
281 Return Value:
282 
283  None.
284 
285 Environment:
286 
287  Kernel mode. Normal APCs disabled (critical region held).
288 
289 --*/
290 
291 {
292  KIRQL OldIrql;
293 
294  ExAcquireResourceExclusiveLite (&PsLoadedModuleResource, TRUE);
295  OldIrql = KeRaiseIrqlToSynchLevel ();
296  ExAcquireSpinLockAtDpcLevel (&PsLoadedModuleSpinLock);
297 
298  if (Insert == TRUE) {
299  InsertTailList (&PsLoadedModuleList, &DataTableEntry->InLoadOrderLinks);
300 
301 #if defined (_WIN64)
302 
303  RtlInsertInvertedFunctionTable (&PsInvertedFunctionTable,
304  DataTableEntry->DllBase,
305  DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage);
306 
307 #endif
308 
309  }
310  else {
311 
312 #if defined (_WIN64)
313 
314  RtlRemoveInvertedFunctionTable (&PsInvertedFunctionTable,
315  DataTableEntry->DllBase);
316 
317 #endif
318 
319  RemoveEntryList (&DataTableEntry->InLoadOrderLinks);
320  }
321 
322  ExReleaseSpinLockFromDpcLevel (&PsLoadedModuleSpinLock);
323  KeLowerIrql (OldIrql);
324  ExReleaseResourceLite (&PsLoadedModuleResource);
325 }
326 
327 typedef struct _MI_LARGE_PAGE_DRIVER_ENTRY {
328  LIST_ENTRY Links;
329  UNICODE_STRING BaseName;
330 } MI_LARGE_PAGE_DRIVER_ENTRY, *PMI_LARGE_PAGE_DRIVER_ENTRY;
331 
332 LIST_ENTRY MiLargePageDriverList;
333 
334 ULONG MiLargePageAllDrivers;
335 
336 VOID
337 MiInitializeDriverLargePageList (
338  VOID
339  )
340 
341 /*++
342 
343 Routine Description:
344 
345  Parse the registry settings and set up the list of driver names that we'll
346  try to load in large pages.
347 
348 Arguments:
349 
350  None.
351 
352 Return Value:
353 
354  None.
355 
356 Environment:
357 
358  Kernel mode, Phase 0 Initialization.
359 
360  Nonpaged pool exists but not paged pool.
361 
362  The PsLoadedModuleList has not been set up yet AND the boot drivers
363  have NOT been relocated to their final resting places.
364 
365 --*/
366 {
367  PWCHAR Start;
368  PWCHAR End;
369  PWCHAR Walk;
370  ULONG NameLength;
371  PMI_LARGE_PAGE_DRIVER_ENTRY Entry;
372 
373  InitializeListHead (&MiLargePageDriverList);
374 
375  if (MmLargePageDriverBufferLength == (ULONG)-1) {
376  return;
377  }
378 
379  Start = MmLargePageDriverBuffer;
380  End = MmLargePageDriverBuffer + (MmLargePageDriverBufferLength - sizeof(WCHAR)) / sizeof(WCHAR);
381 
382  while (Start < End) {
383  if (UNICODE_WHITESPACE(*Start)) {
384  Start += 1;
385  continue;
386  }
387 
388  if (*Start == (WCHAR)'*') {
389  MiLargePageAllDrivers = 1;
390  break;
391  }
392 
393  for (Walk = Start; Walk < End; Walk += 1) {
394  if (UNICODE_WHITESPACE(*Walk)) {
395  break;
396  }
397  }
398 
399  //
400  // Got a string - add it to our list.
401  //
402 
403  NameLength = (ULONG)(Walk - Start) * sizeof (WCHAR);
404 
405 
406  Entry = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
407  sizeof (MI_LARGE_PAGE_DRIVER_ENTRY),
408  'pLmM');
409 
410  if (Entry == NULL) {
411  break;
412  }
413 
414  Entry->BaseName.Buffer = Start;
415  Entry->BaseName.Length = (USHORT) NameLength;
416  Entry->BaseName.MaximumLength = (USHORT) NameLength;
417 
418  InsertTailList (&MiLargePageDriverList, &Entry->Links);
419 
420  Start = Walk + 1;
421  }
422 
423  return;
424 }
425 
426 LOGICAL
427 MiUseLargeDriverPage (
428  IN ULONG NumberOfPtes,
429  IN OUT PVOID *ImageBaseAddress,
430  IN PUNICODE_STRING BaseImageName,
431  IN ULONG Pass
432  )
433 
434 /*++
435 
436 Routine Description:
437 
438  This routine checks whether the specified image should be loaded into
439  a large page address space, and if so, tries to load it.
440 
441 Arguments:
442 
443  NumberOfPtes - Supplies the number of PTEs to map for the image.
444 
445  ImageBaseAddress - Supplies the current address the image header is at,
446  and returns the (new) address for the image header.
447 
448  BaseImageName - Supplies the base path name of the image to load.
449 
450  Pass - Supplies 0 when called from Phase for the boot drivers, 1 otherwise.
451 
452 Return Value:
453 
454  TRUE if large pages were used, FALSE if not.
455 
456 --*/
457 
458 {
459  PFN_NUMBER PagesRequired;
460  PFN_NUMBER ResidentPages;
461  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
462  PVOID SmallVa;
463  PVOID LargeVa;
464  PVOID LargeBaseVa;
465  LOGICAL UseLargePages;
466  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
467  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
468  MMPTE PteContents;
469  PMMPTE SmallPte;
470  PMMPTE LastSmallPte;
471  PMI_LARGE_PAGE_DRIVER_ENTRY LargePageDriverEntry;
472 #ifdef _X86_
473  ULONG ProcessorFeatures;
474 #endif
475 
476  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= APC_LEVEL);
477  ASSERT (*ImageBaseAddress >= MmSystemRangeStart);
478 
479 #ifdef _X86_
480  if ((KeFeatureBits & KF_LARGE_PAGE) == 0) {
481  return FALSE;
482  }
483 
484  //
485  // Capture cr4 to see if large page support has been enabled in the chip
486  // yet (late in Phase 1). Large page PDEs cannot be used until then.
487  //
488  // mov eax, cr4
489  //
490 
491  _asm {
492  _emit 00fh
493  _emit 020h
494  _emit 0e0h
495  mov ProcessorFeatures, eax
496  }
497 
498  if ((ProcessorFeatures & CR4_PSE) == 0) {
499  return FALSE;
500  }
501 #endif
502 
503  //
504  // Check the number of free system PTEs left to prevent a runaway registry
505  // key from exhausting all the system PTEs.
506  //
507 
508  if (MmTotalFreeSystemPtes[SystemPteSpace] < 16 * (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT)) {
509 
510  return FALSE;
511  }
512 
513  if (MiLargePageAllDrivers == 0) {
514 
515  UseLargePages = FALSE;
516 
517  //
518  // Check to see if this name exists in the large page image list.
519  //
520 
521  NextEntry = MiLargePageDriverList.Flink;
522 
523  while (NextEntry != &MiLargePageDriverList) {
524 
525  LargePageDriverEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
526  MI_LARGE_PAGE_DRIVER_ENTRY,
527  Links);
528 
529  if (RtlEqualUnicodeString (BaseImageName,
530  &LargePageDriverEntry->BaseName,
531  TRUE)) {
532 
533  UseLargePages = TRUE;
534  break;
535  }
536 
537  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
538  }
539 
540  if (UseLargePages == FALSE) {
541  return FALSE;
542  }
543  }
544 
545  //
546  // First try to get physically contiguous memory for this driver.
547  // Note we must allocate the entire large page here even though we will
548  // almost always only use a portion of it. This is to ensure no other
549  // frames in it can be mapped with a different cache attribute. After
550  // updating the cache attribute lists, we'll immediately free the excess.
551  // Note that the driver's INIT section will be subsequently freed
552  // and clearly the cache attribute lists must be correct to support that
553  // as well.
554  //
555  // Don't take memory below 16MB as we want to leave that available for
556  // ISA drivers supporting older hardware that may require it.
557  //
558 
559  NumberOfPages = (PFN_NUMBER) MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (
560  NumberOfPtes,
561  MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT);
562 
563  PageFrameIndex = MiFindContiguousPages ((16 * 1024 * 1024) >> PAGE_SHIFT,
564  MmHighestPossiblePhysicalPage,
565  MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT,
566  NumberOfPages,
567  MmCached);
568 
569  //
570  // If a contiguous range is not available then large pages cannot be used
571  // for this driver at this time.
572  //
573 
574  if (PageFrameIndex == 0) {
575  return FALSE;
576  }
577 
578  //
579  // Add the contiguous range to the must-be-cached list so that the excess
580  // memory (and INIT section) can be safely freed to the page lists.
581  //
582 
583  if (MiAddCachedRange (PageFrameIndex, PageFrameIndex + NumberOfPages - 1) == FALSE) {
584  MiFreeContiguousPages (PageFrameIndex, NumberOfPages);
585  return FALSE;
586  }
587 
588  //
589  // Try to get large virtual address space for this driver.
590  //
591 
592  LargeVa = MiMapWithLargePages (PageFrameIndex,
593  NumberOfPages,
594  MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE,
595  MmCached);
596 
597  if (LargeVa == NULL) {
598  MiRemoveCachedRange (PageFrameIndex, PageFrameIndex + NumberOfPages - 1);
599  MiFreeContiguousPages (PageFrameIndex, NumberOfPages);
600  return FALSE;
601  }
602 
603  LargeBaseVa = LargeVa;
604 
605  //
606  // Copy the driver a page at a time as in rare cases, it may have holes.
607  //
608 
609  SmallPte = MiGetPteAddress (*ImageBaseAddress);
610  LastSmallPte = SmallPte + NumberOfPtes;
611 
612  SmallVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (SmallPte);
613 
614  while (SmallPte < LastSmallPte) {
615 
616  PteContents = *SmallPte;
617 
618  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
619  RtlCopyMemory (LargeVa, SmallVa, PAGE_SIZE);
620  }
621  else {
622 
623  //
624  // Retain this page in the large page mapping to simplify unload -
625  // ie: it can always free a single contiguous range.
626  //
627  }
628 
629  SmallPte += 1;
630 
631  LargeVa = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)LargeVa + PAGE_SIZE);
632  SmallVa = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)SmallVa + PAGE_SIZE);
633  }
634 
635  //
636  // Inform our caller of the new (large page) address so the loader data
637  // table entry gets created with it & fixups done accordingly, etc.
638  //
639 
640  *ImageBaseAddress = LargeBaseVa;
641 
642  if (Pass != 0) {
643 
644  //
645  // The system is fully booted so get rid of the original mapping now.
646  // Otherwise, we're in Phase 0, so the caller gets rid of the original
647  // mapping.
648  //
649 
650  SmallPte -= NumberOfPtes;
651 
652  //
653  // No explicit TB flush is done here, instead the system PTE management
654  // code will handle this in a lazy fashion.
655  //
656 
657  PagesRequired = MiDeleteSystemPageableVm (SmallPte,
658  NumberOfPtes,
659  0,
660  &ResidentPages);
661 
662  //
663  // Non boot-loaded drivers have system PTEs and commit charged.
664  //
665 
666  MiReleaseSystemPtes (SmallPte, (ULONG)NumberOfPtes, SystemPteSpace);
667 
668  InterlockedExchangeAdd (&MmTotalSystemDriverPages,
669  0 - (ULONG)(PagesRequired - ResidentPages));
670 
671  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (ResidentPages,
672  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_UNLOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE1);
673 
674  MiReturnCommitment (PagesRequired);
675  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_DRIVER_UNLOAD1, PagesRequired);
676  }
677 
678  //
679  // Note the unused trailing portion (and their resident available charge)
680  // of the large page mapping are kept as they would have to be mapped
681  // cached to avoid TB attribute conflicts, and therefore cannot be placed
682  // on the general purpose freelists.
683  //
684 
685  return TRUE;
686 }
687 
688 
689 VOID
690 MiCaptureImageExceptionValues (
691  IN PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry
692  )
693 
694 /*++
695 
696 Routine Description:
697 
698  This function stores the exception table information from the image in the
699  loader data table entry.
700 
701 Arguments:
702 
703  DataTableEntry - Supplies the kernel's data table entry.
704 
705 Return Value:
706 
707  None.
708 
709 Environment:
710 
711  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL or below, arbitrary process context.
712 
713 --*/
714 
715 {
716  PVOID CurrentBase;
717  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeader;
718 
719  CurrentBase = (PVOID) DataTableEntry->DllBase;
720 
721  NtHeader = RtlImageNtHeader (CurrentBase);
722 
723 #if defined(_X86_)
724  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.DllCharacteristics & IMAGE_DLLCHARACTERISTICS_NO_SEH) {
725  DataTableEntry->ExceptionTable = (PCHAR)LongToPtr(-1);
726  DataTableEntry->ExceptionTableSize = (ULONG)-1;
727  } else {
728  PIMAGE_LOAD_CONFIG_DIRECTORY32 LoadConfig;
729  ULONG LoadConfigSize;
730  if (IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_LOAD_CONFIG < NtHeader->OptionalHeader.NumberOfRvaAndSizes) {
731  LoadConfig = (PIMAGE_LOAD_CONFIG_DIRECTORY32)((PCHAR)CurrentBase +
732  NtHeader->OptionalHeader.DataDirectory[IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_LOAD_CONFIG].VirtualAddress);
733  LoadConfigSize = NtHeader->OptionalHeader.DataDirectory[IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_LOAD_CONFIG].Size;
734  if (LoadConfig &&
735  LoadConfigSize &&
736  LoadConfig->Size >= RTL_SIZEOF_THROUGH_FIELD(IMAGE_LOAD_CONFIG_DIRECTORY32, SEHandlerCount) &&
737  LoadConfig->SEHandlerTable &&
738  LoadConfig->SEHandlerCount
739  )
740  {
741  DataTableEntry->ExceptionTable = (PVOID)LoadConfig->SEHandlerTable;
742  DataTableEntry->ExceptionTableSize = LoadConfig->SEHandlerCount;
743  } else {
744  DataTableEntry->ExceptionTable = 0;
745  DataTableEntry->ExceptionTableSize = 0;
746  }
747  }
748  }
749 #else
750  if (IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXCEPTION < NtHeader->OptionalHeader.NumberOfRvaAndSizes) {
751  DataTableEntry->ExceptionTable = (PCHAR)CurrentBase +
752  NtHeader->OptionalHeader.DataDirectory[IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXCEPTION].VirtualAddress;
753  DataTableEntry->ExceptionTableSize =
754  NtHeader->OptionalHeader.DataDirectory[IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXCEPTION].Size;
755  }
756 #endif
757 }
758 
759 
760 NTSTATUS
761 MmLoadSystemImage (
762  IN PUNICODE_STRING ImageFileName,
763  IN PUNICODE_STRING NamePrefix OPTIONAL,
764  IN PUNICODE_STRING LoadedBaseName OPTIONAL,
765  IN ULONG LoadFlags,
766  OUT PVOID *ImageHandle,
767  OUT PVOID *ImageBaseAddress
768  )
769 
770 /*++
771 
772 Routine Description:
773 
774  This routine reads the image pages from the specified section into
775  the system and returns the address of the DLL's header.
776 
777  At successful completion, the Section is referenced so it remains
778  until the system image is unloaded.
779 
780 Arguments:
781 
782  ImageFileName - Supplies the full path name (including the image name)
783  of the image to load.
784 
785  NamePrefix - If present, supplies the prefix to use with the image name on
786  load operations. This is used to load the same image multiple
787  times, by using different prefixes.
788 
789  LoadedBaseName - If present, supplies the base name to use on the
790  loaded image instead of the base name found on the
791  image name.
792 
793  LoadFlags - Supplies a combination of bit flags as follows:
794 
795  MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION :
796  - Supplies whether to load this image in session space.
797  Each session gets a different copy of this driver with
798  pages shared as much as possible via copy on write.
799 
800  MM_LOAD_IMAGE_AND_LOCKDOWN :
801  - Supplies TRUE if the image pages should be made
802  non-pageable.
803 
804  ImageHandle - Returns an opaque pointer to the referenced section object
805  of the image that was loaded.
806 
807  ImageBaseAddress - Returns the image base within the system.
808 
809 Return Value:
810 
811  Status of the load operation.
812 
813 Environment:
814 
815  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL or below, arbitrary process context.
816 
817 --*/
818 
819 {
820  LONG OldValue;
821  ULONG i;
822  ULONG DebugInfoSize;
823  PIMAGE_DATA_DIRECTORY DataDirectory;
824  PIMAGE_DEBUG_DIRECTORY DebugDir;
825  PNON_PAGED_DEBUG_INFO ssHeader;
826  PMMPTE PointerPte;
827  SIZE_T DataTableEntrySize;
828  PWSTR BaseDllNameBuffer;
829  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
830  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY TempDataTableEntry;
831  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY FoundDataTableEntry;
832  NTSTATUS Status;
833  PSECTION SectionPointer;
834  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders;
835  UNICODE_STRING PrefixedImageName;
836  UNICODE_STRING BaseName;
837  UNICODE_STRING BaseDirectory;
838  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes;
839  HANDLE FileHandle;
840  HANDLE SectionHandle;
841  IO_STATUS_BLOCK IoStatus;
842  PCHAR NameBuffer;
843  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
844  ULONG NumberOfPtes;
845  PCHAR MissingProcedureName;
846  PWSTR MissingDriverName;
847  PWSTR PrintableMissingDriverName;
848  PLOAD_IMPORTS LoadedImports;
849  LOGICAL AlreadyOpen;
850  LOGICAL IssueUnloadOnFailure;
851  LOGICAL LoadLockOwned;
852  ULONG SectionAccess;
853  PKTHREAD CurrentThread;
854 
855  PAGED_CODE();
856 
857  if (LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) {
858 
859  ASSERT (NamePrefix == NULL);
860  ASSERT (LoadedBaseName == NULL);
861 
862  if ((PsGetCurrentProcess()->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_IN_SESSION) == 0) {
863  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
864  }
865  }
866 
867  LoadLockOwned = FALSE;
868  LoadedImports = (PLOAD_IMPORTS) NO_IMPORTS_USED;
869  SectionPointer = NULL;
870  FileHandle = (HANDLE)0;
871  MissingProcedureName = NULL;
872  MissingDriverName = NULL;
873  IssueUnloadOnFailure = FALSE;
874  FoundDataTableEntry = NULL;
875 
876  NameBuffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
877  MAXIMUM_FILENAME_LENGTH,
878  'nLmM');
879 
880  if (NameBuffer == NULL) {
881  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
882  }
883 
884  //
885  // Initializing these is not needed for correctness, but
886  // without it the compiler cannot compile this code W4 to check
887  // for use of uninitialized variables.
888  //
889 
890  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (NumberOfPtes = (ULONG)-1);
891  DataTableEntry = NULL;
892 
893  //
894  // Get name roots.
895  //
896 
897  if (ImageFileName->Buffer[0] == OBJ_NAME_PATH_SEPARATOR) {
898  PWCHAR p;
899  ULONG l;
900 
901  p = &ImageFileName->Buffer[ImageFileName->Length>>1];
902  while (*(p-1) != OBJ_NAME_PATH_SEPARATOR) {
903  p--;
904  }
905  l = (ULONG)(&ImageFileName->Buffer[ImageFileName->Length>>1] - p);
906  l *= sizeof(WCHAR);
907  BaseName.Length = (USHORT)l;
908  BaseName.Buffer = p;
909  }
910  else {
911  BaseName.Length = ImageFileName->Length;
912  BaseName.Buffer = ImageFileName->Buffer;
913  }
914 
915  BaseName.MaximumLength = BaseName.Length;
916  BaseDirectory = *ImageFileName;
917  BaseDirectory.Length = (USHORT)(BaseDirectory.Length - BaseName.Length);
918  BaseDirectory.MaximumLength = BaseDirectory.Length;
919  PrefixedImageName = *ImageFileName;
920 
921  //
922  // If there's a name prefix, add it to the PrefixedImageName.
923  //
924 
925  if (NamePrefix) {
926  PrefixedImageName.MaximumLength = (USHORT)(BaseDirectory.Length + NamePrefix->Length + BaseName.Length);
927 
928  PrefixedImageName.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (
929  NonPagedPool,
930  PrefixedImageName.MaximumLength,
931  'dLmM');
932 
933  if (!PrefixedImageName.Buffer) {
934  ExFreePool (NameBuffer);
935  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
936  }
937 
938  PrefixedImageName.Length = 0;
939  RtlAppendUnicodeStringToString(&PrefixedImageName, &BaseDirectory);
940  RtlAppendUnicodeStringToString(&PrefixedImageName, NamePrefix);
941  RtlAppendUnicodeStringToString(&PrefixedImageName, &BaseName);
942 
943  //
944  // Alter the basename to match.
945  //
946 
947  BaseName.Buffer = PrefixedImageName.Buffer + BaseDirectory.Length / sizeof(WCHAR);
948  BaseName.Length = (USHORT)(BaseName.Length + NamePrefix->Length);
949  BaseName.MaximumLength = (USHORT)(BaseName.MaximumLength + NamePrefix->Length);
950  }
951 
952  //
953  // If there's a loaded base name, use it instead of the base name.
954  //
955 
956  if (LoadedBaseName) {
957  BaseName = *LoadedBaseName;
958  }
959 
960 #if DBG
961  if (NtGlobalFlag & FLG_SHOW_LDR_SNAPS) {
962  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_TRACE_LEVEL,
963  "MM:SYSLDR Loading %wZ (%wZ) %s\n",
964  &PrefixedImageName,
965  &BaseName,
966  (LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) ? "in session space" : " ");
967  }
968 #endif
969 
970  AlreadyOpen = FALSE;
971 
972 ReCheckLoaderList:
973 
974  //
975  // Arbitrary process context so prevent suspend APCs now.
976  //
977 
978  ASSERT (LoadLockOwned == FALSE);
979  LoadLockOwned = TRUE;
980 
981  CurrentThread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
982  KeEnterCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
983 
984  KeWaitForSingleObject (&MmSystemLoadLock,
985  WrVirtualMemory,
986  KernelMode,
987  FALSE,
988  (PLARGE_INTEGER)NULL);
989 
990  //
991  // Check to see if this name already exists in the loader database.
992  //
993 
994  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
995  while (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
996 
997  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
998  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
999  InLoadOrderLinks);
1000 
1001  if (RtlEqualUnicodeString (&PrefixedImageName,
1002  &DataTableEntry->FullDllName,
1003  TRUE)) {
1004  break;
1005  }
1006 
1007  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
1008  }
1009 
1010  if (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
1011 
1012  //
1013  // Found a match in the loaded module list. See if it's acceptable.
1014  //
1015  // If this thread already loaded the image below and upon rechecking
1016  // finds some other thread did so also, then get rid of our object
1017  // now and use the other thread's inserted entry instead.
1018  //
1019 
1020  if (SectionPointer != NULL) {
1021  ObDereferenceObject (SectionPointer);
1022  SectionPointer = NULL;
1023  }
1024 
1025  if ((LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) == 0) {
1026 
1027  if (MI_IS_SESSION_ADDRESS (DataTableEntry->DllBase) == TRUE) {
1028 
1029  //
1030  // The caller is trying to load a driver in systemwide space
1031  // that has already been loaded in session space. This is
1032  // not allowed.
1033  //
1034 
1035  Status = STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES;
1036  }
1037  else {
1038  *ImageHandle = DataTableEntry;
1039  *ImageBaseAddress = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
1040  Status = STATUS_IMAGE_ALREADY_LOADED;
1041  }
1042  goto return2;
1043  }
1044 
1045  if (MI_IS_SESSION_ADDRESS (DataTableEntry->DllBase) == FALSE) {
1046 
1047  //
1048  // The caller is trying to load a driver in session space
1049  // that has already been loaded in system space. This is
1050  // not allowed.
1051  //
1052 
1053  Status = STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES;
1054  goto return2;
1055  }
1056 
1057  AlreadyOpen = TRUE;
1058 
1059  //
1060  // This image has already been loaded systemwide. If it's
1061  // already been loaded in this session space as well, just
1062  // bump the reference count using the already allocated
1063  // address. Otherwise, insert it into this session space.
1064  //
1065 
1066  Status = MiSessionInsertImage (DataTableEntry->DllBase);
1067 
1068  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1069 
1070  if (Status == STATUS_ALREADY_COMMITTED) {
1071 
1072  //
1073  // This driver's already been loaded in this session.
1074  //
1075 
1076  ASSERT (DataTableEntry->LoadCount >= 1);
1077 
1078  *ImageHandle = DataTableEntry;
1079  *ImageBaseAddress = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
1080 
1081  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1082  }
1083 
1084  //
1085  // The LoadCount should generally not be 0 here, but it is
1086  // possible in the case where an attempt has been made to
1087  // unload a DLL on last dereference, but the DLL refused to
1088  // unload.
1089  //
1090 
1091  goto return2;
1092  }
1093 
1094  //
1095  // This driver is already loaded in the system, but not in
1096  // this particular session - share it now.
1097  //
1098 
1099  FoundDataTableEntry = DataTableEntry;
1100 
1101  DataTableEntry->LoadCount += 1;
1102 
1103  ASSERT (DataTableEntry->SectionPointer != NULL);
1104 
1105  SectionPointer = DataTableEntry->SectionPointer;
1106  }
1107  else if (SectionPointer == NULL) {
1108 
1109  //
1110  // This image is not already loaded.
1111  //
1112  // A NULL SectionPointer indicates this thread didn't already load
1113  // this image below either, so go and get it.
1114  //
1115  // Release the load lock first as getting the image is not cheap.
1116  //
1117 
1118  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
1119  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
1120  LoadLockOwned = FALSE;
1121 
1122  InterlockedOr (&MiFirstDriverLoadEver, 0x1);
1123 
1124  //
1125  // Check and see if a user wants to replace this binary
1126  // via a transfer through the kernel debugger. If this
1127  // fails just continue on with the existing file.
1128  //
1129 
1130  if ((KdDebuggerEnabled) && (KdDebuggerNotPresent == FALSE)) {
1131 
1132  Status = KdPullRemoteFile (ImageFileName,
1133  FILE_ATTRIBUTE_NORMAL,
1134  FILE_OVERWRITE_IF,
1135  FILE_SYNCHRONOUS_IO_NONALERT);
1136 
1137  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1138  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_TRACE_LEVEL,
1139  "MmLoadSystemImage: Pulled %wZ from kd\n",
1140  ImageFileName);
1141  }
1142  }
1143 
1144  DataTableEntry = NULL;
1145 
1146  //
1147  // Attempt to open the driver image itself. If this fails, then the
1148  // driver image cannot be located, so nothing else matters.
1149  //
1150 
1151  InitializeObjectAttributes (&ObjectAttributes,
1152  ImageFileName,
1153  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE),
1154  NULL,
1155  NULL);
1156 
1157  Status = ZwOpenFile (&FileHandle,
1158  FILE_EXECUTE,
1159  &ObjectAttributes,
1160  &IoStatus,
1161  FILE_SHARE_READ | FILE_SHARE_DELETE,
1162  0);
1163 
1164  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1165 
1166 #if DBG
1167  if (NtGlobalFlag & FLG_SHOW_LDR_SNAPS) {
1168  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_WARNING_LEVEL,
1169  "MmLoadSystemImage: cannot open %wZ\n",
1170  ImageFileName);
1171  }
1172 #endif
1173  //
1174  // File not found.
1175  //
1176 
1177  goto return2;
1178  }
1179 
1180  Status = MmCheckSystemImage (FileHandle, FALSE);
1181 
1182  if ((Status == STATUS_IMAGE_CHECKSUM_MISMATCH) ||
1183  (Status == STATUS_IMAGE_MP_UP_MISMATCH) ||
1184  (Status == STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_PROTECT)) {
1185 
1186  goto return1;
1187  }
1188 
1189  //
1190  // Now attempt to create an image section for the file. If this fails,
1191  // then the driver file is not an image. Session space drivers are
1192  // shared text with copy on write data, so don't allow writes here.
1193  //
1194 
1195  if (LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) {
1196  SectionAccess = SECTION_MAP_READ | SECTION_MAP_EXECUTE;
1197  }
1198  else {
1199  SectionAccess = SECTION_ALL_ACCESS;
1200  }
1201 
1202  InitializeObjectAttributes (&ObjectAttributes,
1203  NULL,
1204  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE),
1205  NULL,
1206  NULL);
1207 
1208  Status = ZwCreateSection (&SectionHandle,
1209  SectionAccess,
1210  &ObjectAttributes,
1211  (PLARGE_INTEGER) NULL,
1212  PAGE_EXECUTE,
1213  SEC_IMAGE,
1214  FileHandle);
1215 
1216  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
1217  goto return1;
1218  }
1219 
1220  //
1221  // Now reference the section handle. If this fails something is
1222  // very wrong because it is a kernel handle.
1223  //
1224  // N.B. ObRef sets SectionPointer to NULL on failure.
1225  //
1226 
1227  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (SectionHandle,
1228  SECTION_MAP_EXECUTE,
1229  MmSectionObjectType,
1230  KernelMode,
1231  (PVOID *) &SectionPointer,
1232  (POBJECT_HANDLE_INFORMATION) NULL);
1233 
1234  ZwClose (SectionHandle);
1235 
1236  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1237  goto return1;
1238  }
1239 
1240  if ((LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) &&
1241  (SectionPointer->Segment->ControlArea->u.Flags.FloppyMedia == 0)) {
1242 
1243  //
1244  // Check with all of the drivers along the path to win32k.sys to
1245  // ensure that they are willing to follow the rules required
1246  // of them and to give them a chance to lock down code and data
1247  // that needs to be locked. If any of the drivers along the path
1248  // refuses to participate, fail the win32k.sys load.
1249  //
1250  // It is assumed that all session drivers live on the same physical
1251  // drive, so when the very first session driver is loaded, this
1252  // check can be made.
1253  //
1254  // Note that this is important because these drivers are always
1255  // paged directly in/out from the filesystem so the drive
1256  // containing the filesystem better not get removed !
1257  //
1258 
1259  //
1260  // This is skipped for the WinPE removable media boot case because
1261  // the user may be running WinPE in RAM and want to swap out the
1262  // boot media. In this case, the control area is marked as
1263  // FloppyMedia (even if it was CD-based) as all the pages have
1264  // already been converted to pagefile-backed.
1265  //
1266 
1267  do {
1268  OldValue = MiFirstDriverLoadEver;
1269 
1270  if (OldValue & 0x2) {
1271  break;
1272  }
1273 
1274  if (InterlockedCompareExchange (&MiFirstDriverLoadEver, OldValue | 0x2, OldValue) == OldValue) {
1275 
1276  Status = PpPagePathAssign (SectionPointer->Segment->ControlArea->FilePointer);
1277 
1278  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1279 
1280  KdPrint (("PpPagePathAssign FAILED for %wZ: %x\n",
1281  ImageFileName, Status));
1282 
1283  //
1284  // Failing the insertion of win32k.sys' device
1285  // in the pagefile path is commented out until
1286  // the storage drivers have been modified to
1287  // correctly handle this request. If this is
1288  // added later, add code here to release relevant
1289  // resources for this error path.
1290  //
1291  }
1292 
1293  break;
1294  }
1295  } while (TRUE);
1296  }
1297 
1298  //
1299  // Anything may have changed while the load lock was released.
1300  // So before using the section we just created, go back and see
1301  // if any other threads have slipped through and did it already.
1302  //
1303 
1304  goto ReCheckLoaderList;
1305  }
1306  else {
1307  DataTableEntry = NULL;
1308  }
1309 
1310  //
1311  // Load the driver from the filesystem and pick a virtual address for it.
1312  // All session images are paged directly to and from the filesystem so these
1313  // images remain busy.
1314  //
1315 
1316  Status = MiLoadImageSection (&SectionPointer,
1317  ImageBaseAddress,
1318  ImageFileName,
1319  LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION,
1320  FoundDataTableEntry);
1321 
1322  ASSERT (Status != STATUS_ALREADY_COMMITTED);
1323 
1324  NumberOfPtes = SectionPointer->Segment->TotalNumberOfPtes;
1325 
1326  //
1327  // Normal drivers are dereferenced here and their images can then be
1328  // overwritten. This is ok because we've already read the whole thing
1329  // into memory and from here until reboot (or unload), we back them
1330  // with the pagefile.
1331  //
1332  // Session space drivers are the exception - these images
1333  // are inpaged from the filesystem and we need to keep our reference to
1334  // the file so that it doesn't get overwritten.
1335  //
1336 
1337  if ((LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) == 0) {
1338 
1339  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1340 
1341  //
1342  // Move the driver into a large page if requested via the registry.
1343  //
1344 
1345  MiUseLargeDriverPage (SectionPointer->Segment->TotalNumberOfPtes,
1346  ImageBaseAddress,
1347  &BaseName,
1348  1);
1349  }
1350 
1351  ObDereferenceObject (SectionPointer);
1352  SectionPointer = NULL;
1353  }
1354 
1355  //
1356  // The module LoadCount will be 1 here if the module was just loaded.
1357  // The LoadCount will be >1 if it was attached to by a session (as opposed
1358  // to just loaded).
1359  //
1360 
1361  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1362 
1363  if (AlreadyOpen == TRUE) {
1364 
1365  //
1366  // We're failing and we were just attaching to an already loaded
1367  // driver. We don't want to go through the forced unload path
1368  // because we've already deleted the address space so
1369  // decrement our reference and clear the DataTableEntry.
1370  //
1371 
1372  ASSERT (DataTableEntry != NULL);
1373  DataTableEntry->LoadCount -= 1;
1374  DataTableEntry = NULL;
1375  }
1376  goto return1;
1377  }
1378 
1379  //
1380  // Error recovery from this point out for sessions works as follows:
1381  //
1382  // For sessions, we may or may not have a DataTableEntry at this point.
1383  // If we do, it's because we're attaching to a driver that has already
1384  // been loaded - and the DataTableEntry->LoadCount has been bumped - so
1385  // the error recovery from here on out is to just call
1386  // MmUnloadSystemImage with the DataTableEntry.
1387  //
1388  // If this is the first load of a given driver into a session space, we
1389  // have no DataTableEntry at this point. The view has already been mapped
1390  // and committed and the group/session addresses reserved for this DLL.
1391  // The error recovery path handles all this because
1392  // MmUnloadSystemImage zeroes the relevant fields in the
1393  // LDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY so that MmUnloadSystemImage works properly.
1394  //
1395 
1396  IssueUnloadOnFailure = TRUE;
1397 
1398  if (AlreadyOpen == FALSE) {
1399 
1400  if (((LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) == 0) ||
1401  (*ImageBaseAddress != SectionPointer->Segment->BasedAddress)) {
1402 
1403  //
1404  // Apply the fixups to the section. Note session images need only
1405  // be fixed up once per insertion in the loaded module list.
1406  //
1407 
1408  try {
1409  Status = LdrRelocateImage (*ImageBaseAddress,
1410  "SYSLDR",
1411  STATUS_SUCCESS,
1412  STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES,
1413  STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_FORMAT);
1414 
1415  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1416  Status = GetExceptionCode ();
1417  KdPrint(("MM:sysload - LdrRelocateImage failed status %lx\n",
1418  Status));
1419  }
1420 
1421  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
1422 
1423  //
1424  // Unload the system image and dereference the section.
1425  //
1426 
1427  goto return1;
1428  }
1429  }
1430 
1431  DebugInfoSize = 0;
1432  DataDirectory = NULL;
1433  DebugDir = NULL;
1434 
1435  NtHeaders = RtlImageNtHeader (*ImageBaseAddress);
1436 
1437  //
1438  // Create a loader table entry for this driver before resolving the
1439  // references so that any circular references can resolve properly.
1440  //
1441 
1442  if (LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) {
1443 
1444  DebugInfoSize = sizeof (NON_PAGED_DEBUG_INFO);
1445 
1446  if (IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_DEBUG <
1447  NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.NumberOfRvaAndSizes) {
1448 
1449  DataDirectory = &NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.DataDirectory[IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_DEBUG];
1450 
1451  if (DataDirectory->VirtualAddress &&
1452  DataDirectory->Size &&
1453  (DataDirectory->VirtualAddress + DataDirectory->Size) <
1454  NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.SizeOfImage) {
1455 
1456  DebugDir = (PIMAGE_DEBUG_DIRECTORY)
1457  ((PUCHAR)(*ImageBaseAddress) +
1458  DataDirectory->VirtualAddress);
1459 
1460  DebugInfoSize += DataDirectory->Size;
1461 
1462  for (i = 0;
1463  i < DataDirectory->Size/sizeof(IMAGE_DEBUG_DIRECTORY);
1464  i += 1) {
1465 
1466  if ((DebugDir+i)->AddressOfRawData &&
1467  (DebugDir+i)->AddressOfRawData <
1468  NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.SizeOfImage &&
1469  ((DebugDir+i)->AddressOfRawData +
1470  (DebugDir+i)->SizeOfData) <
1471  NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.SizeOfImage) {
1472 
1473  DebugInfoSize += (DebugDir+i)->SizeOfData;
1474  }
1475  }
1476  }
1477 
1478  DebugInfoSize = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE(DebugInfoSize, sizeof(ULONG));
1479  }
1480  }
1481 
1482  DataTableEntrySize = sizeof (KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY) +
1483  DebugInfoSize +
1484  BaseName.Length + sizeof(UNICODE_NULL);
1485 
1486  DataTableEntry = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
1487  DataTableEntrySize,
1488  'dLmM');
1489 
1490  if (DataTableEntry == NULL) {
1491  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1492  goto return1;
1493  }
1494 
1495  //
1496  // Initialize the flags and load count.
1497  //
1498 
1499  DataTableEntry->Flags = LDRP_LOAD_IN_PROGRESS;
1500  DataTableEntry->LoadCount = 1;
1501  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = (PVOID)LoadedImports;
1502  DataTableEntry->PatchInformation = NULL;
1503 
1504  if ((NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.MajorOperatingSystemVersion >= 5) &&
1505  (NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.MajorImageVersion >= 5)) {
1506  DataTableEntry->Flags |= LDRP_ENTRY_NATIVE;
1507  }
1508 
1509  ssHeader = (PNON_PAGED_DEBUG_INFO) ((ULONG_PTR)DataTableEntry +
1510  sizeof (KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY));
1511 
1512  BaseDllNameBuffer = (PWSTR) ((ULONG_PTR)ssHeader + DebugInfoSize);
1513 
1514  //
1515  // If loading a session space image, store away some debug data.
1516  //
1517 
1518  DataTableEntry->NonPagedDebugInfo = NULL;
1519 
1520  if (LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) {
1521 
1522  DataTableEntry->NonPagedDebugInfo = ssHeader;
1523  DataTableEntry->Flags |= LDRP_NON_PAGED_DEBUG_INFO;
1524 
1525  ssHeader->Signature = NON_PAGED_DEBUG_SIGNATURE;
1526  ssHeader->Flags = 1;
1527  ssHeader->Size = DebugInfoSize;
1528  ssHeader->Machine = NtHeaders->FileHeader.Machine;
1529  ssHeader->Characteristics = NtHeaders->FileHeader.Characteristics;
1530  ssHeader->TimeDateStamp = NtHeaders->FileHeader.TimeDateStamp;
1531  ssHeader->CheckSum = NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.CheckSum;
1532  ssHeader->SizeOfImage = NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.SizeOfImage;
1533  ssHeader->ImageBase = (ULONG_PTR) *ImageBaseAddress;
1534 
1535  if (DebugDir) {
1536 
1537  RtlCopyMemory (ssHeader + 1,
1538  DebugDir,
1539  DataDirectory->Size);
1540 
1541  DebugInfoSize = DataDirectory->Size;
1542 
1543  for (i = 0;
1544  i < DataDirectory->Size/sizeof(IMAGE_DEBUG_DIRECTORY);
1545  i += 1) {
1546 
1547  if ((DebugDir + i)->AddressOfRawData &&
1548  (DebugDir+i)->AddressOfRawData <
1549  NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.SizeOfImage &&
1550  ((DebugDir+i)->AddressOfRawData +
1551  (DebugDir+i)->SizeOfData) <
1552  NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.SizeOfImage) {
1553 
1554  RtlCopyMemory ((PUCHAR)(ssHeader + 1) +
1555  DebugInfoSize,
1556  (PUCHAR)(*ImageBaseAddress) +
1557  (DebugDir + i)->AddressOfRawData,
1558  (DebugDir + i)->SizeOfData);
1559 
1560  //
1561  // Reset the offset in the debug directory to point to
1562  //
1563 
1564  (((PIMAGE_DEBUG_DIRECTORY)(ssHeader + 1)) + i)->
1565  AddressOfRawData = DebugInfoSize;
1566 
1567  DebugInfoSize += (DebugDir+i)->SizeOfData;
1568  }
1569  else {
1570  (((PIMAGE_DEBUG_DIRECTORY)(ssHeader + 1)) + i)->
1571  AddressOfRawData = 0;
1572  }
1573  }
1574  }
1575  }
1576 
1577  //
1578  // Initialize the address of the DLL image file header and the entry
1579  // point address.
1580  //
1581 
1582  DataTableEntry->DllBase = *ImageBaseAddress;
1583  DataTableEntry->EntryPoint =
1584  ((PCHAR)*ImageBaseAddress + NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.AddressOfEntryPoint);
1585  DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage = NumberOfPtes << PAGE_SHIFT;
1586  DataTableEntry->CheckSum = NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.CheckSum;
1587  DataTableEntry->SectionPointer = (PVOID) SectionPointer;
1588 
1589  //
1590  // Store the DLL name.
1591  //
1592 
1593  DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.Buffer = BaseDllNameBuffer;
1594 
1595  DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.Length = BaseName.Length;
1596  DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.MaximumLength = BaseName.Length;
1597  RtlCopyMemory (DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.Buffer,
1598  BaseName.Buffer,
1599  BaseName.Length);
1600  DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.Buffer[BaseName.Length/sizeof(WCHAR)] = UNICODE_NULL;
1601 
1602  DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool | POOL_COLD_ALLOCATION,
1603  PrefixedImageName.Length + sizeof(UNICODE_NULL),
1604  'TDmM');
1605 
1606  if (DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Buffer == NULL) {
1607 
1608  //
1609  // Pool could not be allocated, just set the length to 0.
1610  //
1611 
1612  DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Length = 0;
1613  DataTableEntry->FullDllName.MaximumLength = 0;
1614  }
1615  else {
1616  DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Length = PrefixedImageName.Length;
1617  DataTableEntry->FullDllName.MaximumLength = PrefixedImageName.Length;
1618  RtlCopyMemory (DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Buffer,
1619  PrefixedImageName.Buffer,
1620  PrefixedImageName.Length);
1621  DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Buffer[PrefixedImageName.Length/sizeof(WCHAR)] = UNICODE_NULL;
1622  }
1623 
1624  //
1625  // Capture the exception table data info
1626  //
1627 
1628  MiCaptureImageExceptionValues (DataTableEntry);
1629 
1630  //
1631  // Acquire the loaded module list resource and insert this entry
1632  // into the list.
1633  //
1634 
1635  MiProcessLoaderEntry (DataTableEntry, TRUE);
1636 
1637  MissingProcedureName = NameBuffer;
1638 
1639  try {
1640 
1641  //
1642  // Resolving the image references results in other DLLs being
1643  // loaded if they are referenced by the module that was just loaded.
1644  // An example is when an OEM printer or FAX driver links with
1645  // other general libraries. This is not a problem for session space
1646  // because the general libraries do not have the global data issues
1647  // that win32k.sys and the video drivers do. So we just call the
1648  // standard kernel reference resolver and any referenced libraries
1649  // get loaded into system global space. Code in the routine
1650  // restricts which libraries can be referenced by a driver.
1651  //
1652 
1653  Status = MiResolveImageReferences (*ImageBaseAddress,
1654  &BaseDirectory,
1655  NamePrefix,
1656  &MissingProcedureName,
1657  &MissingDriverName,
1658  &LoadedImports);
1659 
1660  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1661  Status = GetExceptionCode ();
1662  KdPrint(("MM:sysload - ResolveImageReferences failed status %x\n",
1663  Status));
1664  }
1665 
1666  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1667 #if DBG
1668  if (Status == STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND) {
1669  ASSERT (MissingProcedureName == NULL);
1670  }
1671 
1672  if ((Status == STATUS_DRIVER_ORDINAL_NOT_FOUND) ||
1673  (Status == STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND) ||
1674  (Status == STATUS_DRIVER_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND)) {
1675 
1676  if ((ULONG_PTR)MissingProcedureName & ~((ULONG_PTR) (X64K-1))) {
1677 
1678  //
1679  // If not an ordinal, print string.
1680  //
1681 
1682  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_WARNING_LEVEL,
1683  "MissingProcedureName %s\n", MissingProcedureName);
1684  }
1685  else {
1686  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_WARNING_LEVEL,
1687  "MissingProcedureName 0x%p\n", MissingProcedureName);
1688  }
1689  }
1690 
1691  if (MissingDriverName != NULL) {
1692  PrintableMissingDriverName = (PWSTR)((ULONG_PTR)MissingDriverName & ~0x1);
1693  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_WARNING_LEVEL,
1694  "MissingDriverName %ws\n", PrintableMissingDriverName);
1695  }
1696 #endif
1697  MiProcessLoaderEntry (DataTableEntry, FALSE);
1698 
1699  if (DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Buffer != NULL) {
1700  ExFreePool (DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Buffer);
1701  }
1702  ExFreePool (DataTableEntry);
1703 
1704  DataTableEntry = NULL;
1705 
1706  goto return1;
1707  }
1708 
1709  //
1710  // Reinitialize the flags and update the loaded imports.
1711  //
1712 
1713  DataTableEntry->Flags |= (LDRP_SYSTEM_MAPPED | LDRP_ENTRY_PROCESSED | LDRP_MM_LOADED);
1714  DataTableEntry->Flags &= ~LDRP_LOAD_IN_PROGRESS;
1715  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = LoadedImports;
1716 
1717  MiApplyDriverVerifier (DataTableEntry, NULL);
1718 
1719  if (LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) {
1720 
1721  //
1722  // Attempt to lookup the win32k system service table. If the
1723  // service table is found, then compact the table into an array
1724  // of relative 32-bit pointers.
1725  //
1726 
1727 #if defined(_AMD64_)
1728 
1729  PULONG Limit;
1730  BOOLEAN Match;
1731  UNICODE_STRING Name;
1732  NTSTATUS Status1;
1733  NTSTATUS Status2;
1734  PVOID Table;
1735 
1736  RtlInitUnicodeString (&Name, L"win32k.sys");
1737  Match = RtlEqualUnicodeString (&DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
1738  &Name,
1739  TRUE);
1740 
1741  if (Match == TRUE) {
1742  Status1 = LookupEntryPoint (DataTableEntry->DllBase,
1743  "W32pServiceTable",
1744  &Table);
1745 
1746  Status2 = LookupEntryPoint (DataTableEntry->DllBase,
1747  "W32pServiceLimit",
1748  &Limit);
1749 
1750  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status1) && NT_SUCCESS(Status2)) {
1751  KeCompactServiceTable (Table, *Limit, TRUE);
1752 
1753  } else {
1754  DbgBreakPoint ();
1755  }
1756  }
1757 
1758 #endif
1759 
1760  //
1761  // The session image was mapped entirely read-write on initial
1762  // creation. Now that the relocations (if any), image
1763  // resolution and import table updates are complete, correct
1764  // permissions can be applied.
1765  //
1766  // Make the entire image copy on write. The subsequent call
1767  // to MiWriteProtectSystemImage will make various portions
1768  // readonly. Then apply flip various subsections into global
1769  // shared mode if their attributes specify it.
1770  //
1771 
1772  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (DataTableEntry->DllBase);
1773 
1774  MiSetSystemCodeProtection (PointerPte,
1775  PointerPte + NumberOfPtes - 1,
1776  MM_EXECUTE_WRITECOPY);
1777  }
1778 
1779  MiWriteProtectSystemImage (DataTableEntry->DllBase);
1780 
1781  if (LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) {
1782  MiSessionProcessGlobalSubsections (DataTableEntry);
1783  }
1784 
1785  if (PsImageNotifyEnabled) {
1786  IMAGE_INFO ImageInfo;
1787 
1788  ImageInfo.Properties = 0;
1789  ImageInfo.ImageAddressingMode = IMAGE_ADDRESSING_MODE_32BIT;
1790  ImageInfo.SystemModeImage = TRUE;
1791  ImageInfo.ImageSize = DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage;
1792  ImageInfo.ImageBase = *ImageBaseAddress;
1793  ImageInfo.ImageSelector = 0;
1794  ImageInfo.ImageSectionNumber = 0;
1795 
1796  PsCallImageNotifyRoutines(ImageFileName, (HANDLE)NULL, &ImageInfo);
1797  }
1798 
1799  if (MiCacheImageSymbols (*ImageBaseAddress)) {
1800 
1801  //
1802  // TEMP TEMP TEMP rip out when debugger converted
1803  //
1804 
1805  ANSI_STRING AnsiName;
1806  UNICODE_STRING UnicodeName;
1807 
1808  //
1809  // \SystemRoot is 11 characters in length
1810  //
1811  if (PrefixedImageName.Length > (11 * sizeof (WCHAR )) &&
1812  !_wcsnicmp (PrefixedImageName.Buffer, (const PUSHORT)L"\\SystemRoot", 11)) {
1813  UnicodeName = PrefixedImageName;
1814  UnicodeName.Buffer += 11;
1815  UnicodeName.Length -= (11 * sizeof (WCHAR));
1816  sprintf (NameBuffer, "%ws%wZ", &SharedUserData->NtSystemRoot[2], &UnicodeName);
1817  }
1818  else {
1819  sprintf (NameBuffer, "%wZ", &BaseName);
1820  }
1821  RtlInitString (&AnsiName, NameBuffer);
1822  DbgLoadImageSymbols (&AnsiName,
1823  *ImageBaseAddress,
1824  (ULONG_PTR) -1);
1825 
1826  DataTableEntry->Flags |= LDRP_DEBUG_SYMBOLS_LOADED;
1827  }
1828  }
1829 
1830  //
1831  // Flush the instruction cache on all systems in the configuration.
1832  //
1833 
1834  KeSweepIcache (TRUE);
1835  *ImageHandle = DataTableEntry;
1836  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1837 
1838  //
1839  // Session images are always paged by default.
1840  // Non-session images get paged now.
1841  //
1842 
1843  if (LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_IN_SESSION) {
1844  MI_LOG_SESSION_DATA_START (DataTableEntry);
1845  }
1846  else if ((LoadFlags & MM_LOAD_IMAGE_AND_LOCKDOWN) == 0) {
1847 
1848  ASSERT (SectionPointer == NULL);
1849 
1850  MiEnablePagingOfDriver (DataTableEntry);
1851  }
1852 
1853 return1:
1854 
1855  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
1856 
1857  if (IssueUnloadOnFailure == TRUE) {
1858 
1859  if (DataTableEntry == NULL) {
1860 
1861  RtlZeroMemory (&TempDataTableEntry, sizeof (KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY));
1862 
1863  DataTableEntry = &TempDataTableEntry;
1864 
1865  DataTableEntry->DllBase = *ImageBaseAddress;
1866  DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage = NumberOfPtes << PAGE_SHIFT;
1867  DataTableEntry->LoadCount = 1;
1868  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = LoadedImports;
1869 
1870  if ((AlreadyOpen == FALSE) && (SectionPointer != NULL)) {
1871  DataTableEntry->SectionPointer = (PVOID) SectionPointer;
1872  }
1873  }
1874 #if DBG
1875  else {
1876 
1877  //
1878  // If DataTableEntry is NULL, then we are unloading before one
1879  // got created. Once a LDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY is created, the
1880  // load cannot fail, so if it exists here, at least one other
1881  // session contains this image as well.
1882  //
1883 
1884  ASSERT (DataTableEntry->LoadCount > 1);
1885  }
1886 #endif
1887 
1888  MmUnloadSystemImage ((PVOID)DataTableEntry);
1889  }
1890 
1891  if ((AlreadyOpen == FALSE) && (SectionPointer != NULL)) {
1892 
1893  //
1894  // This is needed for failed win32k.sys loads or any session's
1895  // load of the first instance of a driver.
1896  //
1897 
1898  ObDereferenceObject (SectionPointer);
1899  }
1900  }
1901 
1902  if (LoadLockOwned == TRUE) {
1903  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
1904  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
1905  LoadLockOwned = FALSE;
1906  }
1907 
1908  if (FileHandle) {
1909  ZwClose (FileHandle);
1910  }
1911 
1912  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
1913 
1914  UNICODE_STRING ErrorStrings[4];
1915  ULONG UniqueErrorValue;
1916  ULONG StringSize;
1917  ULONG StringCount;
1918  ANSI_STRING AnsiString;
1919  UNICODE_STRING ProcedureName = {0};
1920  UNICODE_STRING DriverName;
1921  ULONG i;
1922  PWCHAR temp;
1923  PWCHAR ptr;
1924  ULONG PacketSize;
1925  SIZE_T length;
1926  PIO_ERROR_LOG_PACKET ErrLog;
1927 
1928  //
1929  // The driver could not be loaded - log an event with the details.
1930  //
1931 
1932  StringSize = 0;
1933 
1934  *(&ErrorStrings[0]) = *ImageFileName;
1935  StringSize += (ImageFileName->Length + sizeof(UNICODE_NULL));
1936  StringCount = 1;
1937 
1938  UniqueErrorValue = 0;
1939 
1940  PrintableMissingDriverName = (PWSTR)((ULONG_PTR)MissingDriverName & ~0x1);
1941  if ((Status == STATUS_DRIVER_ORDINAL_NOT_FOUND) ||
1942  (Status == STATUS_DRIVER_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND) ||
1943  (Status == STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND) ||
1944  (Status == STATUS_PROCEDURE_NOT_FOUND)) {
1945 
1946  ErrorStrings[1].Buffer = L"cannot find";
1947  length = wcslen(ErrorStrings[1].Buffer) * sizeof(WCHAR);
1948  ErrorStrings[1].Length = (USHORT) length;
1949  StringSize += (ULONG)(length + sizeof (UNICODE_NULL));
1950  StringCount += 1;
1951 
1952  RtlInitUnicodeString (&DriverName, PrintableMissingDriverName);
1953 
1954  StringSize += (DriverName.Length + sizeof(UNICODE_NULL));
1955  StringCount += 1;
1956  *(&ErrorStrings[2]) = *(&DriverName);
1957 
1958  if ((ULONG_PTR)MissingProcedureName & ~((ULONG_PTR) (X64K-1))) {
1959 
1960  //
1961  // If not an ordinal, pass as a Unicode string
1962  //
1963 
1964  RtlInitAnsiString (&AnsiString, MissingProcedureName);
1965  if (NT_SUCCESS (RtlAnsiStringToUnicodeString (&ProcedureName, &AnsiString, TRUE))) {
1966  StringSize += (ProcedureName.Length + sizeof(UNICODE_NULL));
1967  StringCount += 1;
1968  *(&ErrorStrings[3]) = *(&ProcedureName);
1969  }
1970  else {
1971  goto GenericError;
1972  }
1973  }
1974  else {
1975 
1976  //
1977  // Just pass ordinal values as is in the UniqueErrorValue.
1978  //
1979 
1980  UniqueErrorValue = PtrToUlong (MissingProcedureName);
1981  }
1982  }
1983  else {
1984 
1985 GenericError:
1986 
1987  UniqueErrorValue = (ULONG) Status;
1988 
1989  if (MmIsRetryIoStatus(Status)) {
1990 
1991  //
1992  // Coalesce the various low memory values into just one.
1993  //
1994 
1995  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1996 
1997  }
1998  else {
1999 
2000  //
2001  // Ideally, the real failing status should be returned. However,
2002  // we need to do a full release worth of testing (ie Longhorn)
2003  // before making that change.
2004  //
2005 
2006  Status = STATUS_DRIVER_UNABLE_TO_LOAD;
2007  }
2008 
2009  ErrorStrings[1].Buffer = L"failed to load";
2010  length = wcslen(ErrorStrings[1].Buffer) * sizeof(WCHAR);
2011  ErrorStrings[1].Length = (USHORT) length;
2012  StringSize += (ULONG)(length + sizeof (UNICODE_NULL));
2013  StringCount += 1;
2014  }
2015 
2016  PacketSize = sizeof (IO_ERROR_LOG_PACKET) + StringSize;
2017 
2018  //
2019  // Enforce I/O manager interface (ie: UCHAR) size restrictions.
2020  //
2021 
2022  if (PacketSize < MAXUCHAR) {
2023 
2024  ErrLog = IoAllocateGenericErrorLogEntry ((UCHAR)PacketSize);
2025 
2026  if (ErrLog != NULL) {
2027 
2028  //
2029  // Fill it in and write it out as a single string.
2030  //
2031 
2032  ErrLog->ErrorCode = STATUS_LOG_HARD_ERROR;
2033  ErrLog->FinalStatus = Status;
2034  ErrLog->UniqueErrorValue = UniqueErrorValue;
2035 
2036  ErrLog->StringOffset = (USHORT) sizeof (IO_ERROR_LOG_PACKET);
2037 
2038  temp = (PWCHAR) ((PUCHAR) ErrLog + ErrLog->StringOffset);
2039 
2040  for (i = 0; i < StringCount; i += 1) {
2041 
2042  ptr = ErrorStrings[i].Buffer;
2043 
2044  RtlCopyMemory (temp, ptr, ErrorStrings[i].Length);
2045  temp += (ErrorStrings[i].Length / sizeof (WCHAR));
2046 
2047  *temp = L' ';
2048  temp += 1;
2049  }
2050 
2051  *(temp - 1) = UNICODE_NULL;
2052  ErrLog->NumberOfStrings = 1;
2053 
2054  IoWriteErrorLogEntry (ErrLog);
2055  }
2056  }
2057 
2058  //
2059  // The only way this pointer has the low bit set is if we are expected
2060  // to free the pool containing the name. Typically the name points at
2061  // a loaded module list entry and so no one has to free it and in this
2062  // case the low bit will NOT be set. If the module could not be found
2063  // and was therefore not loaded, then we left a piece of pool around
2064  // containing the name since there is no loaded module entry already -
2065  // this must be released now.
2066  //
2067 
2068  if ((ULONG_PTR)MissingDriverName & 0x1) {
2069  ExFreePool (PrintableMissingDriverName);
2070  }
2071 
2072  if (ProcedureName.Buffer != NULL) {
2073  RtlFreeUnicodeString (&ProcedureName);
2074  }
2075  ExFreePool (NameBuffer);
2076  return Status;
2077  }
2078 
2079 return2:
2080 
2081  if (LoadLockOwned == TRUE) {
2082  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
2083  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
2084  LoadLockOwned = FALSE;
2085  }
2086 
2087  if (NamePrefix) {
2088  ExFreePool (PrefixedImageName.Buffer);
2089  }
2090 
2091  ExFreePool (NameBuffer);
2092 
2093  return Status;
2094 }
2095 
2096 VOID
2097 MiReturnFailedSessionPages (
2098  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
2099  IN PMMPTE LastPte
2100  )
2101 
2102 /*++
2103 
2104 Routine Description:
2105 
2106  This routine is a nonpaged wrapper which undoes session image loads
2107  that failed midway through reading in the pages.
2108 
2109 Arguments:
2110 
2111  PointerPte - Supplies the starting PTE for the range to unload.
2112 
2113  LastPte - Supplies the ending PTE for the range to unload.
2114 
2115 Return Value:
2116 
2117  None.
2118 
2119 --*/
2120 
2121 {
2122  KIRQL OldIrql;
2123  PMMPFN Pfn1;
2124  PMMPFN Pfn2;
2125  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
2126 
2127  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2128 
2129  while (PointerPte <= LastPte) {
2130  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
2131 
2132  //
2133  // Delete the page.
2134  //
2135 
2136  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
2137 
2138  //
2139  // Set the pointer to PTE as empty so the page
2140  // is deleted when the reference count goes to zero.
2141  //
2142 
2143  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2144  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
2145 
2146  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
2147 
2148  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
2149  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
2150 
2151  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
2152  }
2153  PointerPte += 1;
2154  }
2155 
2156  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2157 }
2158 
2159 
2160 NTSTATUS
2161 MiLoadImageSection (
2162  IN OUT PSECTION *InputSectionPointer,
2163  OUT PVOID *ImageBaseAddress,
2164  IN PUNICODE_STRING ImageFileName,
2165  IN ULONG LoadInSessionSpace,
2166  IN PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY FoundDataTableEntry
2167  )
2168 
2169 /*++
2170 
2171 Routine Description:
2172 
2173  This routine loads the specified image into the kernel part of the
2174  address space.
2175 
2176 Arguments:
2177 
2178  InputSectionPointer - Supplies the section object for the image. This may
2179  be replaced by a pagefile-backed section (for
2180  protection purposes) for session images if it is
2181  determined that the image section is concurrently
2182  being accessed by a user app.
2183 
2184  ImageBaseAddress - Returns the address that the image header is at.
2185 
2186  ImageFileName - Supplies the full path name (including the image name)
2187  of the image to load.
2188 
2189  LoadInSessionSpace - Supplies nonzero to load this image in session space.
2190  Each session gets a different copy of this driver with
2191  pages shared as much as possible via copy on write.
2192 
2193  Supplies zero if this image should be loaded in global
2194  space.
2195 
2196  FoundDataTableEntry - Supplies the loader data table entry if the image
2197  has already been loaded. This can only happen for
2198  session space. It means this driver has already
2199  been loaded into a different session, so this session
2200  still needs to map it.
2201 
2202 Return Value:
2203 
2204  Status of the operation.
2205 
2206 --*/
2207 
2208 {
2209  KAPC_STATE ApcState;
2210  PFN_NUMBER PagesRequired;
2211  PFN_NUMBER ActualPagesUsed;
2212  PSECTION SectionPointer;
2213  PSECTION NewSectionPointer;
2214  PVOID OpaqueSession;
2215  PMMPTE ProtoPte;
2216  PMMPTE LastProto;
2217  PMMPTE FirstPte;
2218  PMMPTE LastPte;
2219  PMMPTE PointerPte;
2220  PEPROCESS Process;
2221  PEPROCESS TargetProcess;
2222  ULONG NumberOfPtes;
2223  MMPTE PteContents;
2224  MMPTE TempPte;
2225  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
2226  PVOID UserVa;
2227  PVOID SystemVa;
2228  NTSTATUS Status;
2229  NTSTATUS ExceptionStatus;
2230  PVOID Base;
2231  ULONG_PTR ViewSize;
2232  LARGE_INTEGER SectionOffset;
2233  LOGICAL LoadSymbols;
2234  PVOID BaseAddress;
2235  PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea;
2236  PSUBSECTION Subsection;
2237 
2238  PAGED_CODE();
2239 
2240 #if !DBG
2241  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (ImageFileName);
2242 #endif
2243 
2244  SectionPointer = *InputSectionPointer;
2245 
2246  NumberOfPtes = SectionPointer->Segment->TotalNumberOfPtes;
2247 
2248  if (LoadInSessionSpace != 0) {
2249 
2250  //
2251  // Allocate a unique systemwide session space virtual address for
2252  // the driver.
2253  //
2254 
2255  if (FoundDataTableEntry == NULL) {
2256 
2257  Status = MiSessionWideReserveImageAddress (SectionPointer,
2258  &BaseAddress,
2259  &NewSectionPointer);
2260 
2261  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
2262  return Status;
2263  }
2264 
2265  if (NewSectionPointer != NULL) {
2266  SectionPointer = NewSectionPointer;
2267  *InputSectionPointer = NewSectionPointer;
2268  }
2269  }
2270  else {
2271  BaseAddress = FoundDataTableEntry->DllBase;
2272  }
2273 
2274 #if DBG
2275  if (NtGlobalFlag & FLG_SHOW_LDR_SNAPS) {
2276  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_TRACE_LEVEL,
2277  "MM: MiLoadImageSection: Image %wZ, BasedAddress 0x%p, Allocated Session BaseAddress 0x%p\n",
2278  ImageFileName,
2279  SectionPointer->Segment->BasedAddress,
2280  BaseAddress);
2281  }
2282 #endif
2283 
2284  //
2285  // Session images are mapped backed directly by the file image.
2286  // All pristine pages of the image will be shared across all
2287  // sessions, with each page treated as copy-on-write on first write.
2288  //
2289  // NOTE: This makes the file image "busy", a different behavior
2290  // as normal kernel drivers are backed by the paging file only.
2291  //
2292 
2293  Status = MiShareSessionImage (BaseAddress, SectionPointer);
2294 
2295  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
2296  MiRemoveImageSessionWide (FoundDataTableEntry,
2297  BaseAddress,
2298  NumberOfPtes << PAGE_SHIFT);
2299  return Status;
2300  }
2301 
2302  *ImageBaseAddress = BaseAddress;
2303 
2304  return Status;
2305  }
2306 
2307  ASSERT (FoundDataTableEntry == NULL);
2308 
2309  //
2310  // Calculate the number of pages required to load this image.
2311  //
2312  // Start out by charging for everything and subtract out any gap
2313  // pages after the image loads successfully.
2314  //
2315 
2316  PagesRequired = NumberOfPtes;
2317  ActualPagesUsed = 0;
2318 
2319  //
2320  // See if ample pages exist to load this image.
2321  //
2322 
2323  if (MiChargeResidentAvailable (PagesRequired, MM_RESAVAIL_ALLOCATE_LOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE) == FALSE) {
2324  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
2325  }
2326 
2327  //
2328  // Reserve the necessary system address space.
2329  //
2330 
2331  FirstPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (NumberOfPtes, SystemPteSpace);
2332 
2333  if (FirstPte == NULL) {
2334  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PagesRequired,
2335  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_LOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE1);
2336  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
2337  }
2338 
2339  PointerPte = FirstPte;
2340  SystemVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
2341 
2342  if (MiChargeCommitment (PagesRequired, NULL) == FALSE) {
2343  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PagesRequired,
2344  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_LOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE1);
2345  MiReleaseSystemPtes (FirstPte, NumberOfPtes, SystemPteSpace);
2346  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
2347  }
2348 
2349  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_DRIVER_PAGES, PagesRequired);
2350 
2351  InterlockedExchangeAdd ((PLONG)&MmDriverCommit, (LONG) PagesRequired);
2352 
2353  //
2354  // Map a view into the user portion of the address space.
2355  //
2356 
2357  Process = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
2358 
2359  //
2360  // Since callees are not always in the context of the system process,
2361  // attach here when necessary to guarantee the driver load occurs in a
2362  // known safe address space to prevent security holes.
2363  //
2364 
2365  OpaqueSession = NULL;
2366 
2367  KeStackAttachProcess (&PsInitialSystemProcess->Pcb, &ApcState);
2368 
2369  ZERO_LARGE (SectionOffset);
2370  Base = NULL;
2371  ViewSize = 0;
2372 
2373  if (NtGlobalFlag & FLG_ENABLE_KDEBUG_SYMBOL_LOAD) {
2374  LoadSymbols = TRUE;
2375  NtGlobalFlag &= ~FLG_ENABLE_KDEBUG_SYMBOL_LOAD;
2376  }
2377  else {
2378  LoadSymbols = FALSE;
2379  }
2380 
2381  TargetProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
2382 
2383  Status = MmMapViewOfSection (SectionPointer,
2384  TargetProcess,
2385  &Base,
2386  0,
2387  0,
2388  &SectionOffset,
2389  &ViewSize,
2390  ViewUnmap,
2391  0,
2392  PAGE_EXECUTE);
2393 
2394  if (LoadSymbols) {
2395  NtGlobalFlag |= FLG_ENABLE_KDEBUG_SYMBOL_LOAD;
2396  }
2397 
2398  if (Status == STATUS_IMAGE_MACHINE_TYPE_MISMATCH) {
2399  Status = STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_FORMAT;
2400  }
2401 
2402  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
2403 
2404  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
2405 
2406  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PagesRequired,
2407  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_LOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE2);
2408 
2409  MiReleaseSystemPtes (FirstPte, NumberOfPtes, SystemPteSpace);
2410  MiReturnCommitment (PagesRequired);
2411 
2412  return Status;
2413  }
2414 
2415  //
2416  // Allocate a physical page(s) and copy the image data.
2417  // Note for session drivers, the physical pages have already
2418  // been allocated and just data copying is done here.
2419  //
2420 
2421  ControlArea = SectionPointer->Segment->ControlArea;
2422 
2423  if ((ControlArea->u.Flags.GlobalOnlyPerSession == 0) &&
2424  (ControlArea->u.Flags.Rom == 0)) {
2425  Subsection = (PSUBSECTION)(ControlArea + 1);
2426  }
2427  else {
2428  Subsection = (PSUBSECTION)((PLARGE_CONTROL_AREA)ControlArea + 1);
2429  }
2430 
2431  ASSERT (Subsection->SubsectionBase != NULL);
2432  ProtoPte = Subsection->SubsectionBase;
2433 
2434  *ImageBaseAddress = SystemVa;
2435 
2436  UserVa = Base;
2437  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
2438  TempPte.u.Long |= MM_PTE_EXECUTE;
2439 
2440  LastProto = &Subsection->SubsectionBase[Subsection->PtesInSubsection];
2441  LastPte = PointerPte + NumberOfPtes;
2442 
2443  ExceptionStatus = STATUS_SUCCESS;
2444 
2445  while (PointerPte < LastPte) {
2446 
2447  if (ProtoPte >= LastProto) {
2448 
2449  //
2450  // Handle extended subsections.
2451  //
2452 
2453  Subsection = Subsection->NextSubsection;
2454  ProtoPte = Subsection->SubsectionBase;
2455  LastProto = &Subsection->SubsectionBase[
2456  Subsection->PtesInSubsection];
2457  }
2458 
2459  PteContents = *ProtoPte;
2460  if ((PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1) ||
2461  (PteContents.u.Soft.Protection != MM_NOACCESS)) {
2462 
2463  ActualPagesUsed += 1;
2464 
2465  PageFrameIndex = MiAllocatePfn (PointerPte, MM_EXECUTE);
2466 
2467  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
2468  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
2469 
2470  ASSERT (MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex)->u1.WsIndex == 0);
2471 
2472  try {
2473 
2474  RtlCopyMemory (SystemVa, UserVa, PAGE_SIZE);
2475 
2476  } except (MiMapCacheExceptionFilter (&ExceptionStatus,
2477  GetExceptionInformation())) {
2478 
2479  //
2480  // An exception occurred, unmap the view and
2481  // return the error to the caller.
2482  //
2483 
2484 #if DBG
2485  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_WARNING_LEVEL,
2486  "MiLoadImageSection: Exception 0x%x copying driver SystemVa 0x%p, UserVa 0x%p\n",ExceptionStatus,SystemVa,UserVa);
2487 #endif
2488 
2489  MiReturnFailedSessionPages (FirstPte, PointerPte);
2490 
2491  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PagesRequired,
2492  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_LOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE3);
2493 
2494  MiReleaseSystemPtes (FirstPte, NumberOfPtes, SystemPteSpace);
2495 
2496  MiReturnCommitment (PagesRequired);
2497 
2498  Status = MiUnmapViewOfSection (TargetProcess, Base, 0);
2499 
2500  ASSERT (NT_SUCCESS (Status));
2501 
2502  //
2503  // Purge the section as we want these pages on the freelist
2504  // instead of at the tail of standby, as we're completely
2505  // done with the section. This is because other valuable
2506  // standby pages end up getting reused (especially during
2507  // bootup) when the section pages are the ones that really
2508  // will never be referenced again.
2509  //
2510  // Note this isn't done for session images as they're
2511  // inpaged directly from the filesystem via the section.
2512  //
2513 
2514  MmPurgeSection (ControlArea->FilePointer->SectionObjectPointer,
2515  NULL,
2516  0,
2517  FALSE);
2518 
2519  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
2520 
2521  return ExceptionStatus;
2522  }
2523  }
2524  else {
2525 
2526  //
2527  // The PTE is no access.
2528  //
2529 
2530  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
2531  }
2532 
2533  ProtoPte += 1;
2534  PointerPte += 1;
2535  SystemVa = ((PCHAR)SystemVa + PAGE_SIZE);
2536  UserVa = ((PCHAR)UserVa + PAGE_SIZE);
2537  }
2538 
2539  Status = MiUnmapViewOfSection (TargetProcess, Base, 0);
2540  ASSERT (NT_SUCCESS (Status));
2541 
2542  //
2543  // Purge the section as we want these pages on the freelist instead of
2544  // at the tail of standby, as we're completely done with the section.
2545  // This is because other valuable standby pages end up getting reused
2546  // (especially during bootup) when the section pages are the ones that
2547  // really will never be referenced again.
2548  //
2549 
2550  MmPurgeSection (ControlArea->FilePointer->SectionObjectPointer,
2551  NULL,
2552  0,
2553  FALSE);
2554 
2555  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
2556 
2557  //
2558  // Return any excess resident available and commit.
2559  //
2560 
2561  if (PagesRequired != ActualPagesUsed) {
2562  ASSERT (PagesRequired > ActualPagesUsed);
2563  PagesRequired -= ActualPagesUsed;
2564 
2565  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PagesRequired,
2566  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_LOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE_EXCESS);
2567 
2568  MiReturnCommitment (PagesRequired);
2569  }
2570 
2571  return Status;
2572 }
2573 
2574 VOID
2575 MmFreeDriverInitialization (
2576  IN PVOID ImageHandle
2577  )
2578 
2579 /*++
2580 
2581 Routine Description:
2582 
2583  This routine removes the pages that relocate and debug information from
2584  the address space of the driver.
2585 
2586  NOTE: This routine looks at the last sections defined in the image
2587  header and if that section is marked as DISCARDABLE in the
2588  characteristics, it is removed from the image. This means
2589  that all discardable sections at the end of the driver are
2590  deleted.
2591 
2592 Arguments:
2593 
2594  SectionObject - Supplies the section object for the image.
2595 
2596 Return Value:
2597 
2598  None.
2599 
2600 --*/
2601 
2602 {
2603  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
2604  PMMPTE PointerPte;
2605  PMMPTE LastPte;
2606  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPtes;
2607  PVOID Base;
2608  PVOID StartVa;
2609  ULONG i;
2610  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders;
2611  PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER NtSection;
2612  PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER FoundSection;
2613  PFN_NUMBER PagesDeleted;
2614 
2615  DataTableEntry = (PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY)ImageHandle;
2616  Base = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
2617 
2618  ASSERT (MI_IS_SESSION_ADDRESS (Base) == FALSE);
2619 
2620  NumberOfPtes = DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage >> PAGE_SHIFT;
2621  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress (Base) + NumberOfPtes;
2622 
2623  NtHeaders = (PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS) RtlImageNtHeader (Base);
2624 
2625  if (NtHeaders == NULL) {
2626  return;
2627  }
2628 
2629  NtSection = (PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER)((PCHAR)NtHeaders +
2630  sizeof(ULONG) +
2631  sizeof(IMAGE_FILE_HEADER) +
2632  NtHeaders->FileHeader.SizeOfOptionalHeader
2633  );
2634 
2635  NtSection += NtHeaders->FileHeader.NumberOfSections;
2636 
2637  FoundSection = NULL;
2638  for (i = 0; i < NtHeaders->FileHeader.NumberOfSections; i += 1) {
2639  NtSection -= 1;
2640  if ((NtSection->Characteristics & IMAGE_SCN_MEM_DISCARDABLE) != 0) {
2641  FoundSection = NtSection;
2642  }
2643  else {
2644 
2645  //
2646  // There was a non discardable section between this
2647  // section and the last non discardable section, don't
2648  // discard this section and don't look any more.
2649  //
2650 
2651  break;
2652  }
2653  }
2654 
2655  if (FoundSection != NULL) {
2656 
2657  StartVa = (PVOID) (ROUND_TO_PAGES (
2658  (PCHAR)Base + FoundSection->VirtualAddress));
2659 
2660  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartVa);
2661 
2662  NumberOfPtes = (PFN_NUMBER)(LastPte - PointerPte);
2663 
2664  if (NumberOfPtes != 0) {
2665 
2666  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (StartVa)) {
2667 
2668  //
2669  // Don't free the INIT code for a driver mapped by large pages
2670  // because if it unloads later, we'd have to deal with
2671  // discontiguous ranges of pages to free.
2672  //
2673 
2674  return;
2675  }
2676  else {
2677  PagesDeleted = MiDeleteSystemPageableVm (PointerPte,
2678  NumberOfPtes,
2679  MI_DELETE_FLUSH_TB,
2680  NULL);
2681  }
2682 
2683  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PagesDeleted,
2684  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_DRIVER_INITIALIZATION);
2685 
2686  MiReturnCommitment (PagesDeleted);
2687  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_DRIVER_INIT_CODE, PagesDeleted);
2688 
2689  InterlockedExchangeAdd ((PLONG)&MmDriverCommit,
2690  (LONG) (0 - PagesDeleted));
2691  }
2692  }
2693 
2694  return;
2695 }
2696 
2697 LOGICAL
2698 MiChargeResidentAvailable (
2699  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages,
2700  IN ULONG Id
2701  )
2702 
2703 /*++
2704 
2705 Routine Description:
2706 
2707  This routine is a nonpaged wrapper to charge resident available pages.
2708 
2709 Arguments:
2710 
2711  NumberOfPages - Supplies the number of pages to charge.
2712 
2713  Id - Supplies a tracking ID for debugging purposes.
2714 
2715 Return Value:
2716 
2717  TRUE if the pages were charged, FALSE if not.
2718 
2719 --*/
2720 
2721 {
2722  KIRQL OldIrql;
2723 
2724  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2725 
2726  if (MI_NONPAGEABLE_MEMORY_AVAILABLE() <= (SPFN_NUMBER)NumberOfPages) {
2727  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2728  return FALSE;
2729  }
2730 
2731  MI_DECREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (NumberOfPages, Id);
2732 
2733  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2734 
2735  return TRUE;
2736 }
2737 
2738 VOID
2739 MiFlushPteListFreePfns (
2740  IN PVOID *VaFlushList,
2741  IN ULONG FlushCount
2742  )
2743 
2744 /*++
2745 
2746 Routine Description:
2747 
2748  This routine flushes all the PTEs in the PTE flush list.
2749  If the list has overflowed, the entire TB is flushed.
2750 
2751  This routine also decrements the sharecounts on the relevant PFNs.
2752 
2753 Arguments:
2754 
2755  VaFlushList - Supplies a pointer to the list to be flushed.
2756 
2757  Count - Supplies a count of entries to be flushed.
2758 
2759 Return Value:
2760 
2761  None.
2762 
2763 Environment:
2764 
2765  Kernel mode, working set mutex held, APC_LEVEL.
2766 
2767 --*/
2768 
2769 {
2770  ULONG i;
2771  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
2772  PMMPFN Pfn;
2773  PMMPTE PointerPte;
2774  MMPTE TempPte;
2775  MMPTE PreviousPte;
2776  KIRQL OldIrql;
2777 
2778  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
2779 
2780  ASSERT (FlushCount != 0);
2781 
2782  //
2783  // Put the PTEs in transition and decrement the number of
2784  // valid PTEs within the containing page table page. Note
2785  // that for a private page, the page table page is still
2786  // needed because the page is in transition.
2787  //
2788 
2789  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2790 
2791  for (i = 0; i < FlushCount; i += 1) {
2792 
2793  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VaFlushList[i]);
2794 
2795  TempPte = *PointerPte;
2796  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&TempPte);
2797  Pfn = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2798 
2799  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte,
2800  Pfn->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection);
2801 
2802  PreviousPte = *PointerPte;
2803 
2804  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
2805 
2806  MI_CAPTURE_DIRTY_BIT_TO_PFN (&PreviousPte, Pfn);
2807 
2808  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn, PageFrameIndex);
2809  }
2810 
2811  //
2812  // Flush the relevant entries from the translation buffer.
2813  //
2814 
2815  if (FlushCount == 1) {
2816  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
2817  }
2818  else if (FlushCount < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
2819  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (FlushCount, &VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
2820  }
2821  else {
2822  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x19);
2823  }
2824 
2825  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2826 
2827  return;
2828 }
2829 
2830 VOID
2831 MiEnablePagingOfDriver (
2832  IN PVOID ImageHandle
2833  )
2834 
2835 {
2836  ULONG Span;
2837  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
2838  PMMPTE LastPte;
2839  PMMPTE PointerPte;
2840  PVOID Base;
2841  ULONG i;
2842  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders;
2843  PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER FoundSection;
2844  PIMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER OptionalHeader;
2845 
2846  //
2847  // Don't page kernel mode code if customer does not want it paged.
2848  //
2849 
2850  if (MmDisablePagingExecutive & MM_SYSTEM_CODE_LOCKED_DOWN) {
2851  return;
2852  }
2853 
2854  //
2855  // If the driver has pageable code, make it paged.
2856  //
2857 
2858  DataTableEntry = (PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY) ImageHandle;
2859  Base = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
2860 
2861  NtHeaders = (PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS) RtlImageNtHeader (Base);
2862 
2863  if (NtHeaders == NULL) {
2864  return;
2865  }
2866 
2867  OptionalHeader = (PIMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER)((PCHAR)NtHeaders +
2868 #if defined (_WIN64)
2869  FIELD_OFFSET (IMAGE_NT_HEADERS64, OptionalHeader)
2870 #else
2871  FIELD_OFFSET (IMAGE_NT_HEADERS32, OptionalHeader)
2872 #endif
2873  );
2874 
2875  FoundSection = IMAGE_FIRST_SECTION (NtHeaders);
2876 
2877  i = NtHeaders->FileHeader.NumberOfSections;
2878 
2879  PointerPte = NULL;
2880 
2881  //
2882  // Initializing LastPte is not needed for correctness, but without it
2883  // the compiler cannot compile this code W4 to check for use of
2884  // uninitialized variables.
2885  //
2886 
2887  LastPte = NULL;
2888 
2889  while (i > 0) {
2890 #if DBG
2891  if ((*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'tini') ||
2892  (*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'egap')) {
2893  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_INFO_LEVEL,
2894  "driver %wZ has lower case sections (init or pagexxx)\n",
2895  &DataTableEntry->FullDllName);
2896  }
2897 #endif
2898 
2899  //
2900  // Mark as pageable any section which starts with the
2901  // first 4 characters PAGE or .eda (for the .edata section).
2902  //
2903 
2904  if ((*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'EGAP') ||
2905  (*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'ade.')) {
2906 
2907  //
2908  // This section is pageable, save away the start and end.
2909  //
2910 
2911  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
2912 
2913  //
2914  // Previous section was NOT pageable, get the start address.
2915  //
2916 
2917  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)(ROUND_TO_PAGES (
2918  (PCHAR)Base + FoundSection->VirtualAddress)));
2919  }
2920 
2921  //
2922  // Generally, SizeOfRawData is larger than VirtualSize for each
2923  // section because it includes the padding to get to the subsection
2924  // alignment boundary. However, if the image is linked with
2925  // subsection alignment == native page alignment, the linker will
2926  // have VirtualSize be much larger than SizeOfRawData because it
2927  // will account for all the bss.
2928  //
2929 
2930  Span = FoundSection->SizeOfRawData;
2931 
2932  if (Span < FoundSection->Misc.VirtualSize) {
2933  Span = FoundSection->Misc.VirtualSize;
2934  }
2935 
2936  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PCHAR)Base +
2937  FoundSection->VirtualAddress +
2938  (OptionalHeader->SectionAlignment - 1) +
2939  Span - PAGE_SIZE);
2940 
2941  }
2942  else {
2943 
2944  //
2945  // This section is not pageable, if the previous section was
2946  // pageable, enable it.
2947  //
2948 
2949  if (PointerPte != NULL) {
2950  MiSetPagingOfDriver (PointerPte, LastPte);
2951  PointerPte = NULL;
2952  }
2953  }
2954  i -= 1;
2955  FoundSection += 1;
2956  }
2957  if (PointerPte != NULL) {
2958  MiSetPagingOfDriver (PointerPte, LastPte);
2959  }
2960 }
2961 
2962 
2963 VOID
2964 MiSetPagingOfDriver (
2965  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
2966  IN PMMPTE LastPte
2967  )
2968 
2969 /*++
2970 
2971 Routine Description:
2972 
2973  This routine marks the specified range of PTEs as pageable.
2974 
2975 Arguments:
2976 
2977  PointerPte - Supplies the starting PTE.
2978 
2979  LastPte - Supplies the ending PTE.
2980 
2981 Return Value:
2982 
2983  None.
2984 
2985 Environment:
2986 
2987  Kernel Mode, IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below.
2988 
2989  This routine could be made PAGELK but it is a high frequency routine
2990  so it is actually better to keep it nonpaged to avoid bringing in the
2991  entire PAGELK section.
2992 
2993 --*/
2994 
2995 {
2996  PVOID Base;
2997  PFN_NUMBER PageCount;
2998  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
2999  PMMPFN Pfn;
3000  PETHREAD Thread;
3001  ULONG FlushCount;
3002  PVOID VaFlushList[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
3003 
3004  PAGED_CODE ();
3005 
3006  Base = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
3007 
3008  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (Base)) {
3009 
3010  //
3011  // No need to lock physical addresses.
3012  //
3013 
3014  return;
3015  }
3016 
3017  ASSERT (MI_IS_SESSION_IMAGE_ADDRESS (Base) == FALSE);
3018 
3019  PageCount = 0;
3020  FlushCount = 0;
3021  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
3022 
3023  LOCK_WORKING_SET (Thread, &MmSystemCacheWs);
3024 
3025  while (PointerPte <= LastPte) {
3026 
3027  //
3028  // Check to make sure this PTE has not already been
3029  // made pageable (or deleted). It is pageable if it
3030  // is not valid, or if the PFN database wsindex element
3031  // is non zero.
3032  //
3033 
3034  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
3035  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
3036  Pfn = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
3037  ASSERT (Pfn->u2.ShareCount == 1);
3038 
3039  //
3040  // If the wsindex is nonzero, then this page is already pageable
3041  // and has a WSLE entry. Ignore it here and let the trimmer
3042  // take it if memory comes under pressure.
3043  //
3044 
3045  if (Pfn->u1.WsIndex == 0) {
3046 
3047  //
3048  // Original PTE may need to be set for drivers loaded
3049  // via ntldr.
3050  //
3051 
3052  if (Pfn->OriginalPte.u.Long == 0) {
3053  Pfn->OriginalPte.u.Long = MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE;
3054  Pfn->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection |= MM_EXECUTE;
3055  }
3056 
3057  VaFlushList[FlushCount] = Base;
3058  FlushCount += 1;
3059 
3060  if (FlushCount == MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
3061  MiFlushPteListFreePfns ((PVOID *)&VaFlushList, FlushCount);
3062  FlushCount = 0;
3063  }
3064 
3065  PageCount += 1;
3066  }
3067  }
3068  Base = (PVOID)((PCHAR)Base + PAGE_SIZE);
3069  PointerPte += 1;
3070  }
3071 
3072  if (FlushCount != 0) {
3073  MiFlushPteListFreePfns ((PVOID *)&VaFlushList, FlushCount);
3074  }
3075 
3076  UNLOCK_WORKING_SET (Thread, &MmSystemCacheWs);
3077 
3078  if (PageCount != 0) {
3079  InterlockedExchangeAdd (&MmTotalSystemDriverPages, (LONG) PageCount);
3080 
3081  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PageCount,
3082  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_SET_DRIVER_PAGING);
3083  }
3084 }
3085 
3086 
3087 PVOID
3088 MmPageEntireDriver (
3089  __in PVOID AddressWithinSection
3090  )
3091 
3092 /*++
3093 
3094 Routine Description:
3095 
3096  This routine allows a driver to page out all of its code and
3097  data regardless of the attributes of the various image sections.
3098 
3099  Note, this routine can be called multiple times with no
3100  intervening calls to MmResetDriverPaging.
3101 
3102 Arguments:
3103 
3104  AddressWithinSection - Supplies an address within the driver, e.g.
3105  DriverEntry.
3106 
3107 Return Value:
3108 
3109  Base address of driver.
3110 
3111 Environment:
3112 
3113  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL or below.
3114 
3115 --*/
3116 
3117 {
3118  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
3119  PMMPTE FirstPte;
3120  PMMPTE LastPte;
3121  PVOID BaseAddress;
3122 
3123  PAGED_CODE();
3124
