3125  DataTableEntry = MiLookupDataTableEntry (AddressWithinSection, FALSE);
3126 
3127  if (DataTableEntry == NULL) {
3128  return NULL;
3129  }
3130 
3131  //
3132  // Don't page kernel mode code if disabled via registry.
3133  //
3134 
3135  if (MmDisablePagingExecutive & MM_SYSTEM_CODE_LOCKED_DOWN) {
3136  return DataTableEntry->DllBase;
3137  }
3138 
3139  if (DataTableEntry->SectionPointer != NULL) {
3140 
3141  //
3142  // Driver is mapped as an image (ie: session space), this is always
3143  // pageable.
3144  //
3145 
3146  ASSERT (MI_IS_SESSION_IMAGE_ADDRESS (AddressWithinSection) == TRUE);
3147 
3148  return DataTableEntry->DllBase;
3149  }
3150 
3151  //
3152  // Force any active DPCs to clear the system before we page the driver.
3153  //
3154 
3155  KeFlushQueuedDpcs ();
3156 
3157  BaseAddress = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
3158  FirstPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseAddress);
3159  LastPte = (FirstPte - 1) + (DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage >> PAGE_SHIFT);
3160 
3161  ASSERT (MI_IS_SESSION_IMAGE_ADDRESS (AddressWithinSection) == FALSE);
3162 
3163  MiSetPagingOfDriver (FirstPte, LastPte);
3164 
3165  return BaseAddress;
3166 }
3167 
3168 
3169 VOID
3170 MmResetDriverPaging (
3171  __in PVOID AddressWithinSection
3172  )
3173 
3174 /*++
3175 
3176 Routine Description:
3177 
3178  This routines resets the driver paging to what the image specified.
3179  Hence image sections such as the IAT, .text, .data will be locked
3180  down in memory.
3181 
3182  Note, there is no requirement that MmPageEntireDriver was called.
3183 
3184 Arguments:
3185 
3186  AddressWithinSection - Supplies an address within the driver, e.g.
3187  DriverEntry.
3188 
3189 Return Value:
3190 
3191  None.
3192 
3193 Environment:
3194 
3195  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL or below.
3196 
3197 --*/
3198 
3199 {
3200  ULONG Span;
3201  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
3202  PMMPTE LastPte;
3203  PMMPTE PointerPte;
3204  PVOID Base;
3205  ULONG i;
3206  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders;
3207  PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER FoundSection;
3208 
3209  PAGED_CODE();
3210 
3211  //
3212  // Don't page kernel mode code if disabled via registry.
3213  //
3214 
3215  if (MmDisablePagingExecutive & MM_SYSTEM_CODE_LOCKED_DOWN) {
3216  return;
3217  }
3218 
3219  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (AddressWithinSection)) {
3220  return;
3221  }
3222 
3223  //
3224  // If the driver has pageable code, make it paged.
3225  //
3226 
3227  DataTableEntry = MiLookupDataTableEntry (AddressWithinSection, FALSE);
3228 
3229  if (DataTableEntry->SectionPointer != NULL) {
3230 
3231  //
3232  // Driver is mapped by image hence already paged.
3233  //
3234 
3235  ASSERT (MI_IS_SESSION_IMAGE_ADDRESS (AddressWithinSection) == TRUE);
3236 
3237  return;
3238  }
3239 
3240  Base = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
3241 
3242  NtHeaders = (PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS) RtlImageNtHeader (Base);
3243 
3244  if (NtHeaders == NULL) {
3245  return;
3246  }
3247 
3248  FoundSection = (PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER)((PCHAR)NtHeaders +
3249  sizeof(ULONG) +
3250  sizeof(IMAGE_FILE_HEADER) +
3251  NtHeaders->FileHeader.SizeOfOptionalHeader
3252  );
3253 
3254  i = NtHeaders->FileHeader.NumberOfSections;
3255  PointerPte = NULL;
3256 
3257  while (i > 0) {
3258 #if DBG
3259  if ((*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'tini') ||
3260  (*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'egap')) {
3261  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_INFO_LEVEL,
3262  "driver %wZ has lower case sections (init or pagexxx)\n",
3263  &DataTableEntry->FullDllName);
3264  }
3265 #endif
3266 
3267  //
3268  // Don't lock down code for sections marked as discardable or
3269  // sections marked with the first 4 characters PAGE or .eda
3270  // (for the .edata section) or INIT.
3271  //
3272 
3273  if (((FoundSection->Characteristics & IMAGE_SCN_MEM_DISCARDABLE) != 0) ||
3274  (*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'EGAP') ||
3275  (*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'ade.') ||
3276  (*(PULONG)FoundSection->Name == 'TINI')) {
3277 
3278  NOTHING;
3279 
3280  }
3281  else {
3282 
3283  //
3284  // This section is non-pageable.
3285  //
3286 
3287  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (
3288  (PCHAR)Base + FoundSection->VirtualAddress);
3289 
3290  //
3291  // Generally, SizeOfRawData is larger than VirtualSize for each
3292  // section because it includes the padding to get to the subsection
3293  // alignment boundary. However, if the image is linked with
3294  // subsection alignment == native page alignment, the linker will
3295  // have VirtualSize be much larger than SizeOfRawData because it
3296  // will account for all the bss.
3297  //
3298 
3299  Span = FoundSection->SizeOfRawData;
3300 
3301  if (Span < FoundSection->Misc.VirtualSize) {
3302  Span = FoundSection->Misc.VirtualSize;
3303  }
3304 
3305  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PCHAR)Base +
3306  FoundSection->VirtualAddress +
3307  (Span - 1));
3308 
3309  ASSERT (PointerPte <= LastPte);
3310 
3311  MiLockCode (PointerPte, LastPte, MM_LOCK_BY_NONPAGE);
3312  }
3313  i -= 1;
3314  FoundSection += 1;
3315  }
3316  return;
3317 }
3318 
3319 
3320 VOID
3321 MiClearImports (
3322  IN PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry
3323  )
3324 /*++
3325 
3326 Routine Description:
3327 
3328  Free up the import list and clear the pointer. This stops the
3329  recursion performed in MiDereferenceImports().
3330 
3331 Arguments:
3332 
3333  DataTableEntry - provided for the driver.
3334 
3335 Return Value:
3336 
3337  Status of the import list construction operation.
3338 
3339 --*/
3340 
3341 {
3342  PAGED_CODE();
3343 
3344  if (DataTableEntry->LoadedImports == (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT) {
3345  return;
3346  }
3347 
3348  if (DataTableEntry->LoadedImports == (PVOID)NO_IMPORTS_USED) {
3349  NOTHING;
3350  }
3351  else if (SINGLE_ENTRY(DataTableEntry->LoadedImports)) {
3352  NOTHING;
3353  }
3354  else {
3355  //
3356  // free the memory
3357  //
3358  ExFreePool ((PVOID)DataTableEntry->LoadedImports);
3359  }
3360 
3361  //
3362  // stop the recursion
3363  //
3364  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT;
3365 }
3366 
3367 VOID
3368 MiRememberUnloadedDriver (
3369  IN PUNICODE_STRING DriverName,
3370  IN PVOID Address,
3371  IN ULONG Length
3372  )
3373 
3374 /*++
3375 
3376 Routine Description:
3377 
3378  This routine saves information about unloaded drivers so that ones that
3379  forget to delete lookaside lists or queues can be caught.
3380 
3381 Arguments:
3382 
3383  DriverName - Supplies a Unicode string containing the driver's name.
3384 
3385  Address - Supplies the address the driver was loaded at.
3386 
3387  Length - Supplies the number of bytes the driver load spanned.
3388 
3389 Return Value:
3390 
3391  None.
3392 
3393 --*/
3394 
3395 {
3396  PUNLOADED_DRIVERS Entry;
3397  ULONG NumberOfBytes;
3398 
3399  if (DriverName->Length == 0) {
3400 
3401  //
3402  // This is an aborted load and the driver name hasn't been filled
3403  // in yet. No need to save it.
3404  //
3405 
3406  return;
3407  }
3408 
3409  //
3410  // Serialization is provided by the caller, so just update the list now.
3411  // Note the allocations are nonpaged so they can be searched at bugcheck
3412  // time.
3413  //
3414 
3415  if (MmUnloadedDrivers == NULL) {
3416  NumberOfBytes = MI_UNLOADED_DRIVERS * sizeof (UNLOADED_DRIVERS);
3417 
3418  MmUnloadedDrivers = (PUNLOADED_DRIVERS)ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
3419  NumberOfBytes,
3420  'TDmM');
3421  if (MmUnloadedDrivers == NULL) {
3422  return;
3423  }
3424  RtlZeroMemory (MmUnloadedDrivers, NumberOfBytes);
3425  MmLastUnloadedDriver = 0;
3426  }
3427  else if (MmLastUnloadedDriver >= MI_UNLOADED_DRIVERS) {
3428  MmLastUnloadedDriver = 0;
3429  }
3430 
3431  Entry = &MmUnloadedDrivers[MmLastUnloadedDriver];
3432 
3433  //
3434  // Free the old entry as we recycle into the new.
3435  //
3436 
3437  RtlFreeUnicodeString (&Entry->Name);
3438 
3439  Entry->Name.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
3440  DriverName->Length,
3441  'TDmM');
3442 
3443  if (Entry->Name.Buffer == NULL) {
3444  Entry->Name.MaximumLength = 0;
3445  Entry->Name.Length = 0;
3446  MiUnloadsSkipped += 1;
3447  return;
3448  }
3449 
3450  RtlCopyMemory(Entry->Name.Buffer, DriverName->Buffer, DriverName->Length);
3451  Entry->Name.Length = DriverName->Length;
3452  Entry->Name.MaximumLength = DriverName->MaximumLength;
3453 
3454  Entry->StartAddress = Address;
3455  Entry->EndAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)Address + Length);
3456 
3457  KeQuerySystemTime (&Entry->CurrentTime);
3458 
3459  MiTotalUnloads += 1;
3460  MmLastUnloadedDriver += 1;
3461 }
3462 
3463 PUNICODE_STRING
3464 MmLocateUnloadedDriver (
3465  IN PVOID VirtualAddress
3466  )
3467 
3468 /*++
3469 
3470 Routine Description:
3471 
3472  This routine attempts to find the specified virtual address in the
3473  unloaded driver list.
3474 
3475 Arguments:
3476 
3477  VirtualAddress - Supplies a virtual address that might be within a driver
3478  that has already unloaded.
3479 
3480 Return Value:
3481 
3482  A pointer to a Unicode string containing the unloaded driver's name.
3483 
3484 Environment:
3485 
3486  Kernel mode, bugcheck time.
3487 
3488 --*/
3489 
3490 {
3491  PUNLOADED_DRIVERS Entry;
3492  ULONG i;
3493  ULONG Index;
3494 
3495  //
3496  // No serialization is needed because we've crashed.
3497  //
3498 
3499  if (MmUnloadedDrivers == NULL) {
3500  return NULL;
3501  }
3502 
3503  Index = MmLastUnloadedDriver - 1;
3504 
3505  for (i = 0; i < MI_UNLOADED_DRIVERS; i += 1) {
3506  if (Index >= MI_UNLOADED_DRIVERS) {
3507  Index = MI_UNLOADED_DRIVERS - 1;
3508  }
3509  Entry = &MmUnloadedDrivers[Index];
3510  if (Entry->Name.Buffer != NULL) {
3511  if ((VirtualAddress >= Entry->StartAddress) &&
3512  (VirtualAddress < Entry->EndAddress)) {
3513  return &Entry->Name;
3514  }
3515  }
3516  Index -= 1;
3517  }
3518 
3519  return NULL;
3520 }
3521 
3522 
3523 NTSTATUS
3524 MmUnloadSystemImage (
3525  IN PVOID ImageHandle
3526  )
3527 
3528 /*++
3529 
3530 Routine Description:
3531 
3532  This routine unloads a previously loaded system image and returns
3533  the allocated resources.
3534 
3535 Arguments:
3536 
3537  ImageHandle - Supplies a pointer to the section object of the
3538  image to unload.
3539 
3540 Return Value:
3541 
3542  Various NTSTATUS codes.
3543 
3544 Environment:
3545 
3546  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL or below, arbitrary process context.
3547 
3548 --*/
3549 
3550 {
3551  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
3552  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
3553  PMMPTE LastPte;
3554  PFN_NUMBER PagesRequired;
3555  PFN_NUMBER ResidentPages;
3556  PMMPTE PointerPte;
3557  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPtes;
3558  PFN_NUMBER RoundedNumberOfPtes;
3559  PVOID BasedAddress;
3560  SIZE_T NumberOfBytes;
3561  LOGICAL MustFree;
3562  SIZE_T CommittedPages;
3563  LOGICAL ViewDeleted;
3564  PIMAGE_ENTRY_IN_SESSION DriverImage;
3565  NTSTATUS Status;
3566  PSECTION SectionPointer;
3567  PKTHREAD CurrentThread;
3568 
3569  ViewDeleted = FALSE;
3570  DataTableEntry = (PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY)ImageHandle;
3571  BasedAddress = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
3572 
3573  //
3574  // Arbitrary process context so prevent suspend APCs now.
3575  //
3576 
3577  CurrentThread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
3578  KeEnterCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
3579 
3580  KeWaitForSingleObject (&MmSystemLoadLock,
3581  WrVirtualMemory,
3582  KernelMode,
3583  FALSE,
3584  (PLARGE_INTEGER)NULL);
3585 
3586  if (DataTableEntry->LoadedImports == (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT) {
3587 
3588  //
3589  // Any driver loaded at boot that did not have its import list
3590  // and LoadCount reconstructed cannot be unloaded because we don't
3591  // know how many other drivers may be linked to it.
3592  //
3593 
3594  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
3595  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
3596  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
3597  }
3598 
3599  ASSERT (DataTableEntry->LoadCount != 0);
3600 
3601  if (MI_IS_SESSION_IMAGE_ADDRESS (BasedAddress)) {
3602 
3603  //
3604  // A printer driver may be referenced multiple times for the
3605  // same session space. Only unload the last reference.
3606  //
3607 
3608  DriverImage = MiSessionLookupImage (BasedAddress);
3609 
3610  ASSERT (DriverImage);
3611 
3612  ASSERT (DriverImage->ImageCountInThisSession);
3613 
3614  DriverImage->ImageCountInThisSession -= 1;
3615 
3616  if (DriverImage->ImageCountInThisSession != 0) {
3617 
3618  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
3619  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
3620 
3621  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
3622  }
3623 
3624  //
3625  // The reference count for this image has dropped to zero in this
3626  // session, so we can delete this session's view of the image.
3627  //
3628 
3629  NumberOfBytes = DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage;
3630 
3631  //
3632  // Free the session space taken up by the image, unmapping it from
3633  // the current VA space - note this does not remove page table pages
3634  // from the session PageTables[]. Each data page is only freed
3635  // if there are no other references to it (ie: from any other
3636  // sessions).
3637  //
3638 
3639  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BasedAddress);
3640  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)BasedAddress + NumberOfBytes));
3641 
3642  PagesRequired = MiDeleteSystemPageableVm (PointerPte,
3643  (PFN_NUMBER)(LastPte - PointerPte),
3644  MI_DELETE_FLUSH_TB,
3645  &ResidentPages);
3646 
3647  //
3648  // Note resident available is returned here without waiting for load
3649  // count to reach zero because it is charged each time a session space
3650  // driver locks down its code or data regardless of whether it is really
3651  // the same copy-on-write backing page(s) that some other session has
3652  // already locked down.
3653  //
3654 
3655  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (ResidentPages,
3656  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_UNLOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE);
3657 
3658  SectionPointer = (PSECTION) DataTableEntry->SectionPointer;
3659 
3660  ASSERT (SectionPointer != NULL);
3661  ASSERT (SectionPointer->Segment->u1.ImageCommitment != 0);
3662 
3663  if (BasedAddress != SectionPointer->Segment->BasedAddress) {
3664  CommittedPages = SectionPointer->Segment->TotalNumberOfPtes;
3665  }
3666  else {
3667  CommittedPages = SectionPointer->Segment->u1.ImageCommitment;
3668  }
3669 
3670  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmSessionSpace->CommittedPages,
3671  0 - CommittedPages);
3672 
3673  MM_BUMP_SESS_COUNTER(MM_DBG_SESSION_COMMIT_IMAGE_UNLOAD,
3674  (ULONG)CommittedPages);
3675 
3676  ViewDeleted = TRUE;
3677 
3678  //
3679  // Return the commitment we took out on the pagefile when the
3680  // image was allocated.
3681  //
3682 
3683  MiReturnCommitment (CommittedPages);
3684  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_DRIVER_UNLOAD, CommittedPages);
3685 
3686  //
3687  // Tell the session space image handler that we are releasing
3688  // our claim to the image.
3689  //
3690 
3691  ASSERT (DataTableEntry->LoadCount != 0);
3692 
3693  MiRemoveImageSessionWide (DataTableEntry,
3694  BasedAddress,
3695  DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage);
3696 
3697  ASSERT (MiSessionLookupImage (BasedAddress) == NULL);
3698  }
3699 
3700  ASSERT (DataTableEntry->LoadCount != 0);
3701 
3702  DataTableEntry->LoadCount -= 1;
3703 
3704  if (DataTableEntry->LoadCount != 0) {
3705 
3706  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
3707  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
3708  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
3709  }
3710 
3711  if (MmVerifierData.Level & DRIVER_VERIFIER_DEADLOCK_DETECTION) {
3712  VerifierDeadlockFreePool (DataTableEntry->DllBase, DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage);
3713  }
3714 
3715  if (DataTableEntry->Flags & LDRP_IMAGE_VERIFYING) {
3716  MiVerifyingDriverUnloading (DataTableEntry);
3717  }
3718 
3719  if (MiActiveVerifierThunks != 0) {
3720  MiVerifierCheckThunks (DataTableEntry);
3721  }
3722 
3723  //
3724  // Unload symbols from debugger.
3725  //
3726 
3727  if (DataTableEntry->Flags & LDRP_DEBUG_SYMBOLS_LOADED) {
3728 
3729  //
3730  // TEMP TEMP TEMP rip out when debugger converted
3731  //
3732 
3733  ANSI_STRING AnsiName;
3734 
3735  Status = RtlUnicodeStringToAnsiString (&AnsiName,
3736  &DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
3737  TRUE);
3738 
3739  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
3740  DbgUnLoadImageSymbols (&AnsiName, BasedAddress, (ULONG)-1);
3741  RtlFreeAnsiString (&AnsiName);
3742  }
3743  }
3744 
3745  //
3746  // No unload can happen till after Mm has finished Phase 1 initialization.
3747  // Therefore, large pages are already in effect (if this platform supports
3748  // it).
3749  //
3750 
3751  if (ViewDeleted == FALSE) {
3752 
3753  NumberOfPtes = DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage >> PAGE_SHIFT;
3754 
3755  if (MmSnapUnloads) {
3756  MiRememberUnloadedDriver (&DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
3757  BasedAddress,
3758  (ULONG)(NumberOfPtes << PAGE_SHIFT));
3759  }
3760 
3761  if (DataTableEntry->Flags & LDRP_SYSTEM_MAPPED) {
3762 
3763  if (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (MiGetPdeAddress (BasedAddress))) {
3764 
3765  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (MiGetPdeAddress (BasedAddress)) + MiGetPteOffset (BasedAddress);
3766 
3767  RoundedNumberOfPtes = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (NumberOfPtes,
3768  MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT);
3769  MiUnmapLargePages (BasedAddress,
3770  RoundedNumberOfPtes << PAGE_SHIFT);
3771 
3772  //
3773  // MiFreeContiguousPages is going to return commitment
3774  // and resident available so don't do it here.
3775  //
3776 
3777  MiRemoveCachedRange (PageFrameIndex, PageFrameIndex + RoundedNumberOfPtes - 1);
3778  MiFreeContiguousPages (PageFrameIndex, RoundedNumberOfPtes);
3779  PagesRequired = NumberOfPtes;
3780  }
3781  else {
3782  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BasedAddress);
3783 
3784  //
3785  // No explicit TB flush is done here, instead the system PTE
3786  // management code will handle this in a lazy fashion.
3787  //
3788 
3789  PagesRequired = MiDeleteSystemPageableVm (PointerPte,
3790  NumberOfPtes,
3791  0,
3792  &ResidentPages);
3793 
3794  //
3795  // Note that drivers loaded at boot that have not been relocated
3796  // have no system PTEs or commit charged.
3797  //
3798 
3799  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPte,
3800  (ULONG)NumberOfPtes,
3801  SystemPteSpace);
3802 
3803  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (ResidentPages,
3804  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_UNLOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE1);
3805 
3806  MiReturnCommitment (PagesRequired);
3807  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_DRIVER_UNLOAD1, PagesRequired);
3808 
3809  InterlockedExchangeAdd (&MmTotalSystemDriverPages,
3810  0 - (ULONG)(PagesRequired - ResidentPages));
3811  }
3812 
3813  if (DataTableEntry->SectionPointer != NULL) {
3814  InterlockedExchangeAdd ((PLONG)&MmDriverCommit,
3815  (LONG) (0 - PagesRequired));
3816  }
3817  }
3818  else {
3819 
3820  //
3821  // This must be a boot driver that was not relocated into
3822  // system PTEs. If large or super pages are enabled, the
3823  // image pages must be freed without referencing the
3824  // non-existent page table pages. If large/super pages are
3825  // not enabled, note that system PTEs were not used to map the
3826  // image and thus, cannot be freed.
3827 
3828  //
3829  // This is further complicated by the fact that the INIT and/or
3830  // discardable portions of these images may have already been freed.
3831  //
3832 
3833  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (NumberOfPtes,
3834  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_UNLOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE1);
3835 
3836  MiReturnCommitment (NumberOfPtes);
3837  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_DRIVER_UNLOAD1, NumberOfPtes);
3838  }
3839  }
3840 
3841  //
3842  // Search the loaded module list for the data table entry that describes
3843  // the DLL that was just unloaded. It is possible an entry is not in the
3844  // list if a failure occurred at a point in loading the DLL just before
3845  // the data table entry was generated.
3846  //
3847 
3848  if (DataTableEntry->InLoadOrderLinks.Flink != NULL) {
3849  MiProcessLoaderEntry (DataTableEntry, FALSE);
3850  MustFree = TRUE;
3851  }
3852  else {
3853  MustFree = FALSE;
3854  }
3855 
3856  //
3857  // Handle unloading of any dependent DLLs that we loaded automatically
3858  // for this image.
3859  //
3860 
3861  MiDereferenceImports ((PLOAD_IMPORTS)DataTableEntry->LoadedImports);
3862 
3863  MiClearImports (DataTableEntry);
3864 
3865  //
3866  // Free this loader entry.
3867  //
3868 
3869  if (MustFree == TRUE) {
3870 
3871  if (DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Buffer != NULL) {
3872  ExFreePool (DataTableEntry->FullDllName.Buffer);
3873  }
3874 
3875  //
3876  // Dereference the section object (session images only).
3877  //
3878 
3879  if (DataTableEntry->SectionPointer != NULL) {
3880  ObDereferenceObject (DataTableEntry->SectionPointer);
3881  }
3882 
3883  if (DataTableEntry->PatchInformation) {
3884  MiRundownHotpatchList ((PVOID)DataTableEntry->PatchInformation);
3885  }
3886 
3887  ExFreePool (DataTableEntry);
3888  }
3889 
3890  KeReleaseMutant (&MmSystemLoadLock, 1, FALSE, FALSE);
3891  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
3892 
3893  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
3894 }
3895 
3896 
3897 NTSTATUS
3898 MiBuildImportsForBootDrivers (
3899  VOID
3900  )
3901 
3902 /*++
3903 
3904 Routine Description:
3905 
3906  Construct an import list chain for boot-loaded drivers.
3907  If this cannot be done for an entry, its chain is set to LOADED_AT_BOOT.
3908 
3909  If a chain can be successfully built, then this driver's DLLs
3910  will be automatically unloaded if this driver goes away (provided
3911  no other driver is also using them). Otherwise, on driver unload,
3912  its dependent DLLs would have to be explicitly unloaded.
3913 
3914  Note that the incoming LoadCount values are not correct and thus, they
3915  are reinitialized here.
3916 
3917 Arguments:
3918 
3919  None.
3920 
3921 Return Value:
3922 
3923  Various NTSTATUS codes.
3924 
3925 --*/
3926 
3927 {
3928  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
3929  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
3930  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry2;
3931  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry2;
3932  ULONG i;
3933  ULONG j;
3934  ULONG ImageCount;
3935  PVOID *ImageReferences;
3936  PVOID LastImageReference;
3937  PULONG_PTR ImportThunk;
3938  ULONG_PTR BaseAddress;
3939  ULONG_PTR LastAddress;
3940  ULONG ImportSize;
3941  ULONG ImportListSize;
3942  PLOAD_IMPORTS ImportList;
3943  LOGICAL UndoEverything;
3944  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY KernelDataTableEntry;
3945  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY HalDataTableEntry;
3946  UNICODE_STRING KernelString;
3947  UNICODE_STRING HalString;
3948 
3949  PAGED_CODE();
3950 
3951  ImageCount = 0;
3952 
3953  KernelDataTableEntry = NULL;
3954  HalDataTableEntry = NULL;
3955 
3956 #define KERNEL_NAME L"ntoskrnl.exe"
3957 
3958  KernelString.Buffer = (const PUSHORT) KERNEL_NAME;
3959  KernelString.Length = sizeof (KERNEL_NAME) - sizeof (WCHAR);
3960  KernelString.MaximumLength = sizeof KERNEL_NAME;
3961 
3962 #define HAL_NAME L"hal.dll"
3963 
3964  HalString.Buffer = (const PUSHORT) HAL_NAME;
3965  HalString.Length = sizeof (HAL_NAME) - sizeof (WCHAR);
3966  HalString.MaximumLength = sizeof HAL_NAME;
3967 
3968  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
3969 
3970  while (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
3971 
3972  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
3973  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
3974  InLoadOrderLinks);
3975 
3976  if (RtlEqualUnicodeString (&KernelString,
3977  &DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
3978  TRUE)) {
3979 
3980  KernelDataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
3981  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
3982  InLoadOrderLinks);
3983  }
3984  else if (RtlEqualUnicodeString (&HalString,
3985  &DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
3986  TRUE)) {
3987 
3988  HalDataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
3989  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
3990  InLoadOrderLinks);
3991  }
3992 
3993  //
3994  // Initialize these properly so error recovery is simplified.
3995  //
3996 
3997  if (DataTableEntry->Flags & LDRP_DRIVER_DEPENDENT_DLL) {
3998  if ((DataTableEntry == HalDataTableEntry) || (DataTableEntry == KernelDataTableEntry)) {
3999  DataTableEntry->LoadCount = 1;
4000  }
4001  else {
4002  DataTableEntry->LoadCount = 0;
4003  }
4004  }
4005  else {
4006  DataTableEntry->LoadCount = 1;
4007  }
4008 
4009  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT;
4010 
4011  ImageCount += 1;
4012  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
4013  }
4014 
4015  if (KernelDataTableEntry == NULL || HalDataTableEntry == NULL) {
4016  return STATUS_NOT_FOUND;
4017  }
4018 
4019  ImageReferences = (PVOID *) ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool | POOL_COLD_ALLOCATION,
4020  ImageCount * sizeof (PVOID),
4021  'TDmM');
4022 
4023  if (ImageReferences == NULL) {
4024  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4025  }
4026 
4027  UndoEverything = FALSE;
4028 
4029  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
4030 
4031  for ( ; NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList; NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink) {
4032 
4033  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
4034  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
4035  InLoadOrderLinks);
4036 
4037  ImportThunk = (PULONG_PTR)RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (
4038  DataTableEntry->DllBase,
4039  TRUE,
4040  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IAT,
4041  &ImportSize);
4042 
4043  if (ImportThunk == NULL) {
4044  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = NO_IMPORTS_USED;
4045  continue;
4046  }
4047 
4048  RtlZeroMemory (ImageReferences, ImageCount * sizeof (PVOID));
4049 
4050  ImportSize /= sizeof(PULONG_PTR);
4051 
4052  BaseAddress = 0;
4053 
4054  //
4055  // Initializing these locals is not needed for correctness, but
4056  // without it the compiler cannot compile this code W4 to check
4057  // for use of uninitialized variables.
4058  //
4059 
4060  j = 0;
4061  LastAddress = 0;
4062 
4063  for (i = 0; i < ImportSize; i += 1, ImportThunk += 1) {
4064 
4065  //
4066  // Check the hint first.
4067  //
4068 
4069  if (BaseAddress != 0) {
4070  if (*ImportThunk >= BaseAddress && *ImportThunk < LastAddress) {
4071  ASSERT (ImageReferences[j]);
4072  continue;
4073  }
4074  }
4075 
4076  j = 0;
4077  NextEntry2 = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
4078 
4079  while (NextEntry2 != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
4080 
4081  DataTableEntry2 = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry2,
4082  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
4083  InLoadOrderLinks);
4084 
4085  BaseAddress = (ULONG_PTR) DataTableEntry2->DllBase;
4086  LastAddress = BaseAddress + DataTableEntry2->SizeOfImage;
4087 
4088  if (*ImportThunk >= BaseAddress && *ImportThunk < LastAddress) {
4089  ImageReferences[j] = DataTableEntry2;
4090  break;
4091  }
4092 
4093  NextEntry2 = NextEntry2->Flink;
4094  j += 1;
4095  }
4096 
4097  if (*ImportThunk < BaseAddress || *ImportThunk >= LastAddress) {
4098  if (*ImportThunk) {
4099 #if DBG
4100  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_WARNING_LEVEL,
4101  "MM: broken import linkage %p %p %p\n",
4102  DataTableEntry,
4103  ImportThunk,
4104  *ImportThunk);
4105  DbgBreakPoint ();
4106 #endif
4107  UndoEverything = TRUE;
4108  goto finished;
4109  }
4110 
4111  BaseAddress = 0;
4112  }
4113  }
4114 
4115  ImportSize = 0;
4116 
4117  //
4118  // Initializing LastImageReference is not needed for correctness, but
4119  // without it the compiler cannot compile this code W4 to check
4120  // for use of uninitialized variables.
4121  //
4122 
4123  LastImageReference = NULL;
4124 
4125  for (i = 0; i < ImageCount; i += 1) {
4126 
4127  if ((ImageReferences[i] != NULL) &&
4128  (ImageReferences[i] != KernelDataTableEntry) &&
4129  (ImageReferences[i] != HalDataTableEntry)) {
4130 
4131  LastImageReference = ImageReferences[i];
4132  ImportSize += 1;
4133  }
4134  }
4135 
4136  if (ImportSize == 0) {
4137  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = NO_IMPORTS_USED;
4138  }
4139  else if (ImportSize == 1) {
4140  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = POINTER_TO_SINGLE_ENTRY (LastImageReference);
4141  ((PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY)LastImageReference)->LoadCount += 1;
4142  }
4143  else {
4144  ImportListSize = ImportSize * sizeof(PVOID) + sizeof(SIZE_T);
4145 
4146  ImportList = (PLOAD_IMPORTS) ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool | POOL_COLD_ALLOCATION,
4147  ImportListSize,
4148  'TDmM');
4149 
4150  if (ImportList == NULL) {
4151  UndoEverything = TRUE;
4152  break;
4153  }
4154 
4155  ImportList->Count = ImportSize;
4156 
4157  j = 0;
4158  for (i = 0; i < ImageCount; i += 1) {
4159 
4160  if ((ImageReferences[i] != NULL) &&
4161  (ImageReferences[i] != KernelDataTableEntry) &&
4162  (ImageReferences[i] != HalDataTableEntry)) {
4163 
4164  ImportList->Entry[j] = ImageReferences[i];
4165  ((PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY)ImageReferences[i])->LoadCount += 1;
4166  j += 1;
4167  }
4168  }
4169 
4170  ASSERT (j == ImportSize);
4171 
4172  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = ImportList;
4173  }
4174  }
4175 
4176 finished:
4177 
4178  ExFreePool ((PVOID)ImageReferences);
4179 
4180  //
4181  // The kernel and HAL are never unloaded.
4182  //
4183 
4184  if ((KernelDataTableEntry->LoadedImports != NO_IMPORTS_USED) &&
4185  (!POINTER_TO_SINGLE_ENTRY(KernelDataTableEntry->LoadedImports))) {
4186  ExFreePool ((PVOID)KernelDataTableEntry->LoadedImports);
4187  }
4188 
4189  if ((HalDataTableEntry->LoadedImports != NO_IMPORTS_USED) &&
4190  (!POINTER_TO_SINGLE_ENTRY(HalDataTableEntry->LoadedImports))) {
4191  ExFreePool ((PVOID)HalDataTableEntry->LoadedImports);
4192  }
4193 
4194  KernelDataTableEntry->LoadedImports = (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT;
4195  HalDataTableEntry->LoadedImports = (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT;
4196 
4197  if (UndoEverything == TRUE) {
4198 
4199  //
4200  // An error occurred and this is an all or nothing operation so
4201  // roll everything back.
4202  //
4203 
4204  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
4205  while (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
4206  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
4207  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
4208  InLoadOrderLinks);
4209 
4210  ImportList = DataTableEntry->LoadedImports;
4211  if (ImportList == LOADED_AT_BOOT || ImportList == NO_IMPORTS_USED ||
4212  SINGLE_ENTRY(ImportList)) {
4213  NOTHING;
4214  }
4215  else {
4216  ExFreePool (ImportList);
4217  }
4218 
4219  DataTableEntry->LoadedImports = (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT;
4220  DataTableEntry->LoadCount = 1;
4221  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
4222  }
4223 
4224  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4225  }
4226 
4227  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
4228 }
4229 
4230 
4231 LOGICAL
4232 MiCallDllUnloadAndUnloadDll(
4233  IN PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry
4234  )
4235 
4236 /*++
4237 
4238 Routine Description:
4239 
4240  All the references from other drivers to this DLL have been cleared.
4241  The only remaining issue is that this DLL must support being unloaded.
4242  This means having no outstanding DPCs, allocated pool, etc.
4243 
4244  If the DLL has an unload routine that returns SUCCESS, then we clean
4245  it up and free up its memory now.
4246 
4247  Note this routine is NEVER called for drivers - only for DLLs that were
4248  loaded due to import references from various drivers.
4249 
4250 Arguments:
4251 
4252  DataTableEntry - provided for the DLL.
4253 
4254 Return Value:
4255 
4256  TRUE if the DLL was successfully unloaded, FALSE if not.
4257 
4258 --*/
4259 
4260 {
4261  PMM_DLL_UNLOAD Func;
4262  NTSTATUS Status;
4263  LOGICAL Unloaded;
4264 
4265  PAGED_CODE();
4266 
4267  Unloaded = FALSE;
4268 
4269  Func = (PMM_DLL_UNLOAD) (ULONG_PTR) MiLocateExportName (DataTableEntry->DllBase, "DllUnload");
4270 
4271  if (Func) {
4272 
4273  //
4274  // The unload function was found in the DLL so unload it now.
4275  //
4276 
4277  Status = Func();
4278 
4279  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
4280 
4281  //
4282  // Set up the reference count so the import DLL looks like a regular
4283  // driver image is being unloaded.
4284  //
4285 
4286  ASSERT (DataTableEntry->LoadCount == 0);
4287  DataTableEntry->LoadCount = 1;
4288 
4289  MmUnloadSystemImage ((PVOID)DataTableEntry);
4290  Unloaded = TRUE;
4291  }
4292  }
4293 
4294  return Unloaded;
4295 }
4296 
4297 
4298 PVOID
4299 MiLocateExportName (
4300  IN PVOID DllBase,
4301  IN PCHAR FunctionName
4302  )
4303 
4304 /*++
4305 
4306 Routine Description:
4307 
4308  This function is invoked to locate a function name in an export directory.
4309 
4310 Arguments:
4311 
4312  DllBase - Supplies the image base.
4313 
4314  FunctionName - Supplies the the name to be located.
4315 
4316 Return Value:
4317 
4318  The address of the located function or NULL.
4319 
4320 --*/
4321 
4322 {
4323  PVOID Func;
4324  PULONG NameTableBase;
4325  PUSHORT NameOrdinalTableBase;
4326  PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY ExportDirectory;
4327  PULONG Addr;
4328  ULONG ExportSize;
4329  LONG Low;
4330  LONG Middle;
4331  LONG High;
4332  LONG Result;
4333  USHORT OrdinalNumber;
4334 
4335  PAGED_CODE();
4336 
4337  Func = NULL;
4338 
4339  //
4340  // Locate the DLL's export directory.
4341  //
4342 
4343  ExportDirectory = (PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY) RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (
4344  DllBase,
4345  TRUE,
4346  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT,
4347  &ExportSize);
4348 
4349  if (ExportDirectory) {
4350 
4351  NameTableBase = (PULONG)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfNames);
4352  NameOrdinalTableBase = (PUSHORT)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfNameOrdinals);
4353 
4354  //
4355  // Look in the export name table for the specified function name.
4356  //
4357 
4358  Low = 0;
4359  Middle = 0;
4360  High = ExportDirectory->NumberOfNames - 1;
4361 
4362  while (High >= Low) {
4363 
4364  //
4365  // Compute the next probe index and compare the export name entry
4366  // with the specified function name.
4367  //
4368 
4369  Middle = (Low + High) >> 1;
4370  Result = strcmp(FunctionName,
4371  (PCHAR)((PCHAR)DllBase + NameTableBase[Middle]));
4372 
4373  if (Result < 0) {
4374  High = Middle - 1;
4375  }
4376  else if (Result > 0) {
4377  Low = Middle + 1;
4378  }
4379  else {
4380  break;
4381  }
4382  }
4383 
4384  //
4385  // If the high index is less than the low index, then a matching table
4386  // entry was not found. Otherwise, get the ordinal number from the
4387  // ordinal table and location the function address.
4388  //
4389 
4390  if (High >= Low) {
4391 
4392  OrdinalNumber = NameOrdinalTableBase[Middle];
4393  Addr = (PULONG)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfFunctions);
4394  Func = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)DllBase + Addr[OrdinalNumber]);
4395 
4396  //
4397  // If the function address is w/in range of the export directory,
4398  // then the function is forwarded, which is not allowed, so ignore
4399  // it.
4400  //
4401 
4402  if ((ULONG_PTR)Func > (ULONG_PTR)ExportDirectory &&
4403  (ULONG_PTR)Func < ((ULONG_PTR)ExportDirectory + ExportSize)) {
4404  Func = NULL;
4405  }
4406  }
4407  }
4408 
4409  return Func;
4410 }
4411 
4412 
4413 NTSTATUS
4414 MiDereferenceImports (
4415  IN PLOAD_IMPORTS ImportList
4416  )
4417 
4418 /*++
4419 
4420 Routine Description:
4421 
4422  Decrement the reference count on each DLL specified in the image import
4423  list. If any DLL's reference count reaches zero, then free the DLL.
4424 
4425  No locks may be held on entry as MmUnloadSystemImage may be called.
4426 
4427  The parameter list is freed here as well.
4428 
4429 Arguments:
4430 
4431  ImportList - Supplies the list of DLLs to dereference.
4432 
4433 Return Value:
4434 
4435  Status of the dereference operation.
4436 
4437 --*/
4438 
4439 {
4440  ULONG i;
4441  LOGICAL Unloaded;
4442  PVOID SavedImports;
4443  LOAD_IMPORTS SingleTableEntry;
4444  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY ImportTableEntry;
4445 
4446  PAGED_CODE();
4447 
4448  if (ImportList == LOADED_AT_BOOT || ImportList == NO_IMPORTS_USED) {
4449  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
4450  }
4451 
4452  if (SINGLE_ENTRY(ImportList)) {
4453  SingleTableEntry.Count = 1;
4454  SingleTableEntry.Entry[0] = SINGLE_ENTRY_TO_POINTER(ImportList);
4455  ImportList = &SingleTableEntry;
4456  }
4457 
4458  for (i = 0; i < ImportList->Count && ImportList->Entry[i]; i += 1) {
4459  ImportTableEntry = ImportList->Entry[i];
4460 
4461  if (ImportTableEntry->LoadedImports == (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT) {
4462 
4463  //
4464  // Skip this one - it was loaded by ntldr.
4465  //
4466 
4467  continue;
4468  }
4469 
4470 #if DBG
4471  {
4472  ULONG ImageCount;
4473  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
4474  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
4475 
4476  //
4477  // Assert that the first 2 entries are never dereferenced as
4478  // unloading the kernel or HAL would be fatal.
4479  //
4480 
4481  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
4482 
4483  ImageCount = 0;
4484  while (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList && ImageCount < 2) {
4485  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
4486  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
4487  InLoadOrderLinks);
4488  ASSERT (ImportTableEntry != DataTableEntry);
4489  ASSERT (DataTableEntry->LoadCount == 1);
4490  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
4491  ImageCount += 1;
4492  }
4493  }
4494 #endif
4495 
4496  ASSERT (ImportTableEntry->LoadCount >= 1);
4497 
4498  ImportTableEntry->LoadCount -= 1;
4499 
4500  if (ImportTableEntry->LoadCount == 0) {
4501 
4502  //
4503  // Unload this dependent DLL - we only do this to non-referenced
4504  // non-boot-loaded drivers. Stop the import list recursion prior
4505  // to unloading - we know we're done at this point.
4506  //
4507  // Note we can continue on afterwards without restarting
4508  // regardless of which locks get released and reacquired
4509  // because this chain is private.
4510  //
4511 
4512  SavedImports = ImportTableEntry->LoadedImports;
4513 
4514  ImportTableEntry->LoadedImports = (PVOID)NO_IMPORTS_USED;
4515 
4516  Unloaded = MiCallDllUnloadAndUnloadDll ((PVOID)ImportTableEntry);
4517 
4518  if (Unloaded == TRUE) {
4519 
4520  //
4521  // This DLL was unloaded so recurse through its imports and
4522  // attempt to unload all of those too.
4523  //
4524 
4525  MiDereferenceImports ((PLOAD_IMPORTS)SavedImports);
4526 
4527  if ((SavedImports != (PVOID)LOADED_AT_BOOT) &&
4528  (SavedImports != (PVOID)NO_IMPORTS_USED) &&
4529  (!SINGLE_ENTRY(SavedImports))) {
4530 
4531  ExFreePool (SavedImports);
4532  }
4533  }
4534  else {
4535  ImportTableEntry->LoadedImports = SavedImports;
4536  }
4537  }
4538  }
4539 
4540  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
4541 }
4542 
4543 
4544 NTSTATUS
4545 MiResolveImageReferences (
4546  PVOID ImageBase,
4547  IN PUNICODE_STRING ImageFileDirectory,
4548  IN PUNICODE_STRING NamePrefix OPTIONAL,
4549  OUT PCHAR *MissingProcedureName,
4550  OUT PWSTR *MissingDriverName,
4551  OUT PLOAD_IMPORTS *LoadedImports
4552  )
4553 
4554 /*++
4555 
4556 Routine Description:
4557 
4558  This routine resolves the references from the newly loaded driver
4559  to the kernel, HAL and other drivers.
4560 
4561 Arguments:
4562 
4563  ImageBase - Supplies the address of which the image header resides.
4564 
4565  ImageFileDirectory - Supplies the directory to load referenced DLLs.
4566 
4567 Return Value:
4568 
4569  Status of the image reference resolution.
4570 
4571 --*/
4572 
4573 {
4574  PCHAR MissingProcedureStorageArea;
4575  PVOID ImportBase;
4576  ULONG ImportSize;
4577  ULONG ImportListSize;
4578  ULONG Count;
4579  ULONG i;
4580  PIMAGE_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR ImportDescriptor;
4581  PIMAGE_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR Imp;
4582  NTSTATUS st;
4583  ULONG ExportSize;
4584  PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY ExportDirectory;
4585  PIMAGE_THUNK_DATA NameThunk;
4586  PIMAGE_THUNK_DATA AddrThunk;
4587  PSZ ImportName;
4588  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
4589  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
4590  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY SingleEntry;
4591  ANSI_STRING AnsiString;
4592  UNICODE_STRING ImportName_U;
4593  UNICODE_STRING ImportDescriptorName_U;
4594  UNICODE_STRING DllToLoad;
4595  UNICODE_STRING DllToLoad2;
4596  PVOID Section;
4597  PVOID BaseAddress;
4598  LOGICAL PrefixedNameAllocated;
4599  LOGICAL ReferenceImport;
4600  ULONG LinkWin32k = 0;
4601  ULONG LinkNonWin32k = 0;
4602  PLOAD_IMPORTS ImportList;
4603  PLOAD_IMPORTS CompactedImportList;
4604  LOGICAL Loaded;
4605  UNICODE_STRING DriverDirectory;
4606 
4607  PAGED_CODE();
4608 
4609  *LoadedImports = NO_IMPORTS_USED;
4610 
4611  MissingProcedureStorageArea = *MissingProcedureName;
4612 
4613  ImportDescriptor = (PIMAGE_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR) RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (
4614  ImageBase,
4615  TRUE,
4616  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IMPORT,
4617  &ImportSize);
4618 
4619  if (ImportDescriptor == NULL) {
4620  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
4621  }
4622 
4623  // Count the number of imports so we can allocate enough room to
4624  // store them all chained off this module's LDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY.
4625  //
4626 
4627  Count = 0;
4628  for (Imp = ImportDescriptor; Imp->Name && Imp->OriginalFirstThunk; Imp += 1) {
4629  Count += 1;
4630  }
4631 
4632  if (Count != 0) {
4633  ImportListSize = Count * sizeof(PVOID) + sizeof(SIZE_T);
4634 
4635  ImportList = (PLOAD_IMPORTS) ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool | POOL_COLD_ALLOCATION,
4636  ImportListSize,
4637  'TDmM');
4638 
4639  //
4640  // Zero it so we can recover gracefully if we fail in the middle.
4641  // If the allocation failed, just don't build the import list.
4642  //
4643 
4644  if (ImportList != NULL) {
4645  RtlZeroMemory (ImportList, ImportListSize);
4646  ImportList->Count = Count;
4647  }
4648  }
4649  else {
4650  ImportList = NULL;
4651  }
4652 
4653  Count = 0;
4654  while (ImportDescriptor->Name && ImportDescriptor->OriginalFirstThunk) {
4655 
4656  ImportName = (PSZ)((PCHAR)ImageBase + ImportDescriptor->Name);
4657 
4658  //
4659  // A driver can link with win32k.sys if and only if it is a GDI
4660  // driver.
4661  // Also display drivers can only link to win32k.sys (and BBT ...).
4662  //
4663  // So if we get a driver that links to win32k.sys and has more
4664  // than one set of imports, we will fail to load it.
4665  //
4666 
4667  LinkWin32k = LinkWin32k |
4668  (!_strnicmp(ImportName, "win32k", sizeof("win32k") - 1));
4669 
4670  //
4671  // We don't want to count coverage, win32k and irt (BBT) since
4672  // display drivers CAN link against these.
4673  //
4674 
4675  LinkNonWin32k = LinkNonWin32k |
4676  ((_strnicmp(ImportName, "win32k", sizeof("win32k") - 1)) &&
4677 
4678 #if defined(_AMD64_)
4679 
4680  (_strnicmp(ImportName, "ntoskrnl", sizeof("ntoskrnl") - 1)) &&
4681 
4682 #endif
4683 
4684  (_strnicmp(ImportName, "dxapi", sizeof("dxapi") - 1)) &&
4685  (_strnicmp(ImportName, "coverage", sizeof("coverage") - 1)) &&
4686  (_strnicmp(ImportName, "irt", sizeof("irt") - 1)));
4687 
4688 
4689  if (LinkNonWin32k && LinkWin32k) {
4690  MiDereferenceImports (ImportList);
4691  if (ImportList) {
4692  ExFreePool (ImportList);
4693  }
4694  return STATUS_PROCEDURE_NOT_FOUND;
4695  }
4696 
4697  if ((!_strnicmp(ImportName, "ntdll", sizeof("ntdll") - 1)) ||
4698  (!_strnicmp(ImportName, "winsrv", sizeof("winsrv") - 1)) ||
4699  (!_strnicmp(ImportName, "advapi32", sizeof("advapi32") - 1)) ||
4700  (!_strnicmp(ImportName, "kernel32", sizeof("kernel32") - 1)) ||
4701  (!_strnicmp(ImportName, "user32", sizeof("user32") - 1)) ||
4702  (!_strnicmp(ImportName, "gdi32", sizeof("gdi32") - 1)) ) {
4703 
4704  MiDereferenceImports (ImportList);
4705 
4706  if (ImportList) {
4707  ExFreePool (ImportList);
4708  }
4709  return STATUS_PROCEDURE_NOT_FOUND;
4710  }
4711 
4712  if ((!_strnicmp(ImportName, "ntoskrnl", sizeof("ntoskrnl") - 1)) ||
4713  (!_strnicmp(ImportName, "win32k", sizeof("win32k") - 1)) ||
4714  (!_strnicmp(ImportName, "hal", sizeof("hal") - 1))) {
4715 
4716  //
4717  // These imports don't get refcounted because we don't
4718  // ever want to unload them.
4719  //
4720 
4721  ReferenceImport = FALSE;
4722  }
4723  else {
4724  ReferenceImport = TRUE;
4725  }
4726 
4727  RtlInitAnsiString (&AnsiString, ImportName);
4728  st = RtlAnsiStringToUnicodeString (&ImportName_U, &AnsiString, TRUE);
4729 
4730  if (!NT_SUCCESS(st)) {
4731  MiDereferenceImports (ImportList);
4732  if (ImportList != NULL) {
4733  ExFreePool (ImportList);
4734  }
4735  return st;
4736  }
4737 
4738  if (NamePrefix &&
4739  (_strnicmp(ImportName, "ntoskrnl", sizeof("ntoskrnl") - 1) &&
4740  _strnicmp(ImportName, "hal", sizeof("hal") - 1))) {
4741 
4742  ImportDescriptorName_U.MaximumLength = (USHORT)(ImportName_U.Length + NamePrefix->Length);
4743  ImportDescriptorName_U.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
4744  ImportDescriptorName_U.MaximumLength,
4745  'TDmM');
4746  if (!ImportDescriptorName_U.Buffer) {
4747  RtlFreeUnicodeString (&ImportName_U);
4748  MiDereferenceImports (ImportList);
4749  if (ImportList != NULL) {
4750  ExFreePool (ImportList);
4751  }
4752  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4753  }
4754 
4755  ImportDescriptorName_U.Length = 0;
4756  RtlAppendUnicodeStringToString(&ImportDescriptorName_U, NamePrefix);
4757  RtlAppendUnicodeStringToString(&ImportDescriptorName_U, &ImportName_U);
4758  PrefixedNameAllocated = TRUE;
4759  }
4760  else {
4761  ImportDescriptorName_U = ImportName_U;
4762  PrefixedNameAllocated = FALSE;
4763  }
4764 
4765  Loaded = FALSE;
4766 
4767 ReCheck:
4768  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
4769  ImportBase = NULL;
4770 
4771  //
4772  // Initializing DataTableEntry is not needed for correctness
4773  // but without it the compiler cannot compile this code
4774  // W4 to check for use of uninitialized variables.
4775  //
4776 
4777  DataTableEntry = NULL;
4778 
4779  while (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
4780 
4781  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
4782  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
4783  InLoadOrderLinks);
4784 
4785  if (RtlEqualUnicodeString (&ImportDescriptorName_U,
4786  &DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
4787  TRUE)) {
4788 
4789  ImportBase = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
4790 
4791  //
4792  // Only bump the LoadCount if this thread did not initiate
4793  // the load below. If this thread initiated the load, then
4794  // the LoadCount has already been bumped as part of the
4795  // load - we only want to increment it here if we are
4796  // "attaching" to a previously loaded DLL.
4797  //
4798 
4799  if ((Loaded == FALSE) && (ReferenceImport == TRUE)) {
4800 
4801  //
4802  // Only increment the load count on the import if it is not
4803  // circular (ie: the import is not from the original
4804  // caller).
4805  //
4806 
4807  if ((DataTableEntry->Flags & LDRP_LOAD_IN_PROGRESS) == 0) {
4808  DataTableEntry->LoadCount += 1;
4809  }
4810  }
4811 
4812  break;
4813  }
4814  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
4815  }
4816 
4817  if (ImportBase == NULL) {
4818 
4819  //
4820  // The DLL name was not located, attempt to load this dll.
4821  //
4822 
4823  DllToLoad.MaximumLength = (USHORT)(ImportName_U.Length +
4824  ImageFileDirectory->Length +
4825  sizeof(WCHAR));
4826 
4827  DllToLoad.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
4828  DllToLoad.MaximumLength,
4829  'TDmM');
4830 
4831  if (DllToLoad.Buffer) {
4832  DllToLoad.Length = ImageFileDirectory->Length;
4833  RtlCopyMemory (DllToLoad.Buffer,
4834  ImageFileDirectory->Buffer,
4835  ImageFileDirectory->Length);
4836 
4837  RtlAppendStringToString ((PSTRING)&DllToLoad,
4838  (PSTRING)&ImportName_U);
4839 
4840  //
4841  // Add NULL termination in case the load fails so the name
4842  // can be returned as the PWSTR MissingDriverName.
4843  //
4844 
4845  DllToLoad.Buffer[(DllToLoad.MaximumLength - 1) / sizeof (WCHAR)] =
4846  UNICODE_NULL;
4847 
4848  st = MmLoadSystemImage (&DllToLoad,
4849  NamePrefix,
4850  NULL,
4851  FALSE,
4852  &Section,
4853  &BaseAddress);
4854 
4855  if (NT_SUCCESS(st)) {
4856 
4857  //
4858  // No need to keep the temporary name buffer around now
4859  // that there is a loaded module list entry for this DLL.
4860  //
4861 
4862  ExFreePool (DllToLoad.Buffer);
4863  }
4864  else {
4865 
4866  if ((st == STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND) &&
4867  (NamePrefix == NULL) &&
4868  (MI_IS_SESSION_ADDRESS (ImageBase))) {
4869 
4870 #define DRIVERS_SUBDIR_NAME L"drivers\\"
4871 
4872  DriverDirectory.Buffer = (const PUSHORT) DRIVERS_SUBDIR_NAME;
4873  DriverDirectory.Length = sizeof (DRIVERS_SUBDIR_NAME) - sizeof (WCHAR);
4874  DriverDirectory.MaximumLength = sizeof DRIVERS_SUBDIR_NAME;
4875 
4876  //
4877  // The DLL file was not located, attempt to load it
4878  // from the drivers subdirectory. This makes it
4879  // possible for drivers like win32k.sys to link to
4880  // drivers that reside in the drivers subdirectory
4881  // (like dxapi.sys).
4882  //
4883 
4884  DllToLoad2.MaximumLength = (USHORT)(ImportName_U.Length +
4885  DriverDirectory.Length +
4886  ImageFileDirectory->Length +
4887  sizeof(WCHAR));
4888 
4889  DllToLoad2.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
4890  DllToLoad2.MaximumLength,
4891  'TDmM');
4892 
4893  if (DllToLoad2.Buffer) {
4894  DllToLoad2.Length = ImageFileDirectory->Length;
4895  RtlCopyMemory (DllToLoad2.Buffer,
4896  ImageFileDirectory->Buffer,
4897  ImageFileDirectory->Length);
4898 
4899  RtlAppendStringToString ((PSTRING)&DllToLoad2,
4900  (PSTRING)&DriverDirectory);
4901 
4902  RtlAppendStringToString ((PSTRING)&DllToLoad2,
4903  (PSTRING)&ImportName_U);
4904 
4905  //
4906  // Add NULL termination in case the load fails
4907  // so the name can be returned as the PWSTR
4908  // MissingDriverName.
4909  //
4910 
4911  DllToLoad2.Buffer[(DllToLoad2.MaximumLength - 1) / sizeof (WCHAR)] =
4912  UNICODE_NULL;
4913 
4914  st = MmLoadSystemImage (&DllToLoad2,
4915  NULL,
4916  NULL,
4917  FALSE,
4918  &Section,
4919  &BaseAddress);
4920 
4921  ExFreePool (DllToLoad.Buffer);
4922 
4923  DllToLoad.Buffer = DllToLoad2.Buffer;
4924  DllToLoad.Length = DllToLoad2.Length;
4925  DllToLoad.MaximumLength = DllToLoad2.MaximumLength;
4926 
4927  if (NT_SUCCESS(st)) {
4928  ExFreePool (DllToLoad.Buffer);
4929  goto LoadFinished;
4930  }
4931  }
4932  else {
4933  Section = NULL;
4934  BaseAddress = NULL;
4935  st = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4936  goto LoadFinished;
4937  }
4938  }
4939 
4940  //
4941  // Return the temporary name buffer to our caller so
4942  // the name of the DLL that failed to load can be displayed.
4943  // Set the low bit of the pointer so our caller knows to
4944  // free this buffer when he's done displaying it (as opposed
4945  // to loaded module list entries which should not be freed).
4946  //
4947 
4948  *MissingDriverName = DllToLoad.Buffer;
4949  *(PULONG)MissingDriverName |= 0x1;
4950 
4951  //
4952  // Set this to NULL so the hard error prints properly.
4953  //
4954 
4955  *MissingProcedureName = NULL;
4956  }
4957  }
4958  else {
4959 
4960  //
4961  // Initializing Section and BaseAddress is not needed for
4962  // correctness but without it the compiler cannot compile
4963  // this code W4 to check for use of uninitialized variables.
4964  //
4965 
4966  Section = NULL;
4967  BaseAddress = NULL;
4968  st = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4969  }
4970 
4971 LoadFinished:
4972 
4973  //
4974  // Call any needed DLL initialization now.
4975  //
4976 
4977  if (NT_SUCCESS(st)) {
4978 #if DBG
4979  PLIST_ENTRY Entry;
4980 #endif
4981  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY TableEntry;
4982 
4983  Loaded = TRUE;
4984 
4985  TableEntry = (PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY) Section;
4986  ASSERT (BaseAddress == TableEntry->DllBase);
4987 
4988 #if DBG
4989  //
4990  // Lookup the dll's table entry in the loaded module list.
4991  // This is expected to always succeed.
4992  //
4993 
4994  Entry = PsLoadedModuleList.Blink;
4995  while (Entry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
4996  TableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (Entry,
4997  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
4998  InLoadOrderLinks);
4999 
5000  if (BaseAddress == TableEntry->DllBase) {
5001  ASSERT (TableEntry == (PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY) Section);
5002  break;
5003  }
5004  ASSERT (TableEntry != (PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY) Section);
5005  Entry = Entry->Blink;
5006  }
5007 
5008  ASSERT (Entry != &PsLoadedModuleList);
5009 #endif
5010 
5011  //
5012  // Call the dll's initialization routine if it has
5013  // one. This routine will reapply verifier thunks to
5014  // any modules that link to this one if necessary.
5015  //
5016 
5017  st = MmCallDllInitialize (TableEntry, &PsLoadedModuleList);
5018 
5019  //
5020  // If the module could not be properly initialized,
5021  // unload it.
5022  //
5023 
5024  if (!NT_SUCCESS(st)) {
5025  MmUnloadSystemImage ((PVOID)TableEntry);
5026  Loaded = FALSE;
5027  }
5028  }
5029 
5030  if (!NT_SUCCESS(st)) {
5031 
5032  RtlFreeUnicodeString (&ImportName_U);
5033  if (PrefixedNameAllocated == TRUE) {
5034  ExFreePool (ImportDescriptorName_U.Buffer);
5035  }
5036  MiDereferenceImports (ImportList);
5037  if (ImportList != NULL) {
5038  ExFreePool (ImportList);
5039  }
5040  return st;
5041  }
5042 
5043  goto ReCheck;
5044  }
5045 
5046  if ((ReferenceImport == TRUE) && (ImportList)) {
5047 
5048  //
5049  // Only add the image providing satisfying our imports to the
5050  // import list if the reference is not circular (ie: the import
5051  // is not from the original caller).
5052  //
5053 
5054  if ((DataTableEntry->Flags & LDRP_LOAD_IN_PROGRESS) == 0) {
5055  ImportList->Entry[Count] = DataTableEntry;
5056  Count += 1;
5057  }
5058  }
5059 
5060  RtlFreeUnicodeString (&ImportName_U);
5061  if (PrefixedNameAllocated) {
5062  ExFreePool (ImportDescriptorName_U.Buffer);
5063  }
5064 
5065  *MissingDriverName = DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.Buffer;
5066 
5067  ExportDirectory = (PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY) RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (
5068  ImportBase,
5069  TRUE,
5070  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT,
5071  &ExportSize);
5072 
5073  if (!ExportDirectory) {
5074  MiDereferenceImports (ImportList);
5075  if (ImportList) {
5076  ExFreePool (ImportList);
5077  }
5078  return STATUS_DRIVER_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND;
5079  }
5080 
5081  //
5082  // Walk through the IAT and snap all the thunks.
5083  //
5084 
5085  if (ImportDescriptor->OriginalFirstThunk) {
5086 
5087  NameThunk = (PIMAGE_THUNK_DATA)((PCHAR)ImageBase + (ULONG)ImportDescriptor->OriginalFirstThunk);
5088  AddrThunk = (PIMAGE_THUNK_DATA)((PCHAR)ImageBase + (ULONG)ImportDescriptor->FirstThunk);
5089 
5090  while (NameThunk->u1.AddressOfData) {
5091 
5092  st = MiSnapThunk (ImportBase,
5093  ImageBase,
5094  NameThunk++,
5095  AddrThunk++,
5096  ExportDirectory,
5097  ExportSize,
5098  FALSE,
5099  MissingProcedureName);
5100 
5101  if (!NT_SUCCESS(st) ) {
5102  MiDereferenceImports (ImportList);
5103  if (ImportList) {
5104  ExFreePool (ImportList);
5105  }
5106  return st;
5107  }
5108  *MissingProcedureName = MissingProcedureStorageArea;
5109  }
5110  }
5111 
5112  ImportDescriptor += 1;
5113  }
5114 
5115  //
5116  // All the imports are successfully loaded so establish and compact
5117  // the import unload list.
5118  //
5119 
5120  if (ImportList) {
5121 
5122  //
5123  // Blank entries occur for things like the kernel, HAL & win32k.sys
5124  // that we never want to unload. Especially for things like
5125  // win32k.sys where the reference count can really hit 0.
5126  //
5127 
5128  //
5129  // Initializing SingleEntry is not needed for correctness
5130  // but without it the compiler cannot compile this code
5131  // W4 to check for use of uninitialized variables.
5132  //
5133 
5134  SingleEntry = NULL;
5135 
5136  Count = 0;
5137  for (i = 0; i < ImportList->Count; i += 1) {
5138  if (ImportList->Entry[i]) {
5139  SingleEntry = POINTER_TO_SINGLE_ENTRY(ImportList->Entry[i]);
5140  Count += 1;
5141  }
5142  }
5143 
5144  if (Count == 0) {
5145 
5146  ExFreePool(ImportList);
5147  ImportList = NO_IMPORTS_USED;
5148  }
5149  else if (Count == 1) {
5150  ExFreePool(ImportList);
5151  ImportList = (PLOAD_IMPORTS)SingleEntry;
5152  }
5153  else if (Count != ImportList->Count) {
5154 
5155  ImportListSize = Count * sizeof(PVOID) + sizeof(SIZE_T);
5156 
5157  CompactedImportList = (PLOAD_IMPORTS)
5158  ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool | POOL_COLD_ALLOCATION,
5159  ImportListSize,
5160  'TDmM');
5161  if (CompactedImportList) {
5162  CompactedImportList->Count = Count;
5163 
5164  Count = 0;
5165  for (i = 0; i < ImportList->Count; i += 1) {
5166  if (ImportList->Entry[i]) {
5167  CompactedImportList->Entry[Count] = ImportList->Entry[i];
5168  Count += 1;
5169  }
5170  }
5171 
5172  ExFreePool(ImportList);
5173  ImportList = CompactedImportList;
5174  }
5175  }
5176 
5177  *LoadedImports = ImportList;
5178  }
5179  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
5180 }
5181 
5182 
5183 NTSTATUS
5184 MiSnapThunk(
5185  IN PVOID DllBase,
5186  IN PVOID ImageBase,
5187  IN PIMAGE_THUNK_DATA NameThunk,
5188  OUT PIMAGE_THUNK_DATA AddrThunk,
5189  IN PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY ExportDirectory,
5190  IN ULONG ExportSize,
5191  IN LOGICAL SnapForwarder,
5192  OUT PCHAR *MissingProcedureName
5193  )
5194 
5195 /*++
5196 
5197 Routine Description:
5198 
5199  This function snaps a thunk using the specified Export Section data.
5200  If the section data does not support the thunk, then the thunk is
5201  partially snapped (Dll field is still non-null, but snap address is
5202  set).
5203 
5204 Arguments:
5205 
5206  DllBase - Base of DLL being snapped to.
5207 
5208  ImageBase - Base of image that contains the thunks to snap.
5209 
5210  Thunk - On input, supplies the thunk to snap. When successfully
5211  snapped, the function field is set to point to the address in
5212  the DLL, and the DLL field is set to NULL.
5213 
5214  ExportDirectory - Supplies the Export Section data from a DLL.
5215 
5216  SnapForwarder - Supplies TRUE if the snap is for a forwarder, and therefore
5217  Address of Data is already setup.
5218 
5219 Return Value:
5220 
5221  STATUS_SUCCESS or STATUS_DRIVER_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND or
5222  STATUS_DRIVER_ORDINAL_NOT_FOUND
5223 
5224 --*/
5225 
5226 {
5227  BOOLEAN Ordinal;
5228  USHORT OrdinalNumber;
5229  PULONG NameTableBase;
5230  PUSHORT NameOrdinalTableBase;
5231  PULONG Addr;
5232  USHORT HintIndex;
5233  LONG High;
5234  LONG Low;
5235  LONG Middle;
5236  LONG Result;
5237  NTSTATUS Status;
5238  PCHAR MissingProcedureName2;
5239  CHAR NameBuffer[ MAXIMUM_FILENAME_LENGTH ];
5240 
5241  PAGED_CODE();
5242 
5243  //
5244  // Determine if snap is by name, or by ordinal
5245  //
5246 
5247  Ordinal = (BOOLEAN)IMAGE_SNAP_BY_ORDINAL(NameThunk->u1.Ordinal);
5248 
5249  if (Ordinal && !SnapForwarder) {
5250 
5251  OrdinalNumber = (USHORT)(IMAGE_ORDINAL(NameThunk->u1.Ordinal) -
5252  ExportDirectory->Base);
5253 
5254  *MissingProcedureName = (PCHAR)(ULONG_PTR)OrdinalNumber;
5255 
5256  }
5257  else {
5258 
5259  //
5260  // Change AddressOfData from an RVA to a VA.
5261  //
5262 
5263  if (!SnapForwarder) {
5264  NameThunk->u1.AddressOfData = (ULONG_PTR)ImageBase + NameThunk->u1.AddressOfData;
5265  }
5266 
5267  strncpy (*MissingProcedureName,
5268  (const PCHAR)&((PIMAGE_IMPORT_BY_NAME)NameThunk->u1.AddressOfData)->Name[0],
5269  MAXIMUM_FILENAME_LENGTH - 1);
5270 
5271  //
5272  // Lookup Name in NameTable
5273  //
5274 
5275  NameTableBase = (PULONG)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfNames);
5276  NameOrdinalTableBase = (PUSHORT)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfNameOrdinals);
5277 
5278  //
5279  // Before dropping into binary search, see if
5280  // the hint index results in a successful
5281  // match. If the hint index is zero, then
5282  // drop into binary search.
5283  //
5284 
5285  HintIndex = ((PIMAGE_IMPORT_BY_NAME)NameThunk->u1.AddressOfData)->Hint;
5286  if ((ULONG)HintIndex < ExportDirectory->NumberOfNames &&
5287  !strcmp((PSZ)((PIMAGE_IMPORT_BY_NAME)NameThunk->u1.AddressOfData)->Name,
5288  (PSZ)((PCHAR)DllBase + NameTableBase[HintIndex]))) {
5289  OrdinalNumber = NameOrdinalTableBase[HintIndex];
5290 
5291  }
5292  else {
5293 
5294  //
5295  // Lookup the import name in the name table using a binary search.
5296  //
5297 
5298  Low = 0;
5299  Middle = 0;
5300  High = ExportDirectory->NumberOfNames - 1;
5301 
5302  while (High >= Low) {
5303 
5304  //
5305  // Compute the next probe index and compare the import name
5306  // with the export name entry.
5307  //
5308 
5309  Middle = (Low + High) >> 1;
5310  Result = strcmp((const PCHAR)&((PIMAGE_IMPORT_BY_NAME)NameThunk->u1.AddressOfData)->Name[0],
5311  (PCHAR)((PCHAR)DllBase + NameTableBase[Middle]));
5312 
5313  if (Result < 0) {
5314  High = Middle - 1;
5315  }
5316  else if (Result > 0) {
5317  Low = Middle + 1;
5318  }
5319  else {
5320  break;
5321  }
5322  }
5323 
5324  //
5325  // If the high index is less than the low index, then a matching
5326  // table entry was not found. Otherwise, get the ordinal number
5327  // from the ordinal table.
5328  //
5329 
5330  if (High < Low) {
5331  return STATUS_DRIVER_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND;
5332  }
5333  else {
5334  OrdinalNumber = NameOrdinalTableBase[Middle];
5335  }
5336  }
5337  }
5338 
5339  //
5340  // If OrdinalNumber is not within the Export Address Table,
5341  // then DLL does not implement function. Snap to LDRP_BAD_DLL.
5342  //
5343 
5344  if ((ULONG)OrdinalNumber >= ExportDirectory->NumberOfFunctions) {
5345  Status = STATUS_DRIVER_ORDINAL_NOT_FOUND;
5346 
5347  }
5348  else {
5349 
5350  MissingProcedureName2 = NameBuffer;
5351 
5352  Addr = (PULONG)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfFunctions);
5353  *(PULONG_PTR)&AddrThunk->u1.Function = (ULONG_PTR)DllBase + Addr[OrdinalNumber];
5354 
5355  // AddrThunk s/b used from here on.
5356 
5357  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
5358 
5359  if (((ULONG_PTR)AddrThunk->u1.Function > (ULONG_PTR)ExportDirectory) &&
5360  ((ULONG_PTR)AddrThunk->u1.Function < ((ULONG_PTR)ExportDirectory + ExportSize)) ) {
5361 
5362  UNICODE_STRING UnicodeString;
5363  ANSI_STRING ForwardDllName;
5364 
5365  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
5366  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
5367  ULONG LocalExportSize;
5368  PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY LocalExportDirectory;
5369 
5370  Status = STATUS_DRIVER_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND;
5371 
5372  //
5373  // Include the dot in the length so we can do prefix later on.
5374  //
5375 
5376  ForwardDllName.Buffer = (PCHAR)AddrThunk->u1.Function;
5377  ForwardDllName.Length = (USHORT)(strchr(ForwardDllName.Buffer, '.') -
5378  ForwardDllName.Buffer + 1);
5379  ForwardDllName.MaximumLength = ForwardDllName.Length;
5380 
5381  if (NT_SUCCESS(RtlAnsiStringToUnicodeString(&UnicodeString,
5382  &ForwardDllName,
5383  TRUE))) {
5384 
5385  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
5386 
5387  while (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
5388 
5389  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
5390  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
5391  InLoadOrderLinks);
5392 
5393  //
5394  // We have to do a case INSENSITIVE comparison for
5395  // forwarder because the linker just took what is in the
5396  // def file, as opposed to looking in the exporting
5397  // image for the name.
5398  // we also use the prefix function to ignore the .exe or
5399  // .sys or .dll at the end.
5400  //
5401 
5402  if (RtlPrefixString((PSTRING)&UnicodeString,
5403  (PSTRING)&DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
5404  TRUE)) {
5405 
5406  LocalExportDirectory = (PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY)
5407  RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (DataTableEntry->DllBase,
5408  TRUE,
5409  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT,
5410  &LocalExportSize);
5411 
5412  if (LocalExportDirectory != NULL) {
5413 
5414  IMAGE_THUNK_DATA thunkData;
5415  PIMAGE_IMPORT_BY_NAME addressOfData;
5416  SIZE_T length;
5417 
5418  //
5419  // One extra byte for NULL termination.
5420  //
5421 
5422  length = strlen(ForwardDllName.Buffer +
5423  ForwardDllName.Length) + 1;
5424 
5425  addressOfData = (PIMAGE_IMPORT_BY_NAME)
5426  ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool,
5427  length +
5428  sizeof(IMAGE_IMPORT_BY_NAME),
5429  ' mM');
5430 
5431  if (addressOfData) {
5432 
5433  RtlCopyMemory(&(addressOfData->Name[0]),
5434  ForwardDllName.Buffer +
5435  ForwardDllName.Length,
5436  length);
5437 
5438  addressOfData->Hint = 0;
5439 
5440  *(PULONG_PTR)&thunkData.u1.AddressOfData =
5441  (ULONG_PTR)addressOfData;
5442 
5443  Status = MiSnapThunk (DataTableEntry->DllBase,
5444  ImageBase,
5445  &thunkData,
5446  &thunkData,
5447  LocalExportDirectory,
5448  LocalExportSize,
5449  TRUE,
5450  &MissingProcedureName2);
5451 
5452  ExFreePool (addressOfData);
5453 
5454  AddrThunk->u1 = thunkData.u1;
5455  }
5456  }
5457 
5458  break;
5459  }
5460 
5461  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
5462  }
5463 
5464  RtlFreeUnicodeString (&UnicodeString);
5465  }
5466 
5467  }
5468 
5469  }
5470  return Status;
5471 }
5472 
5473 NTSTATUS
5474 MmCheckSystemImage (
5475  IN HANDLE ImageFileHandle,
5476  IN LOGICAL PurgeSection
5477  )
5478 
5479 /*++
5480 
5481 Routine Description:
5482 
5483  This function ensures the checksum for a system image is correct
5484  and matches the data in the image.
5485 
5486 Arguments:
5487 
5488  ImageFileHandle - Supplies the file handle of the image. This is a kernel
5489  handle (ie: cannot be tampered with by the user).
5490 
5491  PurgeSection - Supplies TRUE if the data section mapping the image should
5492  be purged prior to returning. Note that the first page
5493  could be used to speed up subsequent image section creation,
5494  but generally the cost of useless data pages sitting in
5495  transition is costly. Better to put the pages immediately
5496  on the free list to preserve the transition cache for more
5497  useful pages.
5498 
5499 Return Value:
5500 
5501  Status value.
5502 
5503 --*/
5504 
5505 {
5506  NTSTATUS Status;
5507  NTSTATUS Status2;
5508  HANDLE Section;
5509  PVOID ViewBase;
5510  SIZE_T ViewSize;
5511  IO_STATUS_BLOCK IoStatusBlock;
5512  PIMAGE_FILE_HEADER FileHeader;
5513  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders;
5514  FILE_STANDARD_INFORMATION StandardInfo;
5515  PSECTION SectionPointer;
5516  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES ObjectAttributes;
5517  KAPC_STATE ApcState;
5518  ULONG SectionType;
5519  SIZE_T NumberOfBytes;
5520 
5521  PAGED_CODE();
5522 
5523  SectionType = SEC_IMAGE;
5524 
5525 retry:
5526 
5527  InitializeObjectAttributes (&ObjectAttributes,
5528  NULL,
5529  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE),
5530  NULL,
5531  NULL);
5532 
5533  Status = ZwCreateSection (&Section,
5534  SECTION_MAP_EXECUTE,
5535  &ObjectAttributes,
5536  NULL,
5537  PAGE_EXECUTE,
5538  SectionType,
5539  ImageFileHandle);
5540 
5541  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
5542  return Status;
5543  }
5544 
5545  ViewBase = NULL;
5546  ViewSize = 0;
5547 
5548  //
5549  // Since callees are not always in the context of the system process,
5550  // attach here when necessary to guarantee the driver load occurs in a
5551  // known safe address space to prevent security holes.
5552  //
5553 
5554  KeStackAttachProcess (&PsInitialSystemProcess->Pcb, &ApcState);
5555 
5556  Status = ZwMapViewOfSection (Section,
5557  NtCurrentProcess (),
5558  (PVOID *)&ViewBase,
5559  0L,
5560  0L,
5561  NULL,
5562  &ViewSize,
5563  ViewShare,
5564  0L,
5565  PAGE_EXECUTE);
5566 
5567  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
5568  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
5569  ZwClose (Section);
5570  return Status;
5571  }
5572 
5573  //
5574  // Now the image is mapped as a data file... Calculate its size and then
5575  // check its checksum.
5576  //
5577 
5578  Status = ZwQueryInformationFile (ImageFileHandle,
5579  &IoStatusBlock,
5580  &StandardInfo,
5581  sizeof(StandardInfo),
5582  FileStandardInformation);
5583 
5584  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
5585 
5586  if (SectionType == SEC_IMAGE) {
5587  NumberOfBytes = ViewSize;
5588  }
5589  else {
5590  NumberOfBytes = StandardInfo.EndOfFile.LowPart;
5591  }
5592 
5593  try {
5594 
5595  if (!LdrVerifyMappedImageMatchesChecksum (
5596  ViewBase,
5597  NumberOfBytes,
5598  StandardInfo.EndOfFile.LowPart)) {
5599 
5600  Status = STATUS_IMAGE_CHECKSUM_MISMATCH;
5601  goto out;
5602  }
5603 
5604  NtHeaders = RtlImageNtHeader (ViewBase);
5605 
5606  if (NtHeaders == NULL) {
5607  Status = STATUS_IMAGE_CHECKSUM_MISMATCH;
5608  goto out;
5609  }
5610 
5611  FileHeader = &NtHeaders->FileHeader;
5612 
5613  //
5614  // Detect configurations inadvertently trying to load 32-bit
5615  // drivers on NT64 or mismatched platform architectures, etc.
5616  //
5617 
5618  if ((FileHeader->Machine != IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_NATIVE) ||
5619  (NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.Magic != IMAGE_NT_OPTIONAL_HDR_MAGIC)) {
5620  Status = STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_PROTECT;
5621  goto out;
5622  }
5623 
5624 #if !defined(NT_UP)
5625  if (!MmVerifyImageIsOkForMpUse (ViewBase)) {
5626  Status = STATUS_IMAGE_MP_UP_MISMATCH;
5627  goto out;
5628  }
5629 #endif
5630  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
5631  Status = STATUS_IMAGE_CHECKSUM_MISMATCH;
5632  }
5633  }
5634 
5635 out:
5636 
5637  ZwUnmapViewOfSection (NtCurrentProcess (), ViewBase);
5638 
5639  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
5640 
5641  if ((Status == STATUS_IMAGE_CHECKSUM_MISMATCH) &&
5642  (SectionType == SEC_IMAGE)) {
5643 
5644  //
5645  // We speculatively tried to verify the checksum using the image
5646  // mapping but this did not match. This can occur if the image has
5647  // a self-signed certificate appended to it (this is a rare occurrence)
5648  // as the certificate data will be present in the data file but is
5649  // not mapped when the file is used as an image. So fall back to
5650  // mapping the file as data and recompute.
5651  //
5652  // Note there are other cases above that can get us to this check but
5653  // it's always ok to retry as data ...
5654  //
5655 
5656  ZwClose (Section);
5657  SectionType = SEC_COMMIT;
5658  goto retry;
5659  }
5660 
5661  if ((PurgeSection == TRUE) && (SectionType == SEC_COMMIT)) {
5662 
5663  Status2 = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (Section,
5664  SECTION_MAP_EXECUTE,
5665  MmSectionObjectType,
5666  KernelMode,
5667  (PVOID *) &SectionPointer,
5668  (POBJECT_HANDLE_INFORMATION) NULL);
5669 
5670  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status2)) {
5671 
5672  MmPurgeSection (SectionPointer->Segment->ControlArea->FilePointer->SectionObjectPointer,
5673  NULL,
5674  0,
5675  FALSE);
5676  ObDereferenceObject (SectionPointer);
5677  }
5678  }
5679 
5680  ZwClose (Section);
5681  return Status;
5682 }
5683 
5684 #if !defined(NT_UP)
5685 BOOLEAN
5686 MmVerifyImageIsOkForMpUse (
5687  IN PVOID BaseAddress
5688  )
5689 {
5690  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders;
5691 
5692  PAGED_CODE();
5693 
5694  NtHeaders = RtlImageNtHeader (BaseAddress);
5695 
5696  if ((NtHeaders != NULL) &&
5697  (KeNumberProcessors > 1) &&
5698  (NtHeaders->FileHeader.Characteristics & IMAGE_FILE_UP_SYSTEM_ONLY)) {
5699 
5700  return FALSE;
5701  }
5702 
5703  return TRUE;
5704 }
5705 #endif
5706 
5707 
5708 PFN_NUMBER
5709 MiDeleteSystemPageableVm (
5710  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
5711  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPtes,
5712  IN ULONG Flags,
5713  OUT PPFN_NUMBER ResidentPages OPTIONAL
5714  )
5715 
5716 /*++
5717 
5718 Routine Description:
5719 
5720  This function deletes pageable system address space (paged pool
5721  or driver pageable sections).
5722 
5723 Arguments:
5724 
5725  PointerPte - Supplies the start of the PTE range to delete.
5726 
5727  NumberOfPtes - Supplies the number of PTEs in the range.
5728 
5729  Flags - Supplies flags indicating what the caller desires.
5730 
5731  ResidentPages - If not NULL, the number of resident pages freed is
5732  returned here.
5733 
5734 Return Value:
5735 
5736  Returns the number of pages actually freed.
5737 
5738 --*/
5739 
5740 {
5741  ULONG TimeStamp;
5742  PMMSUPPORT Ws;
5743  PVOID VirtualAddress;
5744  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
5745  MMPTE PteContents;
5746  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5747  PMMPFN Pfn2;
5748  PFN_NUMBER ValidPages;
5749  PFN_NUMBER PagesRequired;
5750  WSLE_NUMBER WsIndex;
5751  KIRQL OldIrql;
5752  ULONG FlushCount;
5753  PVOID VaFlushList[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
5754  MMWSLENTRY Locked;
5755  PFN_NUMBER PageTableFrameIndex;
5756  LOGICAL WsHeld;
5757  PETHREAD Thread;
5758 
5759  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() <= APC_LEVEL);
5760 
5761  ValidPages = 0;
5762  PagesRequired = 0;
5763  FlushCount = 0;
5764  WsHeld = FALSE;
5765 
5766  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
5767 
5768  if (MI_IS_SESSION_PTE (PointerPte)) {
5769  Ws = &MmSessionSpace->GlobalVirtualAddress->Vm;
5770  }
5771  else {
5772  Ws = &MmSystemCacheWs;
5773  }
5774 
5775 #if defined(_X86PAE_)
5776 
5777  //
5778  // PAE PTEs are written in 2 separate writes so the working set pushlock
5779  // must always be held even to examine PTEs in prototype format - because
5780  // a trim could be happening in parallel (writing the low half and then
5781  // the upper half which would cause otherwise cause us to read the
5782  // PTE contents split in the middle).
5783  //
5784 
5785  WsHeld = TRUE;
5786  LOCK_WORKING_SET (Thread, Ws);
5787 
5788 #endif
5789 
5790  while (NumberOfPtes != 0) {
5791  PteContents = *PointerPte;
5792 
5793  if (PteContents.u.Long != 0) {
5794 
5795  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
5796 
5797  //
5798  // Once the working set mutex is acquired, it is deliberately
5799  // held until all the pages have been freed. This is because
5800  // when paged pool is running low on large servers, we need the
5801  // segment dereference thread to be able to free large amounts
5802  // quickly. Typically this thread will free 64k chunks and we
5803  // don't want to have to contend for the mutex 16 times to do
5804  // this as there may be thousands of other threads also trying
5805  // for it.
5806  //
5807 
5808  if (WsHeld == FALSE) {
5809  WsHeld = TRUE;
5810  LOCK_WORKING_SET (Thread, Ws);
5811  }
5812 
5813  PteContents = *PointerPte;
5814  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5815  continue;
5816  }
5817 
5818  //
5819  // Delete the page.
5820  //
5821 
5822  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PteContents);
5823 
5824  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
5825 
5826  //
5827  // Check to see if this is a pageable page in which
5828  // case it needs to be removed from the working set list.
5829  //
5830 
5831  WsIndex = Pfn1->u1.WsIndex;
5832  if (WsIndex == 0) {
5833  ValidPages += 1;
5834  if (Ws != &MmSystemCacheWs) {
5835  MM_BUMP_SESS_COUNTER (MM_DBG_SESSION_NP_DELVA, 1);
5836  InterlockedDecrementSizeT (&MmSessionSpace->NonPageablePages);
5837  }
5838  }
5839  else {
5840  if (Ws == &MmSystemCacheWs) {
5841  MiRemoveWsle (WsIndex, MmSystemCacheWorkingSetList);
5842  MiReleaseWsle (WsIndex, &MmSystemCacheWs);
5843  }
5844  else {
5845  VirtualAddress = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
5846  WsIndex = MiLocateWsle (VirtualAddress,
5847  MmSessionSpace->Vm.VmWorkingSetList,
5848  WsIndex,
5849  TRUE);
5850 
5851  ASSERT (WsIndex != WSLE_NULL_INDEX);
5852 
5853  //
5854  // Check to see if this entry is locked in
5855  // the working set or locked in memory.
5856  //
5857 
5858  Locked = MmSessionSpace->Wsle[WsIndex].u1.e1;
5859 
5860  MiRemoveWsle (WsIndex, MmSessionSpace->Vm.VmWorkingSetList);
5861 
5862  MiReleaseWsle (WsIndex, &MmSessionSpace->Vm);
5863 
5864  if (Locked.LockedInWs == 1 || Locked.LockedInMemory == 1) {
5865 
5866  //
5867  // This entry is locked.
5868  //
5869 
5870  MM_BUMP_SESS_COUNTER (MM_DBG_SESSION_NP_DELVA, 1);
5871  InterlockedDecrementSizeT (&MmSessionSpace->NonPageablePages);
5872  ValidPages += 1;
5873 
5874  ASSERT (WsIndex < MmSessionSpace->Vm.VmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic);
5875  MmSessionSpace->Vm.VmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic -= 1;
5876 
5877  if (WsIndex != MmSessionSpace->Vm.VmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic) {
5878  WSLE_NUMBER Entry;
5879  PVOID SwapVa;
5880 
5881  Entry = MmSessionSpace->Vm.VmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic;
5882  ASSERT (MmSessionSpace->Wsle[Entry].u1.e1.Valid);
5883  SwapVa = MmSessionSpace->Wsle[Entry].u1.VirtualAddress;
5884  SwapVa = PAGE_ALIGN (SwapVa);
5885 
5886  MiSwapWslEntries (Entry,
5887  WsIndex,
5888  &MmSessionSpace->Vm,
5889  FALSE);
5890  }
5891  }
5892  else {
5893  ASSERT (WsIndex >= MmSessionSpace->Vm.VmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic);
5894  }
5895  }
5896  }
5897 
5898  //
5899  // Check if this is a prototype PTE.
5900  //
5901 
5902  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte == 1) {
5903 
5904  PMMPTE PointerPde;
5905 
5906  ASSERT (Ws != &MmSystemCacheWs);
5907 
5908  //
5909  // Capture the state of the modified bit for this PTE.
5910  //
5911 
5912  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
5913 
5914  if (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5915 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5916  if (!NT_SUCCESS (MiCheckPdeForPagedPool (PointerPte))) {
5917 #endif
5918  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
5919  0x61940,
5920  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte,
5921  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPde->u.Long,
5922  (ULONG_PTR)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPte));
5923 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5924  }
5925 #endif
5926  }
5927 
5928  PageTableFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde);
5929  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTableFrameIndex);
5930 
5931  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5932 
5933  MI_CAPTURE_DIRTY_BIT_TO_PFN (PointerPte, Pfn1);
5934  }
5935  else {
5936  PageTableFrameIndex = Pfn1->u4.PteFrame;
5937  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTableFrameIndex);
5938 
5939  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5940 
5941  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
5942  }
5943 
5944  //
5945  // Decrement the share count for the containing page table page.
5946  //
5947 
5948  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn2, PageTableFrameIndex);
5949 
5950  //
5951  // Decrement the share count for the physical page.
5952  //
5953 
5954  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
5955 
5956  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5957 
5958  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
5959 
5960  if (Flags & MI_DELETE_FLUSH_TB) {
5961 
5962  //
5963  // Flush the TB for this virtual address.
5964  //
5965 
5966  if (FlushCount != MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
5967 
5968  VaFlushList[FlushCount] =
5969  MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
5970  FlushCount += 1;
5971  }
5972  }
5973  else {
5974 
5975  //
5976  // Our caller will lazy flush this entry so stamp the time
5977  // for him. Since zero is used by our caller as an
5978  // indicator no flush is needed, ensure that if the
5979  // inserted field (which may be truncated) is zero, that
5980  // a flush of this address is done before we return.
5981  //
5982 
5983  TimeStamp = KeReadTbFlushTimeStamp ();
5984 
5985  PointerPte->u.Soft.PageFileHigh = TimeStamp;
5986 
5987  if (PointerPte->u.Soft.PageFileHigh == 0) {
5988 
5989  if (FlushCount != MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
5990 
5991  VaFlushList[FlushCount] =
5992  MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
5993  FlushCount += 1;
5994  }
5995  }
5996  }
5997  }
5998  else if (PteContents.u.Soft.Prototype) {
5999 
6000  ASSERT (Ws != &MmSystemCacheWs);
6001 
6002  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
6003  }
6004  else if (PteContents.u.Soft.Transition == 1) {
6005 
6006  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6007 
6008  PteContents = *PointerPte;
6009 
6010  if (PteContents.u.Soft.Transition == 0) {
6011  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6012  continue;
6013  }
6014 
6015  //
6016  // Transition, release page.
6017  //
6018 
6019  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_TRANSITION_PTE (&PteContents);
6020 
6021  //
6022  // Set the pointer to PTE as empty so the page
6023  // is deleted when the reference count goes to zero.
6024  //
6025 
6026  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
6027 
6028  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
6029 
6030  PageTableFrameIndex = Pfn1->u4.PteFrame;
6031  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTableFrameIndex);
6032  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn2, PageTableFrameIndex);
6033 
6034  //
6035  // Check the reference count for the page, if the reference
6036  // count is zero, move the page to the free list, if the
6037  // reference count is not zero, ignore this page. When the
6038  // reference count goes to zero, it will be placed on the
6039  // free list.
6040  //
6041 
6042  if (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) {
6043  MiUnlinkPageFromList (Pfn1);
6044  MiReleasePageFileSpace (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
6045  MiInsertPageInFreeList (PageFrameIndex);
6046  }
6047 
6048  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
6049  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6050  }
6051  else {
6052 
6053  //
6054  // Demand zero, release page file space.
6055  //
6056  if (PteContents.u.Soft.PageFileHigh != 0) {
6057  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6058  MiReleasePageFileSpace (PteContents);
6059  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6060  }
6061 
6062  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
6063  }
6064 
6065  PagesRequired += 1;
6066  }
6067 
6068  NumberOfPtes -= 1;
6069  PointerPte += 1;
6070  }
6071 
6072  if (WsHeld == TRUE) {
6073  UNLOCK_WORKING_SET (Thread, Ws);
6074  }
6075 
6076  //
6077  // Some callers flush the TB themselves, but for the rest we must flush
6078  // here.
6079  //
6080 
6081  if (FlushCount == 0) {
6082  NOTHING;
6083  }
6084  else if (FlushCount == 1) {
