6085  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
6086  }
6087  else if (FlushCount < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
6088  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (FlushCount, &VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
6089  }
6090  else {
6091  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x16);
6092  }
6093 
6094  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (ResidentPages)) {
6095  *ResidentPages = ValidPages;
6096  }
6097 
6098  return PagesRequired;
6099 }
6100 
6101 VOID
6102 MiMarkSectionWritable (
6103  IN PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER SectionTableEntry
6104  )
6105 
6106 /*++
6107 
6108 Routine Description:
6109 
6110  This function is a nonpaged helper routine that updates the characteristics
6111  field of the argument section table entry and marks the page dirty so
6112  that subsequent session loads share the same copy.
6113 
6114 Arguments:
6115 
6116  SectionTableEntry - Supplies the relevant section table entry.
6117 
6118 Return Value:
6119 
6120  None.
6121 
6122 --*/
6123 
6124 {
6125  PEPROCESS Process;
6126  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6127  ULONG FreeBit;
6128  PMMPFN Pfn1;
6129  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
6130  KIRQL OldIrql;
6131  PULONG Characteristics;
6132 
6133  //
6134  // Modify the PE header through hyperspace and mark the header page
6135  // dirty so subsequent sections pick up the same copy.
6136  //
6137  // Note this makes the entire .rdata (.sdata on IA64) writable
6138  // instead of just the import tables.
6139  //
6140 
6141  Process = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
6142 
6143  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (&SectionTableEntry->Characteristics);
6144  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6145 
6146  MiMakeSystemAddressValidPfn (&SectionTableEntry->Characteristics, OldIrql);
6147  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6148 
6149  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
6150 
6151  Characteristics = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (Process, PageFrameIndex);
6152  Characteristics = (PULONG)((PCHAR)Characteristics + MiGetByteOffset (&SectionTableEntry->Characteristics));
6153 
6154  *Characteristics |= IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE;
6155 
6156  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (Process, Characteristics);
6157 
6158  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
6159 
6160  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x7);
6161 
6162  if ((Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
6163  (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 0)) {
6164 
6165  FreeBit = GET_PAGING_FILE_OFFSET (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
6166 
6167  if ((FreeBit != 0) && (FreeBit != MI_PTE_LOOKUP_NEEDED)) {
6168  MiReleaseConfirmedPageFileSpace (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
6169  }
6170 
6171  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.PageFileHigh = 0;
6172  }
6173 
6174  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6175 
6176  return;
6177 }
6178 
6179 VOID
6180 MiMakeEntireImageCopyOnWrite (
6181  IN PSUBSECTION Subsection
6182  )
6183 
6184 /*++
6185 
6186 Routine Description:
6187 
6188  This function sets the protection of all prototype PTEs to copy on write.
6189 
6190 Arguments:
6191 
6192  Subsection - Supplies the base subsection for the entire image.
6193 
6194 Return Value:
6195 
6196  None.
6197 
6198 --*/
6199 
6200 {
6201  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6202  PMMPTE ProtoPte;
6203  PMMPTE LastProtoPte;
6204  MMPTE PteContents;
6205 
6206  //
6207  // Note this is only called for image control areas that have at least
6208  // PAGE_SIZE subsection alignment, and so the first
6209  // subsection which maps the header can always be skipped.
6210  //
6211 
6212  do {
6213  Subsection = Subsection->NextSubsection;
6214 
6215  if (Subsection == NULL) {
6216  break;
6217  }
6218 
6219  //
6220  // Don't mark global subsections as copy on write even when the
6221  // image is relocated. This is easily distinguishable because
6222  // it is the only subsection that is marked readwrite.
6223  //
6224 
6225  if (Subsection->u.SubsectionFlags.Protection == MM_READWRITE) {
6226  continue;
6227  }
6228 
6229  ProtoPte = Subsection->SubsectionBase;
6230  LastProtoPte = Subsection->SubsectionBase + Subsection->PtesInSubsection;
6231 
6232  PointerPte = ProtoPte;
6233 
6234  MmLockPagedPool (ProtoPte, Subsection->PtesInSubsection * sizeof (MMPTE));
6235 
6236  do {
6237  PteContents = *PointerPte;
6238  ASSERT (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 0);
6239  if (PteContents.u.Long != 0) {
6240  if ((PteContents.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
6241  (PteContents.u.Soft.Transition == 1)) {
6242  if (MiSetProtectionOnTransitionPte (PointerPte, MM_EXECUTE_WRITECOPY)) {
6243  continue;
6244  }
6245  }
6246  else {
6247  PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection = MM_EXECUTE_WRITECOPY;
6248  }
6249  }
6250  PointerPte += 1;
6251  } while (PointerPte < LastProtoPte);
6252 
6253  MmUnlockPagedPool (ProtoPte, Subsection->PtesInSubsection * sizeof (MMPTE));
6254 
6255  Subsection->u.SubsectionFlags.Protection = MM_EXECUTE_WRITECOPY;
6256 
6257  } while (TRUE);
6258 
6259  return;
6260 }
6261 
6262 
6263 VOID
6264 MiSetSystemCodeProtection (
6265  IN PMMPTE FirstPte,
6266  IN PMMPTE LastPte,
6267  IN ULONG ProtectionMask
6268  )
6269 
6270 /*++
6271 
6272 Routine Description:
6273 
6274  This function sets the protection of system code as specified.
6275 
6276 Arguments:
6277 
6278  FirstPte - Supplies the starting PTE.
6279 
6280  LastPte - Supplies the ending PTE.
6281 
6282  ProtectionMask - Supplies the desired protection mask.
6283 
6284 Return Value:
6285 
6286  None.
6287 
6288 Environment:
6289 
6290  Kernel Mode, APC_LEVEL or below.
6291 
6292 --*/
6293 
6294 {
6295  KIRQL OldIrql;
6296  MMPTE PteContents;
6297  MMPTE TempPte;
6298  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6299  PMMPTE PointerPde;
6300  PMMPTE PointerProtoPte;
6301  PMMPFN Pfn1;
6302  LOGICAL SessionAddress;
6303  PVOID VirtualAddress;
6304  ULONG FlushCount;
6305  PVOID VaFlushList[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
6306  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
6307  PMMSUPPORT Ws;
6308 
6309  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= APC_LEVEL);
6310 
6311  FlushCount = 0;
6312 
6313 #if defined(_X86_)
6314  ASSERT (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(FirstPte)) == 0);
6315 #endif
6316 
6317  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
6318 
6319  PointerPte = FirstPte;
6320 
6321  if (MI_IS_SESSION_ADDRESS (MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(FirstPte))) {
6322  Ws = &MmSessionSpace->GlobalVirtualAddress->Vm;
6323  SessionAddress = TRUE;
6324  }
6325  else {
6326  Ws = &MmSystemCacheWs;
6327  SessionAddress = FALSE;
6328  }
6329 
6330  LOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, Ws);
6331 
6332  //
6333  // Set these PTEs to the specified protection.
6334  //
6335  // Note that the write bit may already be off (in the valid PTE) if the
6336  // page has already been inpaged from the paging file and has not since
6337  // been dirtied.
6338  //
6339 
6340  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6341 
6342  while (PointerPte <= LastPte) {
6343 
6344  PteContents = *PointerPte;
6345 
6346  if (PteContents.u.Long == 0) {
6347  PointerPte += 1;
6348  continue;
6349  }
6350 
6351  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
6352 
6353  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PteContents.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
6354 
6355  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte == 1) {
6356 
6357  //
6358  // This must be a session address. The prototype PTE contains
6359  // the protection that is pushed out to the real PTE after
6360  // it's been trimmed so update that too.
6361  //
6362 
6363  PointerProtoPte = Pfn1->PteAddress;
6364 
6365  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress (PointerProtoPte);
6366 
6367  if (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6368 
6369  if (SessionAddress == TRUE) {
6370 
6371  //
6372  // Unlock the session working set and lock the
6373  // system working set as we need to make the backing
6374  // prototype PTE valid.
6375  //
6376 
6377  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6378 
6379  UNLOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, Ws);
6380 
6381  LOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, &MmSystemCacheWs);
6382 
6383  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6384  }
6385 
6386  MiMakeSystemAddressValidPfnSystemWs (PointerProtoPte,
6387  OldIrql);
6388 
6389  if (SessionAddress == TRUE) {
6390 
6391  //
6392  // Unlock the system working set and lock the
6393  // session working set as we have made the backing
6394  // prototype PTE valid and can now handle the
6395  // original session PTE.
6396  //
6397 
6398  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6399 
6400  UNLOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, &MmSystemCacheWs);
6401 
6402  LOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, Ws);
6403 
6404  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6405  }
6406 
6407  //
6408  // The world may have changed while we waited.
6409  //
6410 
6411  continue;
6412  }
6413  }
6414  else {
6415  if ((ProtectionMask & MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) == MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) {
6416  //
6417  // This page is already private so ignore the copy on
6418  // write attribute (or anything else). This is very
6419  // unusual.
6420  //
6421 
6422  PointerPte += 1;
6423  continue;
6424  }
6425  PointerProtoPte = NULL;
6426  }
6427 
6428  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = ProtectionMask;
6429 
6430  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (TempPte,
6431  PteContents.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber,
6432  ProtectionMask,
6433  PointerPte);
6434 
6435  //
6436  // Note the dirty and write bits get turned off here.
6437  // Any existing pagefile addresses for clean pages are preserved.
6438  //
6439 
6440  if (MI_IS_PTE_DIRTY (PteContents)) {
6441  MI_CAPTURE_DIRTY_BIT_TO_PFN (&PteContents, Pfn1);
6442  }
6443 
6444  //
6445  // If the new protection is also directly writable, then preserve
6446  // the dirty and write bits so subsequent accesses do not fault.
6447  //
6448 
6449  if ((ProtectionMask == MM_READWRITE) ||
6450  (ProtectionMask == MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE)) {
6451 
6452  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Dirty == 1) {
6453  TempPte.u.Hard.Dirty = 1;
6454  }
6455 
6456 #if !defined(NT_UP)
6457 #if defined(_X86_) || defined(_AMD64_)
6458  TempPte.u.Hard.Writable = 1;
6459 #endif
6460 #endif
6461  }
6462 
6463  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Accessed == 1) {
6464  TempPte.u.Hard.Accessed = 1;
6465  }
6466 
6467  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE_NEW_PROTECTION (PointerPte, TempPte);
6468 
6469  if (PointerProtoPte != NULL) {
6470  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE_NEW_PROTECTION (PointerProtoPte, TempPte);
6471  }
6472 
6473  if (FlushCount < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
6474  VirtualAddress = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
6475  VaFlushList[FlushCount] = VirtualAddress;
6476  FlushCount += 1;
6477  }
6478 
6479  }
6480  else if (PteContents.u.Soft.Prototype == 1) {
6481 
6482  //
6483  // WITH REGARDS TO SESSION SPACE :
6484  //
6485  // Nothing needs to be done if the image was linked with
6486  // greater than or equal to PAGE_SIZE subsection alignment
6487  // because image section creation assigned proper protections
6488  // to each subsection.
6489  //
6490  // However, if the image had less than PAGE_SIZE subsection
6491  // alignment, then image creation uses a single copyonwrite
6492  // subsection to control the entire image, so individual
6493  // protections need to be applied now. Note well - this must
6494  // only be done *ONCE* when the image is first loaded - subsequent
6495  // loads of this image in other sessions do not need to update
6496  // the common prototype PTEs.
6497  //
6498 
6499  PointerProtoPte = MiPteToProto (PointerPte);
6500 
6501  ASSERT (!MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (PointerProtoPte));
6502  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress (PointerProtoPte);
6503 
6504  if (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6505 
6506  if (SessionAddress == TRUE) {
6507 
6508  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6509 
6510  UNLOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, Ws);
6511 
6512  LOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, &MmSystemCacheWs);
6513 
6514  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6515  }
6516 
6517  MiMakeSystemAddressValidPfnSystemWs (PointerProtoPte, OldIrql);
6518 
6519  if (SessionAddress == TRUE) {
6520 
6521  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6522 
6523  UNLOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, &MmSystemCacheWs);
6524 
6525  LOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, Ws);
6526 
6527  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6528  }
6529 
6530  //
6531  // The world may have changed while we waited.
6532  //
6533 
6534  continue;
6535  }
6536 
6537  PteContents = *PointerProtoPte;
6538 
6539  if (PteContents.u.Long != 0) {
6540 
6541  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
6542  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PteContents.u.Trans.PageFrameNumber);
6543  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = ProtectionMask;
6544  }
6545  else {
6546  PointerProtoPte->u.Soft.Protection = ProtectionMask;
6547 
6548  if ((PteContents.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
6549  (PteContents.u.Soft.Transition == 1)) {
6550  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PteContents.u.Trans.PageFrameNumber);
6551  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = ProtectionMask;
6552  }
6553  }
6554  }
6555  }
6556  else if (PteContents.u.Soft.Transition == 1) {
6557 
6558  //
6559  // This page is already private so if copy on write is specified,
6560  // skip this page. This is very unusual.
6561  //
6562 
6563  if ((ProtectionMask & MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) != MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) {
6564  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PteContents.u.Trans.PageFrameNumber);
6565  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = ProtectionMask;
6566  PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection = ProtectionMask;
6567  }
6568  }
6569  else {
6570 
6571  //
6572  // Must be page file space or demand zero.
6573  //
6574 
6575  //
6576  // This page is already private so if copy on write is specified,
6577  // skip this page. This is very unusual.
6578  //
6579 
6580  if ((ProtectionMask & MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) != MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) {
6581  PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection = ProtectionMask;
6582  }
6583  }
6584  PointerPte += 1;
6585  }
6586 
6587  if (FlushCount == 0) {
6588  NOTHING;
6589  }
6590  else if (FlushCount == 1) {
6591  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
6592  }
6593  else if (FlushCount < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
6594  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (FlushCount, &VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
6595  }
6596  else {
6597  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x17);
6598  }
6599 
6600  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6601 
6602  UNLOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread, Ws);
6603 
6604  return;
6605 }
6606 
6607 MM_PROTECTION_MASK
6608 MiComputeDriverProtection (
6609  IN LOGICAL SessionDriver,
6610  IN ULONG SectionProtection
6611  )
6612 
6613 /*++
6614 
6615 Routine Description:
6616 
6617  This function computes the driver protection mask for an image.
6618 
6619 Arguments:
6620 
6621  SessionDriver - Supplies TRUE if this is for a session space driver.
6622 
6623  SectionProtection - Supplies protection from the image header.
6624 
6625 Return Value:
6626 
6627  None.
6628 
6629 --*/
6630 
6631 {
6632  MM_PROTECTION_MASK NewProtection;
6633 
6634  NewProtection = MM_ZERO_ACCESS;
6635 
6636  if (SectionProtection != 0) {
6637 
6638  //
6639  // Always make images executable (unless they're completely
6640  // no-access) for compatibility.
6641  //
6642 
6643 #if !defined (_WIN64)
6644  SectionProtection |= IMAGE_SCN_MEM_EXECUTE;
6645 #endif
6646 
6647  if (MmEnforceWriteProtection == 0) {
6648  SectionProtection |= (IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE | IMAGE_SCN_MEM_EXECUTE);
6649  }
6650  }
6651 
6652  if (SectionProtection & IMAGE_SCN_MEM_EXECUTE) {
6653  NewProtection |= MM_EXECUTE;
6654  }
6655 
6656  if (SectionProtection & IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ) {
6657  NewProtection |= MM_READONLY;
6658  }
6659 
6660  if (SectionProtection & IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE) {
6661 
6662  if (SessionDriver == TRUE) {
6663 
6664  if (NewProtection & MM_EXECUTE) {
6665  NewProtection = MM_EXECUTE_WRITECOPY;
6666  }
6667  else {
6668  NewProtection = MM_WRITECOPY;
6669  }
6670  }
6671  else {
6672  if (NewProtection & MM_EXECUTE) {
6673  NewProtection = MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE;
6674  }
6675  else {
6676  NewProtection = MM_READWRITE;
6677  }
6678  }
6679  }
6680 
6681  if (NewProtection == MM_ZERO_ACCESS) {
6682  NewProtection = MM_NOACCESS;
6683  }
6684 
6685  return NewProtection;
6686 }
6687 
6688 VOID
6689 MiWriteProtectSystemImage (
6690  IN PVOID DllBase
6691  )
6692 
6693 /*++
6694 
6695 Routine Description:
6696 
6697  This function sets the protection of a system component as specified.
6698 
6699 Arguments:
6700 
6701  DllBase - Supplies the base address of the system component.
6702 
6703 Return Value:
6704 
6705  None.
6706 
6707 --*/
6708 
6709 {
6710  ULONG RelevantSectionProtections;
6711  ULONG LastSectionProtection;
6712  ULONG SectionProtection;
6713  ULONG MergedSectionProtection;
6714  ULONG NumberOfSubsections;
6715  ULONG SectionVirtualSize;
6716  ULONG OffsetToSectionTable;
6717  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPtes;
6718  ULONG_PTR VirtualAddress;
6719  PVOID LastVirtualAddress;
6720  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6721  PMMPTE FirstPte;
6722  PMMPTE LastPte;
6723  PMMPTE LastImagePte;
6724  PMMPTE MergedPte;
6725  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeader;
6726  PIMAGE_FILE_HEADER FileHeader;
6727  PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER SectionTableEntry;
6728  MM_PROTECTION_MASK LastProtection;
6729  MM_PROTECTION_MASK MergedProtection;
6730  LOGICAL SessionDriver;
6731 
6732  PAGED_CODE();
6733 
6734  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (DllBase)) {
6735  return;
6736  }
6737 
6738  NtHeader = RtlImageNtHeader (DllBase);
6739 
6740  if (NtHeader == NULL) {
6741  return;
6742  }
6743 
6744  if (MI_IS_SESSION_ADDRESS (DllBase) == 0) {
6745 
6746  //
6747  // Images prior to Win2000 were not protected from stepping all over
6748  // their (and others) code and readonly data. Here we somewhat
6749  // preserve that behavior, but don't allow them to step on anyone else.
6750  //
6751 
6752  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MajorOperatingSystemVersion < 5) {
6753  return;
6754  }
6755 
6756  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MajorImageVersion < 5) {
6757  return;
6758  }
6759  SessionDriver = FALSE;
6760  }
6761  else {
6762  SessionDriver = TRUE;
6763  }
6764 
6765  //
6766  // Don't include IMAGE_SCN_MEM_SHARED because it only applies to session
6767  // drivers and that's handled by MiSessionProcessGlobalSubsections.
6768  //
6769 
6770  RelevantSectionProtections = (IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE | IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | IMAGE_SCN_MEM_EXECUTE);
6771 
6772  //
6773  // If the image has section alignment of at least PAGE_SIZE, then
6774  // the image section was created with individual subsections and
6775  // proper permissions already applied to the prototype PTEs. However,
6776  // our caller may have been changing the individual PTE protections
6777  // in order to relocate the image, so march on regardless of section
6778  // alignment.
6779  //
6780 
6781  NumberOfPtes = BYTES_TO_PAGES (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.SizeOfImage);
6782 
6783  FileHeader = &NtHeader->FileHeader;
6784 
6785  NumberOfSubsections = FileHeader->NumberOfSections;
6786 
6787  ASSERT (NumberOfSubsections != 0);
6788 
6789  OffsetToSectionTable = sizeof(ULONG) +
6790  sizeof(IMAGE_FILE_HEADER) +
6791  FileHeader->SizeOfOptionalHeader;
6792 
6793  SectionTableEntry = (PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER)((PCHAR)NtHeader +
6794  OffsetToSectionTable);
6795 
6796  //
6797  // Verify the image contains subsections ordered by increasing virtual
6798  // address and that there are no overlaps.
6799  //
6800 
6801  LastVirtualAddress = DllBase;
6802 
6803  for ( ; NumberOfSubsections > 0; NumberOfSubsections -= 1, SectionTableEntry += 1) {
6804 
6805  if (SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize == 0) {
6806  SectionVirtualSize = SectionTableEntry->SizeOfRawData;
6807  }
6808  else {
6809  SectionVirtualSize = SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize;
6810  }
6811 
6812  VirtualAddress = (ULONG_PTR)DllBase + SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress;
6813  if ((PVOID)VirtualAddress <= LastVirtualAddress) {
6814 
6815  //
6816  // Subsections are not in an increasing virtual address ordering.
6817  // No protection is provided for such a poorly linked image.
6818  //
6819 
6820  KdPrint (("MM:sysload - Image at %p is badly linked\n", DllBase));
6821  return;
6822  }
6823  LastVirtualAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)VirtualAddress + SectionVirtualSize - 1);
6824  }
6825 
6826  NumberOfSubsections = FileHeader->NumberOfSections;
6827  ASSERT (NumberOfSubsections != 0);
6828 
6829  SectionTableEntry = (PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER)((PCHAR)NtHeader +
6830  OffsetToSectionTable);
6831 
6832  LastVirtualAddress = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)(SectionTableEntry + NumberOfSubsections) - 1);
6833 
6834  //
6835  // Set writable PTE here so the image headers are excluded. This is
6836  // needed so that locking down of sections can continue to edit the
6837  // image headers for counts.
6838  //
6839 
6840  LastSectionProtection = (IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE | IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ);
6841 
6842  FirstPte = MiGetPteAddress (DllBase);
6843  LastImagePte = MiGetPteAddress(DllBase) + NumberOfPtes;
6844 
6845  MergedPte = NULL;
6846  MergedSectionProtection = 0;
6847 
6848  for ( ; NumberOfSubsections > 0; NumberOfSubsections -= 1, SectionTableEntry += 1) {
6849 
6850  if (SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize == 0) {
6851  SectionVirtualSize = SectionTableEntry->SizeOfRawData;
6852  }
6853  else {
6854  SectionVirtualSize = SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize;
6855  }
6856 
6857  VirtualAddress = (ULONG_PTR)DllBase + SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress;
6858 
6859  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)VirtualAddress);
6860 
6861  if ((MergedPte != NULL) && (PointerPte > MergedPte)) {
6862 
6863  //
6864  // Apply the merged protection to the prior straddling PTE.
6865  //
6866 
6867  MergedProtection = MiComputeDriverProtection (SessionDriver,
6868  MergedSectionProtection);
6869  MiSetSystemCodeProtection (MergedPte, MergedPte, MergedProtection);
6870 
6871  if (MergedPte == FirstPte) {
6872 
6873  //
6874  // The merged PTE overlapped with the first PTE of the prior
6875  // subsection, so increment the first PTE now.
6876  //
6877 
6878  FirstPte += 1;
6879  }
6880 
6881  MergedPte = NULL;
6882  MergedSectionProtection = 0;
6883  }
6884 
6885  if (PointerPte >= LastImagePte) {
6886 
6887  //
6888  // Skip relocation subsections (which aren't given VA space).
6889  //
6890 
6891  break;
6892  }
6893 
6894  SectionProtection = (SectionTableEntry->Characteristics & RelevantSectionProtections);
6895 
6896  if (SectionProtection == LastSectionProtection) {
6897 
6898  //
6899  // Merge adjacent subsections that have the same protection.
6900  //
6901 
6902  LastVirtualAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)VirtualAddress + SectionVirtualSize - 1);
6903  continue;
6904  }
6905 
6906  //
6907  // This section has different permissions from the previous one so
6908  // set the protections on the previous one now.
6909  //
6910 
6911  //
6912  // Update the PTE protections. Make sure if it's sharing
6913  // a PTE that the last PTE is set to the most relaxed
6914  // permission combination.
6915  //
6916 
6917  LastPte = (PVOID) MiGetPteAddress (LastVirtualAddress);
6918 
6919  if (LastPte == PointerPte) {
6920 
6921  //
6922  // Don't include the last PTE from the previous subsection as it
6923  // overlaps with this one (and may overlap with the next subsection
6924  // if this one is small!).
6925  //
6926 
6927  LastPte -= 1;
6928 
6929  //
6930  // Compute the most relaxed permission for the straddling PTE
6931  // by merging subsection protections, but don't apply it till
6932  // we have ascertained that there are no more subsections which
6933  // can overlap into this PTE.
6934  //
6935 
6936  if (MergedPte != NULL) {
6937  ASSERT (MergedPte == PointerPte);
6938  }
6939 
6940  MergedSectionProtection |= (SectionProtection | LastSectionProtection);
6941 
6942  MergedPte = PointerPte;
6943  }
6944 
6945  if (LastPte >= FirstPte) {
6946 
6947  ASSERT (FirstPte < LastImagePte);
6948 
6949  if (LastPte >= LastImagePte) {
6950  LastPte = LastImagePte - 1;
6951  }
6952 
6953  ASSERT (LastPte >= FirstPte);
6954 
6955  LastProtection = MiComputeDriverProtection (SessionDriver,
6956  LastSectionProtection);
6957 
6958  MiSetSystemCodeProtection (FirstPte, LastPte, LastProtection);
6959  }
6960 
6961  //
6962  // Initialize variables to describe the current subsection as it
6963  // is the start of a new run.
6964  //
6965 
6966  FirstPte = PointerPte;
6967  LastVirtualAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)VirtualAddress + SectionVirtualSize - 1);
6968  LastSectionProtection = SectionProtection;
6969  }
6970 
6971  if (MergedPte != NULL) {
6972 
6973  //
6974  // Apply the merged protection to the prior straddling PTE.
6975  //
6976 
6977  MergedProtection = MiComputeDriverProtection (SessionDriver,
6978  MergedSectionProtection);
6979 
6980  MiSetSystemCodeProtection (MergedPte, MergedPte, MergedProtection);
6981 
6982  if (MergedPte == FirstPte) {
6983 
6984  //
6985  // The merged PTE overlapped with the first PTE of the prior
6986  // subsection, so increment the first PTE now.
6987  //
6988 
6989  FirstPte += 1;
6990  }
6991 
6992  MergedPte = NULL;
6993  MergedSectionProtection = 0;
6994  }
6995 
6996  //
6997  // Set the protections on the last subsection's PTEs now.
6998  //
6999 
7000  LastPte = (PVOID) MiGetPteAddress (LastVirtualAddress);
7001 
7002  if ((FirstPte < LastImagePte) && (LastPte >= FirstPte)) {
7003 
7004  if (LastPte >= LastImagePte) {
7005  LastPte = LastImagePte - 1;
7006  }
7007 
7008  ASSERT (LastPte >= FirstPte);
7009 
7010  LastProtection = MiComputeDriverProtection (SessionDriver,
7011  LastSectionProtection);
7012 
7013  MiSetSystemCodeProtection (FirstPte, LastPte, LastProtection);
7014  }
7015 
7016  return;
7017 }
7018 
7019 
7020 VOID
7021 MiSessionProcessGlobalSubsections (
7022  IN PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry
7023  )
7024 
7025 /*++
7026 
7027 Routine Description:
7028 
7029  This function sets the protection of a session driver's subsections
7030  to globally shared if their PE header specifies them as such.
7031 
7032 Arguments:
7033 
7034  DataTableEntry - Supplies the loaded module list entry for the driver.
7035 
7036 Return Value:
7037 
7038  None.
7039 
7040 --*/
7041 
7042 {
7043  PVOID DllBase;
7044  PSUBSECTION Subsection;
7045  PMMPTE RealPteBase;
7046  PMMPTE PrototypePteBase;
7047  PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea;
7048  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeader;
7049  PMMPTE PointerPte;
7050  PMMPTE LastPte;
7051  LOGICAL GlobalSubsectionSupport;
7052  PIMAGE_ENTRY_IN_SESSION Image;
7053  ULONG Count;
7054 
7055  PAGED_CODE();
7056 
7057  Image = MiSessionLookupImage (DataTableEntry->DllBase);
7058 
7059  if (Image != NULL) {
7060  ASSERT (MmSessionSpace->ImageLoadingCount >= 0);
7061 
7062  if (Image->ImageLoading == TRUE) {
7063  Image->ImageLoading = FALSE;
7064  ASSERT (MmSessionSpace->ImageLoadingCount > 0);
7065  InterlockedDecrement (&MmSessionSpace->ImageLoadingCount);
7066  }
7067  }
7068  else {
7069  ASSERT (FALSE);
7070  }
7071 
7072  DllBase = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
7073 
7074  ControlArea = ((PSECTION)DataTableEntry->SectionPointer)->Segment->ControlArea;
7075 
7076  ASSERT (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(DllBase) == FALSE);
7077 
7078  ASSERT (MI_IS_SESSION_ADDRESS(DllBase));
7079 
7080  NtHeader = RtlImageNtHeader (DllBase);
7081 
7082  ASSERT (NtHeader);
7083 
7084  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.SectionAlignment < PAGE_SIZE) {
7085  if (Image->GlobalSubs != NULL) {
7086  ExFreePool (Image->GlobalSubs);
7087  Image->GlobalSubs = NULL;
7088  }
7089  return;
7090  }
7091 
7092  //
7093  // Win XP and Win2000 did not support global shared subsections
7094  // for session images. To ensure backwards compatibility for existing
7095  // drivers, ensure that only newer ones get this feature.
7096  //
7097 
7098  GlobalSubsectionSupport = FALSE;
7099 
7100  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MajorOperatingSystemVersion > 5) {
7101  GlobalSubsectionSupport = TRUE;
7102  }
7103  else if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MajorOperatingSystemVersion == 5) {
7104 
7105  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MinorOperatingSystemVersion > 1) {
7106  GlobalSubsectionSupport = TRUE;
7107  }
7108  else if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MinorOperatingSystemVersion == 1) {
7109  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MajorImageVersion > 5) {
7110  GlobalSubsectionSupport = TRUE;
7111  }
7112  else if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MajorImageVersion == 5) {
7113  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MinorImageVersion > 1) {
7114  GlobalSubsectionSupport = TRUE;
7115  }
7116  else if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MinorImageVersion == 1) {
7117  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MajorSubsystemVersion > 5) {
7118  GlobalSubsectionSupport = TRUE;
7119  }
7120  else if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MajorSubsystemVersion == 5) {
7121  if (NtHeader->OptionalHeader.MinorSubsystemVersion >= 2) {
7122  GlobalSubsectionSupport = TRUE;
7123  }
7124  }
7125  }
7126  }
7127  }
7128  }
7129 
7130  if (GlobalSubsectionSupport == FALSE) {
7131  if (Image->GlobalSubs != NULL) {
7132  ExFreePool (Image->GlobalSubs);
7133  Image->GlobalSubs = NULL;
7134  }
7135  return;
7136  }
7137 
7138  if ((ControlArea->u.Flags.GlobalOnlyPerSession == 0) &&
7139  (ControlArea->u.Flags.Rom == 0)) {
7140  Subsection = (PSUBSECTION)(ControlArea + 1);
7141  }
7142  else {
7143  Subsection = (PSUBSECTION)((PLARGE_CONTROL_AREA)ControlArea + 1);
7144  }
7145 
7146  RealPteBase = MiGetPteAddress (DllBase);
7147  PrototypePteBase = Subsection->SubsectionBase;
7148 
7149  //
7150  // Loop through all the subsections.
7151  //
7152 
7153  if (ControlArea->u.Flags.Image == 1) {
7154 
7155  do {
7156 
7157  if (Subsection->u.SubsectionFlags.GlobalMemory == 1) {
7158 
7159  PointerPte = RealPteBase + (Subsection->SubsectionBase - PrototypePteBase);
7160  LastPte = PointerPte + Subsection->PtesInSubsection - 1;
7161 
7162  MiSetSystemCodeProtection (PointerPte,
7163  LastPte,
7164  Subsection->u.SubsectionFlags.Protection);
7165  }
7166 
7167  Subsection = Subsection->NextSubsection;
7168 
7169  } while (Subsection != NULL);
7170  }
7171  else if (Image->GlobalSubs != NULL) {
7172 
7173  Count = 0;
7174  ASSERT (Subsection->NextSubsection == NULL);
7175 
7176  while (Image->GlobalSubs[Count].PteCount != 0) {
7177 
7178  PointerPte = RealPteBase + Image->GlobalSubs[Count].PteIndex;
7179  LastPte = PointerPte + Image->GlobalSubs[Count].PteCount - 1;
7180 
7181  MiSetSystemCodeProtection (PointerPte,
7182  LastPte,
7183  Image->GlobalSubs[Count].Protection);
7184 
7185  Count += 1;
7186  }
7187 
7188  ExFreePool (Image->GlobalSubs);
7189  Image->GlobalSubs = NULL;
7190  }
7191 
7192  return;
7193 }
7194 
7195 
7196 VOID
7197 MiUpdateThunks (
7198  IN PLOADER_PARAMETER_BLOCK LoaderBlock,
7199  IN PVOID OldAddress,
7200  IN PVOID NewAddress,
7201  IN ULONG NumberOfBytes
7202  )
7203 
7204 /*++
7205 
7206 Routine Description:
7207 
7208  This function updates the IATs of all the loaded modules in the system
7209  to handle a newly relocated image.
7210 
7211 Arguments:
7212 
7213  LoaderBlock - Supplies a pointer to the system loader block.
7214 
7215  OldAddress - Supplies the old address of the DLL which was just relocated.
7216 
7217  NewAddress - Supplies the new address of the DLL which was just relocated.
7218 
7219  NumberOfBytes - Supplies the number of bytes spanned by the DLL.
7220 
7221 Return Value:
7222 
7223  None.
7224 
7225 --*/
7226 
7227 {
7228  PULONG_PTR ImportThunk;
7229  ULONG_PTR OldAddressHigh;
7230  ULONG_PTR AddressDifference;
7231  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
7232  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
7233  ULONG_PTR i;
7234  ULONG ImportSize;
7235 
7236  //
7237  // Note this routine must not call any modules outside the kernel.
7238  // This is because that module may itself be the one being relocated right
7239  // now.
7240  //
7241 
7242  OldAddressHigh = (ULONG_PTR)((PCHAR)OldAddress + NumberOfBytes - 1);
7243  AddressDifference = (ULONG_PTR)NewAddress - (ULONG_PTR)OldAddress;
7244 
7245  NextEntry = LoaderBlock->LoadOrderListHead.Flink;
7246 
7247  for ( ; NextEntry != &LoaderBlock->LoadOrderListHead; NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink) {
7248 
7249  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
7250  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
7251  InLoadOrderLinks);
7252 
7253  ImportThunk = (PULONG_PTR) RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (
7254  DataTableEntry->DllBase,
7255  TRUE,
7256  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IAT,
7257  &ImportSize);
7258 
7259  if (ImportThunk == NULL) {
7260  continue;
7261  }
7262 
7263  ImportSize /= sizeof(PULONG_PTR);
7264 
7265  for (i = 0; i < ImportSize; i += 1, ImportThunk += 1) {
7266  if (*ImportThunk >= (ULONG_PTR)OldAddress && *ImportThunk <= OldAddressHigh) {
7267  *ImportThunk += AddressDifference;
7268  }
7269  }
7270  }
7271 }
7272 
7273 
7274 VOID
7275 MiReloadBootLoadedDrivers (
7276  IN PLOADER_PARAMETER_BLOCK LoaderBlock
7277  )
7278 
7279 /*++
7280 
7281 Routine Description:
7282 
7283  The kernel, HAL and boot drivers are relocated by the loader.
7284  All the boot drivers are then relocated again here.
7285 
7286  This function relocates osloader-loaded images into system PTEs. This
7287  gives these images the benefits that all other drivers already enjoy,
7288  including :
7289 
7290  1. Paging of the drivers (this is more than 500K today).
7291  2. Write-protection of their text sections.
7292  3. Automatic unload of drivers on last dereference.
7293 
7294  Note care must be taken when processing HIGHADJ relocations more than once.
7295 
7296 Arguments:
7297 
7298  LoaderBlock - Supplies a pointer to the system loader block.
7299 
7300 Return Value:
7301 
7302  None.
7303 
7304 Environment:
7305 
7306  Kernel mode, Phase 0 Initialization.
7307 
7308 --*/
7309 
7310 {
7311  LOGICAL UsedLargePage;
7312  LOGICAL HasRelocations;
7313  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
7314  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
7315  PIMAGE_FILE_HEADER FileHeader;
7316  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeader;
7317  PIMAGE_DATA_DIRECTORY DataDirectory;
7318  ULONG_PTR i;
7319  ULONG RoundedNumberOfPtes;
7320  ULONG NumberOfPtes;
7321  ULONG NumberOfLoaderPtes;
7322  PMMPTE PointerPte;
7323  PMMPTE LastPte;
7324  PMMPTE LoaderPte;
7325  MMPTE PteContents;
7326  MMPTE TempPte;
7327  PVOID LoaderImageAddress;
7328  PVOID NewImageAddress;
7329  NTSTATUS Status;
7330  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
7331  PFN_NUMBER PteFramePage;
7332  PMMPTE PteFramePointer;
7333  PMMPFN Pfn1;
7334  PMMPFN Pfn2;
7335  KIRQL OldIrql;
7336  PCHAR RelocatedVa;
7337  PCHAR NonRelocatedVa;
7338  LOGICAL StopMoving;
7339 
7340 #if !defined (_X86_)
7341 
7342  //
7343  // Only try to preserve low memory on x86 machines.
7344  //
7345 
7346  MmMakeLowMemory = FALSE;
7347 #endif
7348  StopMoving = FALSE;
7349 
7350  i = 0;
7351  NextEntry = LoaderBlock->LoadOrderListHead.Flink;
7352 
7353  for ( ; NextEntry != &LoaderBlock->LoadOrderListHead; NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink) {
7354 
7355  //
7356  // Skip the kernel and the HAL. Note their relocation sections will
7357  // be automatically reclaimed.
7358  //
7359 
7360  i += 1;
7361  if (i <= 2) {
7362  continue;
7363  }
7364 
7365  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
7366  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
7367  InLoadOrderLinks);
7368 
7369  NtHeader = RtlImageNtHeader (DataTableEntry->DllBase);
7370 
7371  //
7372  // Ensure that the relocation section exists and that the loader
7373  // hasn't freed it already.
7374  //
7375 
7376  if (NtHeader == NULL) {
7377  continue;
7378  }
7379 
7380  FileHeader = &NtHeader->FileHeader;
7381 
7382  if (FileHeader->Characteristics & IMAGE_FILE_RELOCS_STRIPPED) {
7383  continue;
7384  }
7385 
7386  if (IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_BASERELOC >= NtHeader->OptionalHeader.NumberOfRvaAndSizes) {
7387  continue;
7388  }
7389 
7390  DataDirectory = &NtHeader->OptionalHeader.DataDirectory[IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_BASERELOC];
7391 
7392  if (DataDirectory->VirtualAddress == 0) {
7393  HasRelocations = FALSE;
7394  }
7395  else {
7396 
7397  if (DataDirectory->VirtualAddress + DataDirectory->Size > DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage) {
7398 
7399  //
7400  // The relocation section has already been freed, the user must
7401  // be using an old loader that didn't save the relocations.
7402  //
7403 
7404  continue;
7405  }
7406  HasRelocations = TRUE;
7407  }
7408 
7409  LoaderImageAddress = DataTableEntry->DllBase;
7410  LoaderPte = MiGetPteAddress(DataTableEntry->DllBase);
7411  NumberOfLoaderPtes = (ULONG)((ROUND_TO_PAGES(DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage)) >> PAGE_SHIFT);
7412 
7413  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7414 
7415  PointerPte = LoaderPte;
7416  LastPte = PointerPte + NumberOfLoaderPtes;
7417 
7418  while (PointerPte < LastPte) {
7419  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
7420  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
7421  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
7422 
7423  //
7424  // Mark the page as modified so boot drivers that call
7425  // MmPageEntireDriver don't lose their unmodified data !
7426  //
7427 
7428  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x14);
7429 
7430  PointerPte += 1;
7431  }
7432 
7433  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7434 
7435  NumberOfPtes = NumberOfLoaderPtes;
7436 
7437  NewImageAddress = LoaderImageAddress;
7438 
7439  UsedLargePage = MiUseLargeDriverPage (NumberOfPtes,
7440  &NewImageAddress,
7441  &DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
7442  0);
7443 
7444  if (UsedLargePage == TRUE) {
7445 
7446  //
7447  // This image has been loaded into a large page mapping.
7448  //
7449 
7450  RelocatedVa = NewImageAddress;
7451  NonRelocatedVa = (PCHAR) DataTableEntry->DllBase;
7452  PointerPte -= NumberOfPtes;
7453  goto Fixup;
7454  }
7455 
7456  //
7457  // Extra PTEs are allocated here to map the relocation section at the
7458  // new address so the image can be relocated.
7459  //
7460 
7461  PointerPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (NumberOfPtes, SystemPteSpace);
7462 
7463  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
7464  continue;
7465  }
7466 
7467  LastPte = PointerPte + NumberOfPtes;
7468 
7469  NewImageAddress = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
7470 
7471  //
7472  // This assert is important because the assumption is made that PTEs
7473  // (not superpages) are mapping these drivers.
7474  //
7475 
7476  ASSERT (InitializationPhase == 0);
7477 
7478  //
7479  // If the system is configured to make low memory available for ISA
7480  // type drivers, then copy the boot loaded drivers now. Otherwise
7481  // only PTE adjustment is done. Presumably some day when ISA goes
7482  // away this code can be removed.
7483  //
7484 
7485  RelocatedVa = NewImageAddress;
7486  NonRelocatedVa = (PCHAR) DataTableEntry->DllBase;
7487 
7488  while (PointerPte < LastPte) {
7489 
7490  PteContents = *LoaderPte;
7491  ASSERT (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1);
7492 
7493  if (MmMakeLowMemory == TRUE) {
7494 #if DBG
7495  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (LoaderPte);
7496  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
7497  ASSERT (Pfn1->u1.WsIndex == 0);
7498 #endif
7499  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7500 
7501  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
7502  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
7503  }
7504 
7505  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveAnyPage(
7506  MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_PTE (PointerPte));
7507 
7508  if (PageFrameIndex < (16*1024*1024)/PAGE_SIZE) {
7509 
7510  //
7511  // If the frames cannot be replaced with high pages
7512  // then stop copying.
7513  //
7514 
7515 #if defined (_MI_MORE_THAN_4GB_)
7516  if (MiNoLowMemory == 0)
7517 #endif
7518  StopMoving = TRUE;
7519  }
7520 
7521  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte,
7522  PageFrameIndex,
7523  MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE,
7524  PointerPte);
7525 
7526  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
7527  MI_SET_ACCESSED_IN_PTE (&TempPte, 1);
7528 
7529  MiInitializePfnAndMakePteValid (PageFrameIndex, PointerPte, TempPte);
7530  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
7531 
7532  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x15);
7533 
7534  //
7535  // Initialize the WsIndex just like the original page had it.
7536  //
7537 
7538  Pfn1->u1.WsIndex = 0;
7539 
7540  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7541  RtlCopyMemory (RelocatedVa, NonRelocatedVa, PAGE_SIZE);
7542  RelocatedVa += PAGE_SIZE;
7543  NonRelocatedVa += PAGE_SIZE;
7544  }
7545  else {
7546  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte,
7547  PteContents.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber,
7548  MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE,
7549  PointerPte);
7550 
7551  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
7552 
7553  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
7554  }
7555 
7556  PointerPte += 1;
7557  LoaderPte += 1;
7558  }
7559  PointerPte -= NumberOfPtes;
7560 
7561 Fixup:
7562 
7563  ASSERT (*(PULONG)NewImageAddress == *(PULONG)LoaderImageAddress);
7564 
7565  //
7566  // Image is now mapped at the new address. Relocate it (again).
7567  //
7568 
7569  NtHeader->OptionalHeader.ImageBase = (ULONG_PTR)LoaderImageAddress;
7570  if ((MmMakeLowMemory == TRUE) || (UsedLargePage == TRUE)) {
7571  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeader2;
7572 
7573  NtHeader2 = (PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS)((PCHAR)NtHeader + (RelocatedVa - NonRelocatedVa));
7574  NtHeader2->OptionalHeader.ImageBase = (ULONG_PTR)LoaderImageAddress;
7575  }
7576 
7577  if (HasRelocations == TRUE) {
7578  Status = (NTSTATUS)LdrRelocateImage(NewImageAddress,
7579  (CONST PCHAR)"SYSLDR",
7580  (ULONG)STATUS_SUCCESS,
7581  (ULONG)STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES,
7582  (ULONG)STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_FORMAT
7583  );
7584 
7585  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
7586 
7587  if (UsedLargePage == TRUE) {
7588  ASSERT (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (MiGetPdeAddress (NewImageAddress)));
7589  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (MiGetPdeAddress (NewImageAddress)) + MiGetPteOffset (NewImageAddress);
7590 
7591  RoundedNumberOfPtes = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (NumberOfPtes,
7592  MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT);
7593  MiUnmapLargePages (NewImageAddress,
7594  RoundedNumberOfPtes << PAGE_SHIFT);
7595 
7596  MiRemoveCachedRange (PageFrameIndex, PageFrameIndex + RoundedNumberOfPtes - 1);
7597  MiFreeContiguousPages (PageFrameIndex, RoundedNumberOfPtes);
7598  }
7599 
7600  if (MmMakeLowMemory == TRUE) {
7601 
7602  while (PointerPte < LastPte) {
7603 
7604  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
7605  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
7606  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
7607 
7608  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
7609 
7610  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
7611  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
7612 
7613  PointerPte += 1;
7614  }
7615  PointerPte -= NumberOfPtes;
7616  }
7617 
7618  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPte, NumberOfPtes, SystemPteSpace);
7619 
7620  if (StopMoving == TRUE) {
7621  MmMakeLowMemory = FALSE;
7622  }
7623 
7624  continue;
7625  }
7626  }
7627 
7628  //
7629  // Update the IATs for all other loaded modules that reference this one.
7630  //
7631 
7632  NonRelocatedVa = (PCHAR) DataTableEntry->DllBase;
7633  DataTableEntry->DllBase = NewImageAddress;
7634 
7635  MiUpdateThunks (LoaderBlock,
7636  LoaderImageAddress,
7637  NewImageAddress,
7638  DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage);
7639 
7640 
7641  //
7642  // Update the loaded module list entry.
7643  //
7644 
7645  DataTableEntry->Flags |= LDRP_SYSTEM_MAPPED;
7646  DataTableEntry->DllBase = NewImageAddress;
7647  DataTableEntry->EntryPoint =
7648  (PVOID)((PCHAR)NewImageAddress + NtHeader->OptionalHeader.AddressOfEntryPoint);
7649  DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage = NumberOfPtes << PAGE_SHIFT;
7650 
7651  //
7652  // Update the exception table data info
7653  //
7654 
7655  MiCaptureImageExceptionValues (DataTableEntry);
7656 
7657  //
7658  // Update the PFNs of the image to support trimming.
7659  // Note that the loader addresses are freed now so no references
7660  // to it are permitted after this point.
7661  //
7662 
7663  LoaderPte = MiGetPteAddress (NonRelocatedVa);
7664 
7665  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7666 
7667  while (PointerPte < LastPte) {
7668 
7669  ASSERT ((UsedLargePage == TRUE) || (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1));
7670 
7671  if ((MmMakeLowMemory == TRUE) || (UsedLargePage == TRUE)) {
7672 
7673  ASSERT (LoaderPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
7674  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (LoaderPte);
7675  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
7676  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
7677 
7678  //
7679  // Decrement the share count on the original page table
7680  // page so it can be freed.
7681  //
7682 
7683  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
7684 
7685  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
7686  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
7687  LoaderPte += 1;
7688  }
7689  else {
7690 
7691  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
7692  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
7693  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
7694 
7695  //
7696  // Decrement the share count on the original page table
7697  // page so it can be freed.
7698  //
7699 
7700  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
7701  Pfn1->PteAddress->u.Long = 0;
7702 
7703  //
7704  // Chain the PFN entry to its new page table.
7705  //
7706 
7707  PteFramePointer = MiGetPteAddress(PointerPte);
7708  PteFramePage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PteFramePointer);
7709 
7710  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = PteFramePage;
7711  Pfn1->PteAddress = PointerPte;
7712 
7713  //
7714  // Increment the share count for the page table page that now
7715  // contains the PTE that was copied.
7716  //
7717 
7718  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PteFramePage);
7719  Pfn2->u2.ShareCount += 1;
7720  }
7721 
7722  PointerPte += 1;
7723  }
7724 
7725  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7726 
7727  //
7728  // The physical pages mapping the relocation section are freed
7729  // later with the rest of the initialization code spanned by the
7730  // DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage.
7731  //
7732 
7733  if (StopMoving == TRUE) {
7734  MmMakeLowMemory = FALSE;
7735  }
7736  }
7737 
7738  //
7739  // Flush the instruction cache on all systems in the configuration.
7740  //
7741 
7742  KeSweepIcache (TRUE);
7743 }
7744 
7745 #if defined(_X86_) || defined(_AMD64_)
7746 PMMPTE MiKernelResourceStartPte;
7747 PMMPTE MiKernelResourceEndPte;
7748 #endif
7749 
7750 VOID
7751 MiLocateKernelSections (
7752  IN PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry
7753  )
7754 
7755 /*++
7756 
7757 Routine Description:
7758 
7759  This function locates the resource section in the kernel so it can be
7760  made readwrite if we bugcheck later, as the bugcheck code will write
7761  into it.
7762 
7763 Arguments:
7764 
7765  DataTableEntry - Supplies the kernel's data table entry.
7766 
7767 Return Value:
7768 
7769  None.
7770 
7771 Environment:
7772 
7773  Kernel mode, Phase 0 Initialization.
7774 
7775 --*/
7776 
7777 {
7778  ULONG Span;
7779  PVOID CurrentBase;
7780  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeader;
7781  PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER SectionTableEntry;
7782  LONG i;
7783  PMMPTE PointerPte;
7784  PVOID SectionBaseAddress;
7785 
7786  CurrentBase = (PVOID) DataTableEntry->DllBase;
7787 
7788  NtHeader = RtlImageNtHeader (CurrentBase);
7789 
7790  SectionTableEntry = (PIMAGE_SECTION_HEADER)((PCHAR)NtHeader +
7791  sizeof(ULONG) +
7792  sizeof(IMAGE_FILE_HEADER) +
7793  NtHeader->FileHeader.SizeOfOptionalHeader);
7794 
7795  //
7796  // From the image header, locate the section named '.rsrc'.
7797  //
7798 
7799  i = NtHeader->FileHeader.NumberOfSections;
7800 
7801  PointerPte = NULL;
7802 
7803  while (i > 0) {
7804 
7805  SectionBaseAddress = SECTION_BASE_ADDRESS(SectionTableEntry);
7806 
7807  //
7808  // Generally, SizeOfRawData is larger than VirtualSize for each
7809  // section because it includes the padding to get to the subsection
7810  // alignment boundary. However, if the image is linked with
7811  // subsection alignment == native page alignment, the linker will
7812  // have VirtualSize be much larger than SizeOfRawData because it
7813  // will account for all the bss.
7814  //
7815 
7816  Span = SectionTableEntry->SizeOfRawData;
7817 
7818  if (Span < SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize) {
7819  Span = SectionTableEntry->Misc.VirtualSize;
7820  }
7821 
7822 #if defined(_X86_) || defined(_AMD64_)
7823  if (*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'rsr.') {
7824 
7825  MiKernelResourceStartPte = MiGetPteAddress ((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
7826  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress);
7827 
7828  MiKernelResourceEndPte = MiGetPteAddress (ROUND_TO_PAGES((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
7829  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress + Span));
7830  break;
7831  }
7832 #endif
7833  if (*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'LOOP') {
7834  if (*(PULONG)&SectionTableEntry->Name[4] == 'EDOC') {
7835  ExPoolCodeStart = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
7836  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress);
7837  ExPoolCodeEnd = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
7838  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress +
7839  Span);
7840  }
7841  else if (*(PUSHORT)&SectionTableEntry->Name[4] == 'IM') {
7842  MmPoolCodeStart = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
7843  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress);
7844  MmPoolCodeEnd = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
7845  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress +
7846  Span);
7847  }
7848  }
7849  else if ((*(PULONG)SectionTableEntry->Name == 'YSIM') &&
7850  (*(PULONG)&SectionTableEntry->Name[4] == 'ETPS')) {
7851  MmPteCodeStart = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
7852  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress);
7853  MmPteCodeEnd = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)CurrentBase +
7854  SectionTableEntry->VirtualAddress +
7855  Span);
7856  }
7857 
7858  i -= 1;
7859  SectionTableEntry += 1;
7860  }
7861 }
7862 
7863 VOID
7864 MmMakeKernelResourceSectionWritable (
7865  VOID
7866  )
7867 
7868 /*++
7869 
7870 Routine Description:
7871 
7872  This function makes the kernel's resource section readwrite so the bugcheck
7873  code can write into it.
7874 
7875 Arguments:
7876 
7877  None.
7878 
7879 Return Value:
7880 
7881  None.
7882 
7883 Environment:
7884 
7885  Kernel mode. Any IRQL.
7886 
7887 --*/
7888 
7889 {
7890 #if defined(_X86_) || defined(_AMD64_)
7891  MMPTE TempPte;
7892  MMPTE PteContents;
7893  PMMPTE PointerPte;
7894 
7895  if (MiKernelResourceStartPte == NULL) {
7896  return;
7897  }
7898 
7899  PointerPte = MiKernelResourceStartPte;
7900 
7901  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte))) {
7902 
7903  //
7904  // Mapped physically, doesn't need to be made readwrite.
7905  //
7906 
7907  return;
7908  }
7909 
7910  //
7911  // Since the entry state and IRQL are unknown, just go through the
7912  // PTEs without a lock and make them all readwrite.
7913  //
7914 
7915  do {
7916  PteContents = *PointerPte;
7917 #if defined(NT_UP)
7918  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Write == 0)
7919 #else
7920  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Writable == 0)
7921 #endif
7922  {
7923  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte,
7924  PteContents.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber,
7925  MM_READWRITE,
7926  PointerPte);
7927 #if !defined(NT_UP)
7928  TempPte.u.Hard.Writable = 1;
7929 #endif
7930  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE_NEW_PROTECTION (PointerPte, TempPte);
7931  }
7932  PointerPte += 1;
7933  } while (PointerPte < MiKernelResourceEndPte);
7934 
7935  //
7936  // Don't do this more than once.
7937  //
7938 
7939  MiKernelResourceStartPte = NULL;
7940 
7941  //
7942  // Only flush this processor as the state of the others is unknown.
7943  //
7944 
7945  MI_FLUSH_CURRENT_TB ();
7946 #endif
7947 }
7948 
7949 #ifdef i386
7950 PVOID PsNtosImageBase = (PVOID)0x80100000;
7951 #else
7952 PVOID PsNtosImageBase;
7953 #endif
7954 
7955 #if DBG
7956 PVOID PsNtosImageEnd;
7957 #endif
7958 
7959 #if defined (_WIN64)
7960 
7961 INVERTED_FUNCTION_TABLE PsInvertedFunctionTable = {
7962  0, MAXIMUM_INVERTED_FUNCTION_TABLE_SIZE, FALSE};
7963 
7964 #endif
7965 
7966 LIST_ENTRY PsLoadedModuleList;
7967 ERESOURCE PsLoadedModuleResource;
7968 
7969 LOGICAL
7970 MiInitializeLoadedModuleList (
7971  IN PLOADER_PARAMETER_BLOCK LoaderBlock
7972  )
7973 
7974 /*++
7975 
7976 Routine Description:
7977 
7978  This function initializes the loaded module list based on the LoaderBlock.
7979 
7980 Arguments:
7981 
7982  LoaderBlock - Supplies a pointer to the system loader block.
7983 
7984 Return Value:
7985 
7986  None.
7987 
7988 Environment:
7989 
7990  Kernel mode, Phase 0 Initialization.
7991 
7992 --*/
7993 
7994 {
7995  SIZE_T CommittedPages;
7996  SIZE_T DataTableEntrySize;
7997  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
7998  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntryEnd;
7999  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry1;
8000  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry2;
8001 
8002  CommittedPages = 0;
8003 
8004  //
8005  // Initialize the loaded module list executive resource and spin lock.
8006  //
8007 
8008  ExInitializeResourceLite (&PsLoadedModuleResource);
8009  KeInitializeSpinLock (&PsLoadedModuleSpinLock);
8010 
8011  InitializeListHead (&PsLoadedModuleList);
8012 
8013  //
8014  // Scan the loaded module list and allocate and initialize a data table
8015  // entry for each module. The data table entry is inserted in the loaded
8016  // module list and the initialization order list in the order specified
8017  // in the loader parameter block. The data table entry is inserted in the
8018  // memory order list in memory order.
8019  //
8020 
8021  NextEntry = LoaderBlock->LoadOrderListHead.Flink;
8022  NextEntryEnd = &LoaderBlock->LoadOrderListHead;
8023 
8024  DataTableEntry2 = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
8025  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
8026  InLoadOrderLinks);
8027 
8028  PsNtosImageBase = DataTableEntry2->DllBase;
8029 
8030 #if DBG
8031  PsNtosImageEnd = (PVOID) ((ULONG_PTR) DataTableEntry2->DllBase + DataTableEntry2->SizeOfImage);
8032 #endif
8033 
8034  MiLocateKernelSections (DataTableEntry2);
8035 
8036  while (NextEntry != NextEntryEnd) {
8037 
8038  DataTableEntry2 = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
8039  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
8040  InLoadOrderLinks);
8041 
8042  //
8043  // Allocate a data table entry.
8044  //
8045 
8046  DataTableEntrySize = sizeof (KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY) +
8047  DataTableEntry2->BaseDllName.MaximumLength + sizeof(UNICODE_NULL);
8048 
8049  DataTableEntry1 = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
8050  DataTableEntrySize,
8051  'dLmM');
8052 
8053  if (DataTableEntry1 == NULL) {
8054  return FALSE;
8055  }
8056 
8057  //
8058  // Copy the data table entry.
8059  //
8060 
8061  *DataTableEntry1 = *DataTableEntry2;
8062 
8063  //
8064  // Clear fields we may use later so they don't inherit irrelevant
8065  // loader values.
8066  //
8067 
8068  ((PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY)DataTableEntry1)->NonPagedDebugInfo = NULL;
8069  DataTableEntry1->PatchInformation = NULL;
8070 
8071  DataTableEntry1->FullDllName.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool,
8072  DataTableEntry2->FullDllName.MaximumLength + sizeof(UNICODE_NULL),
8073  'TDmM');
8074 
8075  if (DataTableEntry1->FullDllName.Buffer == NULL) {
8076  ExFreePool (DataTableEntry1);
8077  return FALSE;
8078  }
8079 
8080  DataTableEntry1->BaseDllName.Buffer = (PWSTR)((ULONG_PTR)DataTableEntry1 + sizeof (KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY));
8081 
8082  //
8083  // Copy the strings.
8084  //
8085 
8086  RtlCopyMemory (DataTableEntry1->FullDllName.Buffer,
8087  DataTableEntry2->FullDllName.Buffer,
8088  DataTableEntry1->FullDllName.MaximumLength);
8089 
8090  RtlCopyMemory (DataTableEntry1->BaseDllName.Buffer,
8091  DataTableEntry2->BaseDllName.Buffer,
8092  DataTableEntry1->BaseDllName.MaximumLength);
8093 
8094  DataTableEntry1->BaseDllName.Buffer[DataTableEntry1->BaseDllName.Length/sizeof(WCHAR)] = UNICODE_NULL;
8095 
8096  //
8097  // Always charge commitment regardless of whether we were able to
8098  // relocate the driver, use large pages, etc.
8099  //
8100 
8101  CommittedPages += (DataTableEntry1->SizeOfImage >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8102 
8103  //
8104  // Calculate exception pointers
8105  //
8106 
8107  MiCaptureImageExceptionValues(DataTableEntry1);
8108 
8109  //
8110  // Insert the data table entry in the load order list in the order
8111  // they are specified.
8112  //
8113 
8114  InsertTailList (&PsLoadedModuleList,
8115  &DataTableEntry1->InLoadOrderLinks);
8116 
8117 #if defined (_WIN64)
8118 
8119  RtlInsertInvertedFunctionTable (&PsInvertedFunctionTable,
8120  DataTableEntry1->DllBase,
8121  DataTableEntry1->SizeOfImage);
8122 
8123 #endif
8124 
8125  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
8126  }
8127 
8128  //
8129  // Charge commitment for each boot loaded driver so that if unloads
8130  // later, the return will balance. Note that the actual number of
8131  // free pages is not changing now so the commit limits need to be
8132  // bumped by the same amount.
8133  //
8134  // Resident available does not need to be charged here because it
8135  // has been already (by virtue of being snapped from available pages).
8136  //
8137 
8138  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_LOAD_SYSTEM_IMAGE_TEMP, CommittedPages);
8139 
8140  MmTotalCommittedPages += CommittedPages;
8141  MmTotalCommitLimit += CommittedPages;
8142  MmTotalCommitLimitMaximum += CommittedPages;
8143 
8144  MiBuildImportsForBootDrivers ();
8145 
8146  return TRUE;
8147 }
8148 
8149 NTSTATUS
8150 MmCallDllInitialize (
8151  IN PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry,
8152  IN PLIST_ENTRY ModuleListHead
8153  )
8154 
8155 /*++
8156 
8157 Routine Description:
8158 
8159  This function calls the DLL's initialize routine.
8160 
8161 Arguments:
8162 
8163  DataTableEntry - Supplies the kernel's data table entry.
8164 
8165 Return Value:
8166 
8167  Various NTSTATUS error codes.
8168 
8169 Environment:
8170 
8171  Kernel mode.
8172 
8173 --*/
8174 
8175 {
8176  NTSTATUS st;
8177  PWCHAR Dot;
8178  PMM_DLL_INITIALIZE Func;
8179  UNICODE_STRING RegistryPath;
8180  UNICODE_STRING ImportName;
8181  ULONG ThunksAdded;
8182 
8183  Func = (PMM_DLL_INITIALIZE)(ULONG_PTR)MiLocateExportName (DataTableEntry->DllBase, "DllInitialize");
8184 
8185  if (!Func) {
8186  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
8187  }
8188 
8189  ImportName.MaximumLength = DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.Length;
8190  ImportName.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
8191  ImportName.MaximumLength,
8192  'TDmM');
8193 
8194  if (ImportName.Buffer == NULL) {
8195  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
8196  }
8197 
8198  ImportName.Length = DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.Length;
8199  RtlCopyMemory (ImportName.Buffer,
8200  DataTableEntry->BaseDllName.Buffer,
8201  ImportName.Length);
8202 
8203  RegistryPath.MaximumLength = (USHORT)(CmRegistryMachineSystemCurrentControlSetServices.Length +
8204  ImportName.Length +
8205  2*sizeof(WCHAR));
8206 
8207  RegistryPath.Buffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
8208  RegistryPath.MaximumLength,
8209  'TDmM');
8210 
8211  if (RegistryPath.Buffer == NULL) {
8212  ExFreePool (ImportName.Buffer);
8213  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
8214  }
8215 
8216  RegistryPath.Length = CmRegistryMachineSystemCurrentControlSetServices.Length;
8217  RtlCopyMemory (RegistryPath.Buffer,
8218  CmRegistryMachineSystemCurrentControlSetServices.Buffer,
8219  CmRegistryMachineSystemCurrentControlSetServices.Length);
8220 
8221  RtlAppendUnicodeToString (&RegistryPath, (const PUSHORT)L"\\");
8222  Dot = wcschr (ImportName.Buffer, L'.');
8223  if (Dot) {
8224  ImportName.Length = (USHORT)((Dot - ImportName.Buffer) * sizeof(WCHAR));
8225  }
8226 
8227  RtlAppendUnicodeStringToString (&RegistryPath, &ImportName);
8228  ExFreePool (ImportName.Buffer);
8229 
8230  //
8231  // Save the number of verifier thunks currently added so we know
8232  // if this activation adds any. To extend the thunk list, the module
8233  // performs an NtSetSystemInformation call which calls back to the
8234  // verifier's MmAddVerifierThunks, which increments MiVerifierThunksAdded.
8235  //
8236 
8237  ThunksAdded = MiVerifierThunksAdded;
8238 
8239  //
8240  // Invoke the DLL's initialization routine.
8241  //
8242 
8243  st = Func (&RegistryPath);
8244 
8245  ExFreePool (RegistryPath.Buffer);
8246 
8247  //
8248  // If the module's initialization routine succeeded, and if it extended
8249  // the verifier thunk list, and this is boot time, reapply the verifier
8250  // to the loaded modules.
8251  //
8252  // Note that boot time is the special case because after boot time, Mm
8253  // loads all the DLLs itself and a DLL initialize is thus guaranteed to
8254  // complete and add its thunks before the importing driver load finishes.
8255  // Since the importing driver is only thunked after its load finishes,
8256  // ordering implicitly guarantees that all DLL-registered thunks are
8257  // properly factored in to the importing driver.
8258  //
8259  // Boot time is special because the loader (not the Mm) already loaded
8260  // the DLLs *AND* the importing drivers so we have to look over our
8261  // shoulder and make it all right after the fact.
8262  //
8263 
8264  if ((NT_SUCCESS(st)) &&
8265  (MiFirstDriverLoadEver == 0) &&
8266  (MiVerifierThunksAdded != ThunksAdded)) {
8267 
8268  MiReApplyVerifierToLoadedModules (ModuleListHead);
8269  }
8270 
8271  return st;
8272 }
8273 
8274 NTKERNELAPI
8275 PVOID
8276 MmGetSystemRoutineAddress (
8277  __in PUNICODE_STRING SystemRoutineName
8278  )
8279 
8280 /*++
8281 
8282 Routine Description:
8283 
8284  This function returns the address of the argument function pointer if
8285  it is in the kernel or HAL, NULL if it is not.
8286 
8287 Arguments:
8288 
8289  SystemRoutineName - Supplies the name of the desired routine.
8290 
8291 Return Value:
8292 
8293  Non-NULL function pointer if successful. NULL if not.
8294 
8295 Environment:
8296 
8297  Kernel mode, PASSIVE_LEVEL, arbitrary process context.
8298 
8299 --*/
8300 
8301 {
8302  PKTHREAD CurrentThread;
8303  NTSTATUS Status;
8304  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
8305  ANSI_STRING AnsiString;
8306  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
8307  UNICODE_STRING KernelString;
8308  UNICODE_STRING HalString;
8309  PVOID FunctionAddress;
8310  LOGICAL Found;
8311  ULONG EntriesChecked;
8312 
8313  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() == PASSIVE_LEVEL);
8314 
8315  EntriesChecked = 0;
8316  FunctionAddress = NULL;
8317 
8318  KernelString.Buffer = (const PUSHORT) KERNEL_NAME;
8319  KernelString.Length = sizeof (KERNEL_NAME) - sizeof (WCHAR);
8320  KernelString.MaximumLength = sizeof KERNEL_NAME;
8321 
8322  HalString.Buffer = (const PUSHORT) HAL_NAME;
8323  HalString.Length = sizeof (HAL_NAME) - sizeof (WCHAR);
8324  HalString.MaximumLength = sizeof HAL_NAME;
8325 
8326  do {
8327  Status = RtlUnicodeStringToAnsiString (&AnsiString,
8328  SystemRoutineName,
8329  TRUE);
8330 
8331  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
8332  break;
8333  }
8334 
8335  KeDelayExecutionThread (KernelMode, FALSE, (PLARGE_INTEGER)&MmShortTime);
8336 
8337  } while (TRUE);
8338 
8339  //
8340  // Arbitrary process context so prevent suspend APCs now.
8341  //
8342 
8343  CurrentThread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
8344  KeEnterCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
8345  ExAcquireResourceSharedLite (&PsLoadedModuleResource, TRUE);
8346 
8347  //
8348  // Check only the kernel and the HAL for exports.
8349  //
8350 
8351  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Flink;
8352  while (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
8353 
8354  Found = FALSE;
8355 
8356  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
8357  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
8358  InLoadOrderLinks);
8359 
8360  if (RtlEqualUnicodeString (&KernelString,
8361  &DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
8362  TRUE)) {
8363 
8364  Found = TRUE;
8365  EntriesChecked += 1;
8366 
8367  }
8368  else if (RtlEqualUnicodeString (&HalString,
8369  &DataTableEntry->BaseDllName,
8370  TRUE)) {
8371 
8372  Found = TRUE;
8373  EntriesChecked += 1;
8374  }
8375 
8376  if (Found == TRUE) {
8377 
8378  FunctionAddress = MiFindExportedRoutineByName (DataTableEntry->DllBase,
8379  &AnsiString);
8380 
8381  if (FunctionAddress != NULL) {
8382  break;
8383  }
8384 
8385  if (EntriesChecked == 2) {
8386  break;
8387  }
8388  }
8389 
8390  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
8391  }
8392 
8393  ExReleaseResourceLite (&PsLoadedModuleResource);
8394  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
8395 
8396  RtlFreeAnsiString (&AnsiString);
8397 
8398  return FunctionAddress;
8399 }
8400 
8401 PVOID
8402 MiFindExportedRoutineByName (
8403  IN PVOID DllBase,
8404  IN PANSI_STRING AnsiImageRoutineName
8405  )
8406 
8407 /*++
8408 
8409 Routine Description:
8410 
8411  This function searches the argument module looking for the requested
8412  exported function name.
8413 
8414 Arguments:
8415 
8416  DllBase - Supplies the base address of the requested module.
8417 
8418  AnsiImageRoutineName - Supplies the ANSI routine name being searched for.
8419 
8420 Return Value:
8421 
8422  The virtual address of the requested routine or NULL if not found.
8423 
8424 --*/
8425 
8426 {
8427  USHORT OrdinalNumber;
8428  PULONG NameTableBase;
8429  PUSHORT NameOrdinalTableBase;
8430  PULONG Addr;
8431  LONG High;
8432  LONG Low;
8433  LONG Middle;
8434  LONG Result;
8435  ULONG ExportSize;
8436  PVOID FunctionAddress;
8437  PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY ExportDirectory;
8438 
8439  PAGED_CODE();
8440 
8441  ExportDirectory = (PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY) RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (
8442  DllBase,
8443  TRUE,
8444  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT,
8445  &ExportSize);
8446 
8447  if (ExportDirectory == NULL) {
8448  return NULL;
8449  }
8450 
8451  //
8452  // Initialize the pointer to the array of RVA-based ansi export strings.
8453  //
8454 
8455  NameTableBase = (PULONG)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfNames);
8456 
8457  //
8458  // Initialize the pointer to the array of USHORT ordinal numbers.
8459  //
8460 
8461  NameOrdinalTableBase = (PUSHORT)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfNameOrdinals);
8462 
8463  //
8464  // Lookup the desired name in the name table using a binary search.
8465  //
8466 
8467  Low = 0;
8468  Middle = 0;
8469  High = ExportDirectory->NumberOfNames - 1;
8470 
8471  while (High >= Low) {
8472 
8473  //
8474  // Compute the next probe index and compare the import name
8475  // with the export name entry.
8476  //
8477 
8478  Middle = (Low + High) >> 1;
8479 
8480  Result = strcmp (AnsiImageRoutineName->Buffer,
8481  (PCHAR)DllBase + NameTableBase[Middle]);
8482 
8483  if (Result < 0) {
8484  High = Middle - 1;
8485  }
8486  else if (Result > 0) {
8487  Low = Middle + 1;
8488  }
8489  else {
8490  break;
8491  }
8492  }
8493 
8494  //
8495  // If the high index is less than the low index, then a matching
8496  // table entry was not found. Otherwise, get the ordinal number
8497  // from the ordinal table.
8498  //
8499 
8500  if (High < Low) {
8501  return NULL;
8502  }
8503 
8504  OrdinalNumber = NameOrdinalTableBase[Middle];
8505 
8506  //
8507  // If the OrdinalNumber is not within the Export Address Table,
8508  // then this image does not implement the function. Return not found.
8509  //
8510 
8511  if ((ULONG)OrdinalNumber >= ExportDirectory->NumberOfFunctions) {
8512  return NULL;
8513  }
8514 
8515  //
8516  // Index into the array of RVA export addresses by ordinal number.
8517  //
8518 
8519  Addr = (PULONG)((PCHAR)DllBase + (ULONG)ExportDirectory->AddressOfFunctions);
8520 
8521  FunctionAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)DllBase + Addr[OrdinalNumber]);
8522 
8523  //
8524  // Forwarders are not used by the kernel and HAL to each other.
8525  //
8526 
8527  ASSERT ((FunctionAddress <= (PVOID)ExportDirectory) ||
8528  (FunctionAddress >= (PVOID)((PCHAR)ExportDirectory + ExportSize)));
8529 
8530  return FunctionAddress;
8531 }
